title: CEPEX AVHRR Imagery over Fiji
summary: This data set contains the processed high resolution NOAA-11 and NOAA-12 AVHRR data collected in real-time by the SeaSpace system on Fiji during CEPEX. The images have been calibrated to radiances, and the earth navigation and satellite viewing angles have been added in NOAA LAC (Local Area Coverage) format. Each image has been split into 512 line components for easier handling, and these component images have been converted to NetCDF. Approx 3-4 overpasses occurred near Fiji daily. The entire data set is available on nine 8-mm data tapes.

title: CEPEX GMS Imagery (Fiji)
summary: This dataset contains processed Japanese GMS-4 geostationary satellite imagery collected by the SeaSpace Terascan system in Nandi, Fiji, during CEPEX. The images have been post processed using Terascan software and converted to NetCDF. The post processing includes calibration, projection onto a regular equal-angle grid covering the CEPEX domain. The imagery are generally hourly and the data set are archived on two 8-mm tapes.

title: VORTEX-95 GOES IR Satellite Images (GIF)
summary: GOES-8 IR imagery collected during the VORTEX-95 period via PC-McIDAS and then converted to GIF image format. These data are available for browsing purposes.

title: VORTEX-95 GOES-8 2-km Vis Imagery (GIF)
summary: Digital GOES-8 2-km visible imagery for selected case days during VORTEX-95. These data are in GIF format for browsing purposes.

title: VORTEX-95 WSI NOWRAD Radar Composites
summary: WSI provided PPI reflectivity data composited from  individual NWS radars (NOWRAD) every 15 minutes at 2 KM resolution during VORTEX-95.  A fixed regional sector was  collected.  These data are in McIDAS format.

title: VORTEX-95 GOES-8 Visible Imagery
summary: This dataset contains GOES-8 Visible imagery collected  during the VORTEX-95 Field program.  These data were collected at 2 KM resolution every 15 minutes from a fixed sector over the VORTEX-95 region.  These data are in McIDAS format

title: GCIP/GIST Station List
summary: List of stations whose data are included in the GCIP/GIST data sets. List includes station name, latitude, longitude,elevation, station type, observing network ID, and station id.

title: MICROFRONTS NCAR/ASTER HotWire Data

title: CEPEX ER-2 Cloud Lidar System (CLS)(RAW)
summary: The Cloud Lidar System (CLS) was flown aboard the ER-2 to conduct cloud radiation measurements during CEPEX. The  instrument was designed to operate at high altitudes  in order to obtain measurements above the highest clouds  providing the true height of cloud boundaries and the  density structure of less dense clouds. The height  structure of cirrus, cloud top density and multiple cloud layers are also provided. The laser type was ND:YAG I,II.  These data are the original binary files taken directly from the lidar system.  Principal Investigator was Dr. James Spinhirne.

title: CEPEX NCAR Electra Video Tapes
summary: This dataset contains VHS format video tapes recorded from two side-looking and one forward-looking video camera  systems mounted on the NCAR Electra during CEPEX. The side- looking systems consisted of General Electric model  1CVK5040 color camera with date/time recording. The  forward-looking cockpit mounted system consisted of a Minolta color camera with JVC recorder. A total of 10 missions are included in the archive.

title: CEPEX Lear Jet Video Tapes
summary: This dataset contains VHS format video tapes recorded from a downward-looking video camera system mounted on the Lear Jet during CEPEX. The system consisted of a Panasonic CCTV model WV-1460 camera with Panasonic model WJ-810 time code generator and Canon model VR-30A portable video recorder (VHS). One video tape has been recorded per mission, for a  total of 19 tapes in the archive.

title: CEPEX NMC Sea Surface Temperature Fields
summary: This dataset contains daily fields of Sea Surface Temperature (SST) produced by the National Meteorological Center (NMC) collected during CEPEX. These SST fields came from NMC's Oceanic Products Set. When available, both grid resolutions of 2.5 x 5.0 and 2.0 x 2.0 degree fields were collected. There are 5 vertical levels for relative humidity; 10 vertical levels for other parameters. The model output contains 1 analyzed field followed by 9-10 forecast fields for each 12-hour run.

title: CEPEX NOAA P-3 Aircraft Video Tapes
summary: This dataset contains VHS format video tapes recorded from a forward-looking video camera system mounted on the P-3 during CEPEX. The portable camera recorded the video on 8mm master tapes, which were later copied to Video Home System (VHS) format. Each tape is approximately 2 hours. There are a total of 13 missions in the archive.

title: GCIP/GIDS-1 Illinois Soil Moisture Data
summary: This dataset contains soil moisture measurments from  approximately 22 sites in the state of Illinois (U.S.A). The data are measured in 11 layers ranging from 0 to 200 centimeters.

title: STORM-FEST GOES Satellite Imagery (GIF)
summary: GOES-7 IR imagery collected during the STORM-FEST period via PC-McIDAS and then converted to GIF image format. These data are available for browsing purposes.

title: GCIP/GIDS-1 GOES Satellite Imagery (GIF)
summary: GOES-7 IR imagery collected during the GCIP/GIDS-1 period via PC-McIDAS and then converted to GIF image format. These data are available for browsing purposes.

title: VORTEX-94 GOES Satellite Imagery (GIF)
summary: GOES-7 IR imagery collected during the VORTEX period via PC-McIDAS and then converted to GIF image format. These data are available for browsing purposes.

title: VORTEX-94 GOES-7 1-km VIS Images (GIF)
summary: Digital GOES-7 1-km visible imagery for selected case days during VORTEX-94. Also includes 2-km data for all project days. These data are in GIF format for browsing purposes.

summary: NMC/CAC 500 mb Analysis (AKA Daily Weather Maps") for the STORM-FEST period. Maps were scanned from the CAC Daily  Weather Map Series publication with the permission of NOAA/ NMC/CAC."

summary: NMC/CAC Surface Analysis (AKA Daily Weather Maps") for the GCIP/GIDS-1 period. Maps were scanned from the CAC Daily  Weather Map Series publication with the permission of NOAA/ NMC/CAC."

title: GCIP/GIDS-1 CAC 500mb Analyses (GIF)
summary: NMC/CAC 500 mb Analysis (AKA Daily Weather Maps") for the GCIP/GIDS-1 period. Maps were scanned from the CAC Daily  Weather Map Series publication with the permission of NOAA/ NMC/CAC."

title: GCIP/GIDS-1 EDC AVHRR Land Cover (GIF)
summary: This dataset consists of monthly GIF images of Land Cover  (vegetation) provided by the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS), EROS Data Center (EDC).  These Land Cover mosaics were produced from AVHRR imagery and are but a sample of the detailed land cover  database available from EDC on CD-ROM.

summary: NMC eta Model 1000mb Analyses for the VORTEX period.

title: CAPE Florida Agricultural Data
summary: Florida Department of Agriculture coordinates a network of stations at ag research sites in central Florida.  Data consists of temperature, humidity, wind speed/direction, solar radiation, evaporation and various soil temperature/ moisture measurements (all 24 h).  Also the Ridge Automated Weather Network measured temperature and winds (9 & 15 m), surface temperature and soil temperature (10 & 50 cm) at 5 min intervals.

title: CAPE USGS Raingauge data
summary: US Geological Survey data consist of various networks of precipitation and stream flow stations in central Florida as part of their geologic/hydrologic assessment program. Stations concentrated in Melbourne/Tampa Bay river inlets and Orlando.  Time resolution varies from 5 min to 1 h. Stream flow data both manual and automatic.

title: STORM-FEST Raw ASOS Network Data, Hourly
summary: NWS,FAA and US Navy installed 45 ASOS stations in the KansasOklahoma area by the end of STORM-FEST.  Data consists of hourly air temperature, dewpoint, wind speed/direction, barometric pressure, altimeter, density altitude, visibilitysky conditions and precipitation.  Only a few sites were officially commissioned during STORM-FEST so caution should be exercised in the use of this data.

title: STORM-FEST ASOS Data (Topeka) (RAW)
summary: The ASOS station at Topeka KS provided 1 min resolution measurements of temperature, dewpoint, wind speed/direction,barometric pressure, altimeter, density altitude, visibilitysky conditions and precipitation. No QC has been applied to this dataset.

title: STORM-FEST AWOS Data (Iowa) (RAW)
summary: The Iowa DOT collected 1 min resolution data for the Iowa AWOS stations.  Data is in original format with no QC.  The data consits of temperature, dewpoint, altimeter, visibilitysky conditions, wind speed/direction, barometric pressure, density altitude and precipitation.

title: STORM-FEST High Plains Climate Data(RAW)
summary: The High Plains Climate Network consists of 86 automatic weather stations in Nebraska, Kansas, Iowa, North Dakota, South Dakota, Colorado and Wyoming.  Data consists of hourlyaverages of temperature, humidity, wind speed/direction, solar radiation, soil temperature and total precipitation.

title: STORM-FEST ASOS Network Data, 5-Min(RAW)
summary: The NWS, FAA and US Navy installed 45 ASOS stations in the  STORM-FEST region by the end of the project, few of these   stations were officially commissioned, so the data should beused with caution.  The data consists of 5 min averages of  temperature, dewpoint, wind speed/direction, barometric  pressure, altimeter, density altitude, visibility, sky conditions and precipitation.  Visibility and sky conditionsused 30 min running averages.

title: STORM-FEST PROFS Data, 5-Min(RAW)
summary: NOAA/FSL operates a 22 station network in Northeastern  CO.  Data consists of 5 min averages of temperature, wind speed/direction, dewpoint, barometric pressure, solar  radiation and precipitation (5 min total).

title: CaPE AWOS Data
summary: Six stations collected: a) 20 min data at St. Augustine, Naples, Sarasota and Marco; b) 5 min data at Ocala and c) 1 min data at Kissimmee.  Parameters include: temperature,  dewpoint, altimeter, visibility, wind speed/direction,    barometric pressure, sky conditions and density altitude.

title: STORM-FEST USDA Little Washita Prcp(RAW)
summary: The USDA/ARS precipitation network is within the scanning range of two WSR-88Ds and consists of 44 raingages over 230 square miles in the Little Washita watershed in central OK. They employ chart recorder gages.  Weekly charts digitized into 5 min time and 0.01 inch resolution and underwent QC.

title: STORM-FEST USGS Streamflow Gages (?)
summary: The USGS located a streamflow gauging station at the outflowof the Little Washita Watershed and at the outflow of an upstream, smaller imbedded watershed, that was part of the Little Washita Basin.  The data consists of a continuous record of stage, individual measurements of discharge throughout a range of stages and notations regarding factorsthat may affect the relationships between stage and  discharge.

title: STORM-FEST NSSL Disdrometer Data
summary: A linear array of 3 disdrometers was installed and operated for STORM-FEST near Chickasha, Oklahoma.  They were located at various spacing to relate scale discontinuties with  radar; accessing space-time varibility of stratiform precip.A drop size distribution was recorded after 1000 drops struck the disdrometer with a size resolution of 0.1 mm.

title: STORM-FEST AWOS Network (Handar)(RAW)
summary: The original Handar AWOS format with no QC for the 48 AWOS sites in the STORM-FEST area.  Data consist of 20 min  averages of temperature, dewpoint, altimeter, visibility, wind speed/direction, barometric pressure, sky conditions, density altitude and precipitation.  Winds were averaged  using a 2-5 min running mean, cloud heights a 30 min runningmean.

title: STORM-FEST Qualimetrics AWOS (RAW)
summary: The original Qualimetrics AWOS format with no QC of the 48 AWOS sites in the STORM-FEST area.  Data consists of 20 min averages of temperature, dewpoint, altimeter, visibility, wind speed/direction, barometric pressure, sky conditions, density altitude and precipitation.  Winds averaged using a 2-5 min running mean, cloud heights a 30 min running mean.

title: STORM-FEST Pacific Dropsonde Data (RAW)
summary: USAF deployed about 200 dropsondes during STORM-FEST over the northeast Pacific Ocean at about 30000 feet. Data consists of pressure, temperature, relative humidity and wind speed/direction. Following STORM-FEST the highest resolution (10 sec) data was converted to NCAR CLASS format.

title: STORM-FEST WPL Boundary Layer Profilers
summary: NOAA/WPL operated 5 boundary layer profilers (915 MHz) in the STORM-FEST boundary layer network near Seneca KS. They were equipped with RASS and provided vertical profiles of winds and temperature at 30 min intervals. Winds were measured at 100 m resolution gates from 0.2 - 3.1 km and at 400 m reslution from 0.4 - 5 km. Temperatures from RASS were measured up to about 2 km.

title: CaPE NWS Tampa Bay MicroArt rawinsonde
summary: Routine (00, 12 UTC) rawinsonde soundings were taken by the NWS at TBW.  In addition, special 3 h interval soundings were taken to support CaPE.  Data consists of vertical  profiles of pressure, temperature, relative humidity and  wind speed/direction with 6 sec vertical resolution.

title: CaPE North Carolina State Minisonde Data
summary: NCS operated a Minisonde from 26 July through 6 August (10 flights). The site was at CCAFS. The data consists of vertical profiles of pressure, temperature, dew point, potential temperature, relative humidity and height (no winds) with approximately 5 sec resloution.

title: STORM-FEST NPGS Picket Fence Sondes(RAW)
summary: NPGS coordinated a network of 7 special and 8 operational (NWS, military and AES) rawinsonde stations along the west coast from California to British Columbia. Soundings were 3 hourly for 4 IOPs. Data consists of 10 sec vertical resolution pressure, temperature, relative humidity and windspeed/direction.

title: CaPE USAF Cape Canaveral Rawinsonde Data
summary: MSS rawinsonde data from the CCAFS include routine daily    soundings (3 weekday; 2 weekend) and special CaPE and USAF/ NASA soundings.  Data consist of vertical profiles of wind  speed/direction, pressure, temperature and relative humidityTwo datasets were collected; 1000 gpf (all) and 6 s (thermo only).

title: CaPE University of Lowell Rawinsondes
summary: University of Lowell's 386SX PC-based Vaisala LORAN rawin-  sonde data at the Orlando Airport typically includes 4      launches per day (1100-1900 UTC).  The data consists of 10  sec resolution vertical profiles of pressure, temperature,  relative humidity and wind speed/direction.

title: STORM-FEST WSR-88D Archive II Radar
summary: WSR-88D 10 cm wavelength Doppler radar data were collected from the following sites during STORM-FEST (in OK Twin Lakes (KTLX), Fredrick and Norman (KFDR); and St. Louis). St. Louis started on 4 March and has no Archive II data. The data consists of radar reflectivity and velocity spectra for each full volume scan (every 5-10 min). The user is referred directly to NCDC.

title: STORM-FEST NWS WSR-57 Digital Data
summary: NWS WSR-57 radars at St. Louis and Grand Island were interfaced with digitizers. The digitized PPI and volume scan reflectivity data were recorded. Recorders were activated at the request of STORM-FEST. One data tape is available for each station, containing all the data collected at the station during STORM-FEST.

title: STORM-FEST WSI NOWRAD Radar Composites
summary: WSI provides PPI reflectivity data from individual NWS  radars and regional NWS radar composites (NOWRAD) every 15 min during STORM-FEST.  A fixed regional sector (STORM-FEST inner domain) and a floater sector were collected via PC- McIDAS.

title: STORM-FEST NWS RADAP II Digital Data
summary: *** This data nver received at OFPS *** 5 NWS 10 cm non-coherent wavelength NWS WSR57 radars around the STORM-FEST area were equipped with RADAP II, which automatically controlled radar operation and aquired 15 min tilt sequence volume scan data of low level PPI and  volumetric reflectivity at a resolution of 2 deg by 1 nautical mile range from 10 - 125 nautical miles.

title: STORM-FEST Cimarron Doppler Digital Data
summary: Cimarron is a 10 cm wavelength Doppler radar that operated in coordination with other radars in the STORM-FEST region to obtain dual-Doppler data.  Reflectivity and velocity spectra data were collected for a total of approximately 26 hours during STORM-FEST.

title: VORTEX-94 Station List
summary: List of stations whose data are included in the VORTEX data sets. List includes station name, latitude, longitude,elevation, station type, observing network ID, and station id.

title: CaPE WSI Radar Composites
summary: Data includes WSI's routine transmission of PPI reflectivityimagery for individual NWS radars and national/regional NWS radar composites (NOWRAD) every 15 min.  Data in two formatsPC-McIDAS (8 bit) and WSI PC (4 bit).

title: CaPE GOES-7 VIS/IR/MSI Imagery
summary: GOES-7 imagery consist of 30 min visible (1 and 4 km),      infrared (4 km) and multi-spectral imagery (8 km; mostly    3-hourly).  There are two data formats McIDAS and GARS.

title: CaPE GOES-7 RISOP (Rapid Scan) Imagery
summary: Rapid Interval Scan Operations Plan (RISOP) periods provide visible, infrared and multi-spectral imagery at up to 5 min intervals.  Seventeen RISOP periods were called during CaPE.

title: STORM-FEST GOES-7 Image Loop Video Films
summary: FSU developed 3 VHS format videos containing loops of 8 km resolution GOES-7 visible, infrared and MSI channel 10 data over the central US during STORM-FEST.  Tapes contain daily loops of 1 hour interval 8-bit imagery.  Some navigational errors may be evident.

title: STORM-FEST GOES-7 1-km Visible Imagery
summary: Digital recordings of daily GOES-7 1-km visible imagery thatwere produced during STORM-FEST from the NSSFC Wideword  workstation.  These data are in McIDAS format.

title: STORM-FEST GOES-7 8-km Infrared Imagery
summary: Digital recordings of daily GOES-7 8-km infrared imagery  that were produced during STORM-FEST from the NSSFC  Wideword workstation.  These data are in McIDAS format.

title: STORM-FEST GOES-7 8-km Channel 10 Images
summary: Digital recordings of daily GOES-7 8-km Channel 10 imagery  that were produced during STORM-FEST from the NSSFC  Wideword workstation.  These data are in McIDAS format.

title: STORM-FEST GOES-7 8-km Visible Imagery
summary: Digital recordings of daily GOES-7 8-km visible imagery thatwere produced during STORM-FEST from the NSSFC Wideword  workstation.  These data are in McIDAS format.

title: STORM-FEST GOES-7 Precipitable Water
summary: Digital recordings of daily GOES-7 precipitable water  imagery that were produced during STORM-FEST from the NSSFC Wideword workstation.  These data are in McIDAS format.

title: CaPE GOES-7 Image Loop Video Films
summary: FSU produced 4 VHS video tapes of 1 km resolution visible   imagery over central Florida.  Tapes used 8 bit imagery fromFSUs GOES direct Readout Groundstation.  Some navigational  errors are present, thus should be used for browse and not  quantitatively.

title: CaPE DMSP SSM/I Data and Imagery
summary: DMSP consists of three near polar orbiting satellites that provide global microwave data from the Special Sensor Micro-wave Imager.  SSM/I provides water vapor measurements (1400 km swath) at three frequencies (19.35, 37.0 and 85.5 GHz). Up to 4 DMSP overpasses of the Florida area were made daily.

title: MICROFRONTS GOES-8 and NOWRAD Imagery
summary: This dataset contains GOES-8 imagery collected during the Microfronts Field program. Included in this dataset are Visible, Infrared, Water Vapor, and Fog products from GOES-8, as well as 15-minute WSI radar composite imagery. See the readme file for this dataset for more details about the individual sensor characteristics.

title: VORTEX-95 GOES IR Satellite Images
summary: GOES-8 IR imagery collected during the VORTEX-95 period via PC-McIDAS.  Images are generally available every 15 minutes.  Files are stored on the tape in compressed McIDAS format.

title: VORTEX-95 GOES-8 Water Vapor
summary: Digital GOES-8 water vapor imagery that were  collected during VORTEX-95.  These data are in  McIDAS format.

title: CaPE USSR Meteor-2 Satellite Data
summary: Imagery from the USSR Meteor-2/3 polar-orbiting satellite   was available up to 6 times/day depending on proximity to   CaPE region and signal scrambling.  Visible imagery (2100-  2600 km swath; 2 km resolution) was collected via PC in bothglossy images and PC format GIFs.

title: STORM-FEST NOAA WP-3D Cloud Microphysics
summary: NOAA/AOC operated a Lockheed Orion WP-3D from 5 Feb through 10 March 1992 for STORM-FEST (9 flights).  The plane  carried a tail 3 cm wavelength Doppler radar and a 5 cm  wavelength lower fuselage non-coherent radar.

title: STORM-FEST NOAA WP-3D Radar Data
summary: NOAA/AOC WP-3D aircraft carried a 5 cm horizontally scanninglower fuselage radar (reflectivity) and a 3 cm vertically scanning tail radar (reflecitivity and velocity).  Both werethree axis stabilized and covered the full 360 deg of azimuth.

title: STORM-FEST NOAA WP-3D Flight Level Data
summary: NOAA/AOC operated a Lockheed Orion WP-3D turboprop from 5  Feb - 10 March 1992 (9 flights).  The flight level data consists of housekeeping (time, position and performance) and state parameters (temperature, moisture and winds) at 1-sec resolution.

title: CaPE Daily Operation Logs
summary: Daily operations logs were produced in the field to  summarize CaPE operations and note events of key interest. These logs incorporated input from various PI's and the  CaPE Operations Director.  The logs contained a brief  meteorlogical overview, with a synopsis of all data.

title: STORM-FEST NCAR Mesoscale Model (MM4)
summary: The NCAR/PSU Mesoscale Model (MM4) was used to develop  research model forecasts up to 36 h (1 h intervals) at 20 kmresolution over the STORM-FEST domain.  MM4 ran every 24 h (12 UTC) and at 00 UTC as directed.  The data cutoff for themodel runs was 1.5 h.

title: VORTEX-94 MAPS Surface Analyses
summary: NOAA/FSL ran the MAPS Sfc Analysis every hour at a standard resolution of about 60 km. These fields are used as part of the initialization of the O-LAPS. The data cutoff for the model runs was about 1 hour.

title: CaPE Site Activity Logs
summary: Site activity logs were maintained at each operational      facility to document operations and key items of interest   that might affect data collection and quality control. When possible logs were collected in digital form.

title: VORTEX-95 Oklahoma LAPS
summary: O-LAPS ingest, quality controls and analyzes conventional and research data for use in real-time storm-scale forecast experiments.  Fields include sfc pressure, temp, humidity  and wind analysis.  This dataset was run during the VORTEX-95 field program.

title: CaPE Principal Investigator Notes/Logs
summary: Individual PI's maintained and archived their own logs and  notes during CaPE.  Some are digital, but most are in paper logbooks.

title: CaPE Sky Photography and Video
summary: Routine sky photography was taken at 5 primary sites KSC,   Melbourne Beach, CP-2, CP-3 and CP-4 radar sites.  These included 35 mm slides, 16 mm time lapse video (usually 10 or30 second frames) and movie or video cameras at coastal     sites.  Also a time lapse video was taken from a camera at  KSC.

title: STORM-FEST Canadian Soundings
summary: Routine 12 hourly and selected special 6 hourly soundings  from 9 Canadian AES stations in western Canada.  The data consists of 10 sec resolution data as well as mandatory and significant levels of pressure, temperature, relative humidity and wind speed/direction.  Following STORM-FEST  the data were converted to NCAR CLASS format.

title: NMC Surface Land Data (IIa), Hourly
summary: Sea level and station pressure, wind speed/direction, air   temperature, dewpoint, present weather, past weather, cloud data, pressure tendency and six-hourly precipitation taken  at manual and automatic NMC,FAA,DOD,Coast Guard,Canadian andMexican sites.

title: NMC North American Surface Analyses
summary: Surface analyses of the North America.

title: MICROFRONTS GOES-8 IR Images (GIF)
summary: GOES-8 Infrared (11 micron) satellite imagery collected for the 1995 MICROFRONTS experiment via McIDAS-X and then  converted to GIF image format. These images are at 4 km  resolution.  These data are available for browsing purposes.

title: MICROFRONTS GOES-8 VIS Images (GIF)
summary: GOES-8 Visible satellite imagery collected for the 1995 MICROFRONTS experiment via McIDAS-X and then  converted to GIF image format. These images are at 4 km  resolution.  These data are available for browsing purposes.

title: MICROFRONTS GOES-8 WV Images (GIF)
summary: GOES-8 Infrared (6.7 micron) satellite imagery collected  for the 1995 MICROFRONTS experiment via McIDAS-X and then  converted to GIF image format. These images are at 8 km  resolution.  These data are available for browsing purposes.

title: STORM-WAVE GOES-8 IR Images (GIF)
summary: GOES-8 Infrared (11 micron) satellite imagery collected for the STORM-WAVE experiment via McIDAS-X and then  converted to GIF image format. These images are at 4 km  resolution.  These data are available for browsing purposes.

title: STORM-WAVE GOES-8 VIS Images (GIF)
summary: GOES-8 Visible satellite imagery collected for the STORM-WAVE experiment via McIDAS-X and then  converted to GIF image format. These images are at 4 km  resolution.  These data are available for browsing purposes.

title: STORM-WAVE GOES-8 WV Images (GIF)
summary: GOES-8 Infrared (6.7 micron) satellite imagery collected  for the STORM-WAVE experiment via McIDAS-X and then  converted to GIF image format. These images are at 8 km  resolution.  These data are available for browsing purposes.

title: CaPE NOAA/OAO P3 Airborne Radar Data
summary: NOAA/OAO WD-P3 aircraft collected radar data during all P3  flights from two radars: the horizontally scanning lower    fuselage radar (non-coherent) and the vertically scanning   tail radar (Doppler).  Raw data in P3 format, UCLA has      software to convert to UF.  The data consists of velocity   (tail) and reflectivity (both).

title: CaPE NOAA P-3 State Parameters
summary: NOAA Office of Aircraft Operations Lockheed Orion WP-3D was available from 5-18 August 1991.  Carried 2 airborne radars and measured housekeeping and state parameters, particle  spectra, liquid water content, small ice particles,  electric field vector (2 components) and particle charge,  all at 1 sec resolution.  from a Formvar replicator, particle charge from an inductio

title: NWS Rawinsonde Data
summary: Standard soundings taken during VORTEX from the existing NWS network every 12 hours. There are 12 sites in and near VORTEX. The sondes were radio-directionally tracked with winds measured at 1-min intervals. Other data consists of pressure, temperature and relative humidity using either a VIZ or SpaceData instrument and are averaged over 6 s intervals. Data are also available in 10 sec resolution CLASS format.

title: NSSL Mobile CLASS Data
summary: NSSL operated 3 (NCAR operated 1) Mobile CLASS sounding systems during VORTEX. Launches were made at the direction of the VORTEX director. Data consists of pressure, relativehumidity and temperature transmitted every 4 sec with 20 secaverages archived every 10 sec. Also wind speed/direction use 30 sec averages every 10 sec.

title: NWS and FAA ASOS/AWOS Data
summary: NOAA/NWS and FAA operated 78 ASOS stations and 34 AWOS stations in the VORTEX region. ASOS data consists of 5-min averages of temperature, dewpoint, wind speed/direction (andgusts), barometric pressure, altimeter, density altitude, visibility and 5-min total precipitation. AWOS data is similar in type with winds averaged over 2-5 min and 20-min averages stored at the site.

title: CaPE USAF/CCAFS RATS Rawinsonde Data
summary: A back-up USAF/CCAFS Radiotheodolite Automatic Tracking System (RATS) was provided to CaPE.  Flights from 9-12 July were for training and RATS was available through 28 July. Data consists of vertical profiles of pressure, temperature,relative humidity and wind speed/direction.  Data are  available in two resolutions: 500-2000 gpf and 6 sec (only thermodynamic and balloon position).

title: WSR-88D Archive Level II Data

title: GOES-7 VIS/IR/MSI Imagery
summary: GOES-7 has the Visible and Infrared Spin-Scan Radiometer (VISSR) which produces day and night IR (4 km) and day visible (1 km) images at 30 min intervals (up to every 5 minduring RISOP). Also the VISSR Atmospheric Sounder (VAS) has 4 IR detectors and 12 narrow band filters that produce multi-spectral imagery.

title: STORM-FEST Observational Data CD-ROM
summary: A 3-CD set containing much of the observational data from the STORM-FEST field experiment. The set contains NCAR King Air, U of Wyoming King Air, U of Washington C131, NOAA P3,NOAA Profilers, Soundings (CLASS, NWS, L2D2 and AES), NCAR ASTER, surface and precipitation data in NetCDF format, GOES satellite, WSI NOWRAD and CP4 in ZEB image format. ZEB and WINDS software are also included (requires Unix workstation).

title: STORM-FEST Model Data CD-ROM

The set contains selected runs of the Aviation, eta, MAPS, and NGM models from NOAA's National Meteorological Center (NMC). Updated versions of the NCAR/ATD ZEB and WINDS software are also included which allow the user to overlay model grids with observational data from the STORM-FEST Observational Data CD-ROM. Note that this software requires a Unix workstation.

title: GCIP/GIDS-1 Observational Data CD-ROM

title: GCIP/GIST Observational Data CD-ROM

title: GCIP/GIST: Radar ABRFC Stage III Precipitation Images
summary: This dataset contains GIF images of daily precipitation  in the Arkansas - Red River Basin.  These images were  derived from WSR-88D radar data and in situ measurements by the Arkansas - Red River Basin River Forecast Center  (RFC) of NOAA's National Weather Service.

title: GCIP/GIST: Radar WSI NOWRAD 2km Radar Composite
summary: WSI provided PPI reflectivity data composited from  individual NWS radars (NOWRAD) every 15 minutes during  VORTEX and GCIP/GIST.  A fixed regional sector was  collected.  This data is in McIDAS format.

title: GCIP/GIST: Radar National Radar Precipitation (GIF)
summary: The GCIP/GIST National Radar Precipitation Composite contains radar derived percipitation values over the CONUS. These images were prepared at the NASA/Marshal Space Flight Center.  One image per day at 12Z is available as a data browse product.

title: GCIP/GIST: Satellite GOES Satellite Imagery (GIF)
summary: GOES-7 IR imagery collected during the GCIP/GIST period via PC-McIDAS and then converted to GIF image format. These data are available for browsing purposes.

title: GCIP/GIST: Satellite GOES-7 1-km Visible Imagery
summary: Digital GOES-7 1-km visible imagery that were collected  during VORTEX-94 and GCIP/GIST.  These data are in McIDAS  format.

title: GCIP/GIST: Satellite GOES-7 2-km Visible (GIF)
summary: Digital GOES-7 2-km visible imagery for GCIP/GIST.  These  data are in GIF format, and are provided for data browse purposes.

title: GCIP/GIST: Satellite GOES-7 4-km Infrared Imagery
summary: Digital GOES-7 4-km infrared imagery that were collected  during VORTEX and GCIP/GIST. These data are in McIDAS  format.

title: GCIP/GIST: Satellite GOES-7 8-km Water Vapor
summary: Digital GOES-7 8-km water vapor imagery that were  collected during VORTEX and GCIP/GIST.  These data are in  McIDAS format.

title: GCIP/GIST: Satellite GOES-7 8-km Water Vapor (GIF)
summary: GOES-7 8-km water vapor imagery that were collected during  VORTEX and GCIP/GIST.  One image per day has been converted to GIF format and placed on-line for browsing purposes.

title: GCIP/GIST: Model NMC eta Model 1000mb Maps (GIF)
summary: NMC eta Model 1000mb Analyses for the GCIP/GIST period.

title: GCIP/GIST: Model NMC eta Model 500mb Maps (GIF)
summary: NMC eta Model 500mb Analyses for the GCIP/GIST period.

title: GCIP/GIST: Radar NWS/OH Gridded Precipitation
summary: This dataset contains hourly gridded precipitation values derived from WSR-88D reflectivity (STAGE-III) by the Arkansas-Red Basin River Forecast Center (ABRFC). The data are on a 4km regular grid in WMO FM-92 GRIB format. These data were received from the National Weather Service Office of Hydrology (NWS/OH). NWS/OH provided the processing of the ABRFC Stage-III products into the GRIB format.

title: GCIP/GIST: Model NMC eta Model 850mb Map Images (GIF)
summary: NMC eta Model 850mb Analyses for the GCIP/GIST period.

title: GCIP/GIST: Land Characterization EDC AVHRR Land Cover (GIF)
summary: This dataset consists of monthly GIF images of Land Cover  (vegetation) provided by the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS), EROS Data Center (EDC) for GCIP/GIST.  These Land Cover  mosaics were produced from AVHRR imagery and are but a  sample of the detailed land cover  database available from EDC on CD-ROM.

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) NCEP RUC Surface Analysis
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's RUC Surface Analysis for 4 and 5 May 1996.  The RUC Surface Analysis is given every hour.  The data are archived in GEMPAK gridded files.

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) NCEP Aviation Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Aviation (AVN) model runs on 4 and 5 May 1996.  The AVN model is run at 00Z and 12Z daily.  The forecast goes out 72 hours and is given every 6 hours except for the 66 hour forecast.  The geographic region covered is the Northern Hemisphere.  The data are archived in GEMPAK gridded files.

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) NCEP meso-Eta Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's meso Eta model runs on 4 and 5 May 1996.  The meso Eta model is run at 03Z and 15Z daily.  The forecast goes out 33 hours and is given every three hours.  The geographic region covered is the U.S.A.  The data are archived in GEMPAK gridded files.

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) NCEP Medium Range Forecast Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Medium Range Forecast (MRF) model runs on 4 and 5 May 1996.  The MRF model is run at 00Z daily.  The forecast goes out ten days and is given every 12 hours.  The data are archived in GEMPAK gridded files.

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) NCEP Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) model runs on 4 and 5 May 1996.  The RUC model is run every three hours.  The forecast goes out 12 hours and is given every three hours.  The data are archived in GEMPAK gridded files

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) NCEP Eta Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Eta model runs on 4 and 5 May 1996.  The Eta model is run at 00Z and 12Z daily.  The forecast goes out 48 hours and is given every six hours.  The geographic region covered is North America. The data are archived in GEMPAK gridded files.

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) NCEP Nested Gridded Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Nested Gridded Model runs on 4 and 5 May 1996.  The Nested Gridded model is run at 00Z and 12Z daily.  The forecast goes out 48 hours and is given every 6 hours.  The data are archived in GEMPAK gridded files.

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) NCEP Aviation Model Products
summary: This dataset contains products derived from NCEP's Aviation (AVN) model runs on 5 May 1996.  The data products are Archived in the NTRANS metafile format.  The NTRANS viewer is needed to display these products (DEC users will need NTRANS from N-AWIPS/GEMPAK 5.4 or later).

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) NCEP Eta Model Products
summary: This dataset contains products derived from NCEP's Eta model runs on 5 May 1996.  The data products are archived in the NTRANS metafile format.  The NTRANS viewer is needed to display these products (DEC users will need NTRANS from N-AWIPS/GEMPAK 5.4 or later).

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) NCEP Nested Gridded Model Products
summary: This dataset contains products derived from NCEP's Nested Gridded Model runs on 5 May 1996.  The data products are archived in the NTRANS metafile format.  The NTRANS viewer is needed to display these products (DEC users will need NTRANS from N-AWIPS/GEMPAK 5.4 or later).

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) NCEP RUC Surface Analysis Products
summary: This dataset contains products derived from NCEP's RUC Surface Analysis for 5 May 1996.  The data products are archived in the NTRANS metafile format.  The NTRANS viewer is needed to display these products (DEC users will need NTRANS from N-AWIPS/GEMPAK 5.4 or later).

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) NCEP Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) Model Products
summary: This dataset contains products derived from NCEP's Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) model runs on 5 May 1996.  The data products are archived in the NTRANS metafile format.  The NTRANS viewer is needed to display these products (DEC users will need NTRANS from N-AWIPS/GEMPAK 5.4 or later).

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) Software for Producing Metafiles
summary: This dataset contains C-shell scripts for generating the metafiles that contain data products derived from the NCEP models.

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) WSI NOWRAD Mosaics (GIF)
summary: This dataset contains WSI NOWRAD radar composite imagery of central USA.  Data are archived as GIF files at a 30 minute frequency.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim ISS PRELIMINARY High Vertical Resolution SkewT plot (GIF)
summary: SkewT/logP plot of the NCAR/Integrated Sounding System (ISS)collected during the ACE-1 intensive operations, via the NCAR/Atmospheric Technology Division (ATD), then plotted and converted to GIF image format.  These images consist of 10-sec vertical resolution level data (temperature, dew point temperature, pressure, and winds). These soundings were typically taken at 00, 06, 12, and 18 UTC daily.  The data used in these plots are PRELIMINARY and could change significantly following final processing by ATD.

title: CEPEX Nauru High Resolution Soundings
summary: This dataset contains the 10-sec vertical resolution sounding data taken at Nauru (WMO 91530) during CEPEX. Sounding schedule was 00, and 12 UTC daily. Nauru was an NCAR Integrated Sounding System Station. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, relative humidity, dew point, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: CEPEX Pago Pago High Resolution Soundings
summary: This dataset contains the 6-sec vertical resolution sounding data taken at Pago Pago, American Samoa (WMO 91530) during CEPEX. Sounding schedule was 00 and 12 UTC daily. Pago Pago was a NWS MicroART system station.  This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point,  relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: CEPEX Lihue High Resolution Soundings
summary: This dataset contains the 6-sec vertical resolution sounding data taken at Lihue, Hawaii (WMO 91165) during CEPEX. Sounding schedule was 00 and 12 UTC daily. Lihue was a NWS MicroART system station. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: CEPEX Hilo High Resolution Soundings
summary: This dataset contains the 6-sec vertical resolution sounding data taken at Hilo, Hawaii (WMO 91285) during CEPEX. Sounding schedule was 00 and 12 UTC daily. Hilo was a NWS MicroART system station. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: CEPEX Majuro High Resolution Soundings
summary: This dataset contains the 6-sec vertical resolution sounding data taken at Majuro (WMO 91376) during CEPEX. Sounding schedule was 00 and 12 UTC daily. Majuro was a NWS MicroART system station.  This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point,  relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: CEPEX Tarawa High Resolution Soundings
summary: This dataset contains the contact vertical resolution sounding data taken at Tarawa, Kiribati (WMO 91610) during CEPEX. Sounding schedule was 00 and 12 daily. Data was digitized from strip chart output. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: CEPEX R/V VICKERS Soundings (MPI)
summary: This dataset contains the 10-sec high resolution  sounding data taken aboard the R/V Vickers during CEPEX. Sounding schedule was 00, 06, 12, and 18 UTC daily. This  dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: CEPEX Kanton Operational Soundings
summary: This dataset contains the mandatory/significant level sounding data taken at Kanton Island during CEPEX. Sounding schedule was 10 and 22 UTC daily. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: STORM-FEST NWS Rawinsonde (RAW)
summary: Standard and special soundings from 33 NWS sites in the  western and central US using NWS Micro-ART system.  Standard12 h soundings supplemented by special 3 and 6 h soundings at request of STORM-FEST.  Data consists of 6 sec resolutionpressure, temperature, relative humidity, wind speed, direction, and altitude.

title: CEPEX MIT Digital Radar Scans
summary: This dataset contains digital radar data from the MIT radar aboard the Research Vessel Vickers during the CEPEX experiment.  These data are the original, raw radar reflectivities and radial velocities recorded by this 5 centimeter doppler radar.  Software for working with this data is available from Steve Rutledge of the Colorado State University.  This dataset consists of 22 high density 8mm data tapes.

title: VORTEX-94 Nowrad Imagery (GIF Format)
summary: Daily radar reflectivity GIF images of a sector of the WSI Nowrad composite for the VORTEX period.  The sector was generally centered over the VORTEX domain, but was occasionally moved.  These data are provided for browsing purposes.

title: GCIP/GIST: Radar Nowrad Imagery (GIF Format)
summary: Daily radar reflectivity GIF images of a sector of the WSI Nowrad composite for the GCIP/GIST period.  The sector was generally centered over the GIST domain, but was occasionally moved.  These data are provided for browsing purposes.

title: STORM-FEST Nowrad Imagery (GIF Format)
summary: Daily radar reflectivity GIF images of a sector of the WSI Nowrad composite for the STORM-FEST Period.  The sector is centered over Kansas. These data are for browsing purposes.

title: VORTEX-95 Nowrad Imagery (GIF Format)
summary: Case day radar reflectivity GIF images of a sector of the WSI Nowrad composite for the VORTEX period.  The sector was generally centered over the VORTEX domain, but was occasionally moved. These data are provided for browsing purposes.

title: GCIP/GIDS-1 Nowrad Imagery (GIF Format)
summary: Daily radar reflectivity GIF images of a sector of the WSI Nowrad composite for the GCIP/GIDS-1 period.  The sector was generally centered over the GIDS-1 domain, but was occasionally moved.  These data are provided for browsing purposes.

title: CEPEX R/V Vickers 35mm Cloud Photography
summary: This dataset contains 35mm slide cloud photography taken  from a hand-held SLR camera system on the R/V Vickers  during CEPEX. Slides were routinely taken hourly (during  daylight hours only) at 4 cardinal positions plus overhead.  All slides were digitized and published on KODAK CD-ROM.  There are a total of 4 CD-ROMs in the archive.

title: STORM-FEST 10 MB Composite (ASCII)
summary: Test dataset from STORM-FEST for Z, T subsetting.

title: STORM-FEST Illinois HOT Doppler Radar
summary: The University of Illinois HOT 5 cm wavelength Doppler radarwas located at Urbana-Champaign Airport and operated by the Iliinois State Water Survey during STORM-FEST.  The radar was activated under the direction of STORM-FEST during designated IOPs. This dataset includes radar reflectivity and radial velocity.

title: STORM-FEST GOES-7 8km Channel 12 (Water Vapor) Imagery
summary: Digital recordings of daily GOES-7 8-km Channel 12 (water vapor imagery that were produced during STORM-FEST from the NSSFC Wideword workstation.  These data are in McIDAS format.

title: CEPEX ER-2 Cloud Video Tapes
summary: This dataset contains VHS format video tapes recorded from a downward-looking video camera system mounted on the ER-2 during CEPEX. One video tape has been recorded per mission, for a total of 15 tapes in the archive. F-stop varied per  mission with shutter speed set at 1/2000 per sec.  This includes cloud video.

title: CEPEX Lear Jet 35mm Cloud Photography
summary: This dataset contains 35mm slide cloud photography taken from a hand-held SLR camera system on the Aeromet Inc. Lear Jet during CEPEX. The camera system was a Minolta X-700 35 mm camera with Minolta multi-function back date/time stamp.  All slides were digitized and published on KODAK CD-ROM.  There are a total of 3 CD-ROMs in the archive.

title: CEPEX Frostpoint/Ozone Soundings
summary: This dataset contains the 10-sec high resolution Frostpoint and Ozone sounding data taken aboard the R/V Vickers and Christmas Island by NOAA/CMDL during CEPEX.  This dataset includes pressure, altitude, temperature, potential temperature, relative humidity, frost point (from Vaisala and Hygrometer), ozone partial pressure, ozone mixing ratio, and water vapor mixing ratio.

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) Upperair Profiler Data
summary: This dataset contains upperair profiler observation data in GEMPAK formatted files.  There is one file per day containing hourly data for the day.  This dataset includes pressure, temperature, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) Sounding Data, Textual
summary: This dataset contains upperair sounding data in ASCII format.  This data can be displayed using the Interactive Sounding Program (ISP).  This dataset includes pressure, temperature, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer ISS PRELIMINARY High Vertical Resolution SkewT plot (GIF)
summary: SkewT/logP plots of the NCAR/Integrated Sounding System (ISS) upper air data collected aboard the R/V Discoverer during the ACE-1 transect and intensive operations, via the NCAR/Atmospheric Technology Division (ATD), then plotted and converted to GIF format.  These images consist of 10-sec vertical resolution data (temperature, dew point temperature, pressure, and winds). These soundings were typically taken at 00 and 12 UTC daily with up to 6-hr frequency during intensive operations. The data used in these plots are PRELIMINARY and could change significantly following final processing by ATD.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer ISS Profiler Wind Profiles [PRELIMINARY] (GIF)
summary: Vertical wind profile plots of the NCAR/Integrated Sounding System (ISS) upper air data collected aboard the R/V Discoverer during the ACE-1 transect and Intensive Operations, via the NCAR/Atmospheric Technology Division (ATD), then converted to GIF image format.  These images consist of 0.25 km vertical resolution wind profiles taken every 30-min. The data used in these plots are PRELIMINARY and could change significantly following final processing by ATD.

title: ACE-1: Satellite GMS-5 VIS A/C TRACK Images (GIF)
summary: GMS-5 Visible (VIS) imagery (with aircraft track overlaid on plot )collected during ACE-1 Intensive Operations in Hobart, Tasmania, via the Australian Bureau of Meteorology, then converted to GIF image format. These images consist of the Southern Ocean (image center 49 deg S, 142 deg E), 4 km resolution,  collected every hour. Digital McIDAS Area Format data files were collected hourly at OFPS from which these GIF images were created.

title: VORTEX-95: Radar WSI NIDS Single Radar Data
summary:
This dataset contains a limited set of WSR-88D Level III data products archived from the WSI NIDS datastream for 13 radars in the VORTEX domain. The products archived are base reflectivity and velocity at 0.5 and 1.5 degrees, composite reflectivity, and Vertical Azimuth Display (VAD) wind profile. The sites that were archived are KGLD, KTWX, KEAX, KPUX, KDDC, KICT, KAMA, KINX, KFDR, KLBB, KDYX, and KFWS. Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format on exabyte tape. One week's data is contained on a single tape, as one Unix tar" file per day.

"

title: GCIP/ESOP-95 and STORM-WAVE: Radar Composite Imagery (GIF)
summary: This dataset contains images generated from the the WSI  NIDS 4 km national radar mosaic for the duration of the STORM-WAVE and GCIP/ESOP-95 Experiments.  One image per  day, generally at 2300 UTC, is available.  These images are provided to allow the user to see a visual representation of the radar reflectivity recorded over the United States on a given day of the project.  They are not meant to be used for scientific analysis, but rather as a browsing product.

title: VORTEX-95 NCEP 29km eta model Surface Flux
summary: This dataset is the NCEP 29km eta model Surface Flux  analyses and 3-hourly forecasts (out to 33 hours) collected during the VORTEX-95 project.  The data are in GRIB format  on a skewed lat-lon grid and on sigma surfaces.  This is a  high volume dataset:  one run of surface flux is about  60 Megabytes(MB)!  This output includes pressure,  geopotential height, temperature, precipitation, specific humidity, soil temperature and moiture content, u and v wind components among many other parameters including many flux parameters.  NOTE:  At the time of VORTEX-95, the 29km eta model was  being run in experimental mode, so use the model output with caution.

title: VORTEX-94 MAPS 3-D Analyses/Forecasts
summary: FSL/Mesoscale Analysis and Prediction System 3-D version every 3 hours is to be used as input for the Oklahoma Local Analysis and Prediction System (O-LAPS). Thisincludes 3-hr forecasts, and every 12 hours, one 6-hr, one 9-hr and one 12-hr forecast.  This output includes pressure, temperature, relative humidity, u and v wind components, precipitation, height, among others.

title: VORTEX-95 MAPS Analyses/Forecasts
summary: FSL/Mesoscale Analysis and Prediction System 3-D version every 3 hours is to be used as input for the Oklahoma Local Analysis and Prediction System (O-LAPS). Thisincludes 3-hr forecasts, and every 12 hours, one 6-hr, one 9-hr and one 12-hr forecast.  This output includes pressure, temperature, relative humidity, u and v wind components, height, precipitation, among others.  This data was collected for VORTEX-95.

title: VORTEX-95 MAPS Surface Analyses
summary: NOAA/FSL ran the MAPS Sfc Analysis every hour at a standard resolution of about 60 km. These fields are used as part of the initialization of the O-LAPS. The data cutoff for the model runs was about 1 hour.  This output includes pressure, temperature, relative humidity, u and v wind components, height, among others.

title: STORM-FEST Eta Model (PC-GRIDS)
summary: Selected eta model outputs captured during STORM-FEST in PC-GRIDS format.  The output includes pressure,  geopotential height, temperature, specific humidity, u and v wind components, vertical velocity, precipitable water, precipitation, among others.

title: ACE-1: Southern Surveyor Navigation data (Hourly)
summary: This dataset contains latitude (negative sign has been dropped) and longitude for the Southern Surveyor on an hourly basis during ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 Particle Concentration PRELIMINARY Data (McMurry)
summary: This Dataset consists of continuous measurements of ultrafine particle concentration taken aboard the C-130 aircraft by Peter McMurry (University of Minnesota). The data represents the total concentration of particles per cubic centimeter larger than 3 nm measured with the University of Minnesota CNC and the ultrafine concentration of particles between 3 and 4 nm measured with the University of Minnesota pulse height analysis method.  The data consist of date, sample number, start and stop time (UTC), total concentration (cm-3), and ultrafine concentration (cm-3). This dataset was processed and quality controlled following the ACE-1 field phase.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Nonmethane Hydrocarbon Data - Air Measurements [PRELIMINARY] (Prinn)
summary: This dataset consists of the Nonmethane Hydrocarbon Air Measurements taken from the bow of the R/V Discoverer by R. Prinn during ACE-1. (Preliminary data)

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Nonmethane Hydrocarbon Data - Equilibrator Measurements [PRELIMINARY] (Prinn)

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim ISS Profiler Wind Profiles [PRELIMINARY] (GIF)
summary: Vertical wind profile plots of the NCAR/Integrated Sounding System (ISS) upper air data collected at Cape Grim during the ACE-1 Intensive Operations, via the NCAR/Atmospheric Technology Division (ATD), then plotted and converted to GIF image format.  These images consist 0.25 km vertical resolution wind profiles taken every 30-min. The data used in these plots are PRELIMINARY and could change significantly following final processing by ATD.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim ISS RASS Temperature Profiles [PRELIMINARY] (GIF)
summary: 915 MHz Radio Acoustic Sounding System (RASS) Temperature profiles of the NCAR/Integrated Sounding System (ISS) upper air data collected at Cape Grim during the ACE-1 Intensive Operations, via the NCAR/Atmospheric Technology Division (ATD), and converted to GIF image format. These images consist of temperature profiles to approx. 1500 m height (AGL) at 60 m vertical resolution, taken every 30-min. The data used in these plots are PRELIMINARY and could change significantly following final processing by ATD.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer ISS RASS Temperature Profiles [PRELIMINARY] (GIF)

summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Nested Gridded Model runs on 4 and 5 January 1995.  The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecasts given every 6 hours and going out 48 hours.  The data are archived in GRIB files on grid number 105.

title: COMET CASE 005 NCEP RUC Surface Analysis
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's RUC Surface Analysis for 4 and 5 January 1995.  The analysis is given every hour.  The data are archived in GRIB files on grid 87.

title: COMET CASE 005 NCEP Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) model runs on 4 and 5 January 1995.  The model runs are every three hours with forecasts given every three hours and going out 12 hours.  The data are archived in GRIB files on grid number 87.

title: COMET CASE 005 NCEP Aviation Model Products
summary: This dataset contains products derived from NCEP's Aviation (AVN) model runs on 4 and 5 January 1995.  The data products are archived in the NTRANS metafile format. The NTRANS viewer is needed to display these products (DEC users will need NTRANS from N-AWIPS/GEMPAK 5.4 or later).

title: COMET CASE 005 NCEP Eta Model Products
summary: This dataset contains products derived from NCEP's Eta model runs on 4 and 5 January 1995.  The data products are archived in the NTRANS metafile format.  The NTRANS viewer is needed to display these products (DEC users will need NTRANS from N-AWIPS/GEMPAK 5.4 or later).

title: COMET CASE 005 NCEP Nested Gridded Model Products
summary: This dataset contains products derived from NCEP's Nested Gridded Model runs on 4 and 5 January 1995.  The data products are archived in the NTRANS metafile format. The NTRANS viewer is needed to display these products (DEC users will need NTRANS from N-AWIPS/GEMPAK 5.4 or later).

title: COMET CASE 005 NCEP RUC Surface Analysis Products
summary: This dataset contains products derived from NCEP's RUC Surface Analysis for 4 and 5 January 1995.  The data products are archived in the NTRANS metafile format. The NTRANS viewer is needed to display these products (DEC users will need NTRANS from N-AWIPS/GEMPAK 5.4 or later).

title: COMET CASE 005 NCEP Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) Model Products
summary: This dataset contains products derived from NCEP's Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) model runs on 4 and 5 January 1995. The data products are archived in the NTRANS metafile format.  The NTRANS viewer is needed to display these products (DEC users will need NTRANS from N-AWIPS/GEMPAK 5.4 or later).

title: COMET CASE 005 MM5 Model Products
summary: This dataset contains products derived from an MM5 model run that was initialized at 00Z on 4 January 1995.  The 36-hour forecast simulation used a 30km grid over the Great Lakes region with a nested 10km grid over Lake Ontario and adjacent downwind areas.  This dataset was contributed by SUNY, Brockport.  The data products are archived in the NTRANS metafile format.  The NTRANS viewer is needed to display these products (DEC users will need NTRANS from N-AWIPS/GEMPAK 5.4 or later).

title: COMET CASE 005 NCEP MRF Model Products

title: COMET CASE 005 Upperair Profiler Products
summary: This dataset contains products derived from Upperair Profiler data from 4 to 6 January 1995.  The data products are archived in the NTRANS metafile format.  The NTRANS viewer is needed to display these products (DEC users will need NTRANS from N-AWIPS/GEMPAK 5.4 or later).

title: ACE-1: Satellite: GMS-5 Digital Satellite Data (McIDAS Area Format)
summary: This dataset contains GMS-5 Digital Satellite Data obtained by the Australian Bureau of Meteorology (BoM) during ACE-1. The data consist of visible, infrared (11 micron), and water vapor (6.7 micron) hourly images in McIDAS AREA format. The image sectors are as follows: Visible (1 km res) -32S to S Pole, 118E to 176E; Infrared (4 km res): 19N to S. Pole, 158W to 79E; Water vapor (4 km res): 19N to S. Pole, 158W to 79E. No additional quality control or navigation corrections have been applied to this imagery.

title: ACE-1: Model Trajectories, Back BoM GASP (Smart" balloon) (Siems)"
summary: This dataset contains Back trajectories for the Smart" balloons released from the R/V Discoverer computed from the Australian Bureau of Meteorology (BoM) Global/Regional Assimilation Prognosis (GASP) Model during ACE-1."

title: ACE-1: Model Trajectories, Back BoM GASP (C130) (Siems)
summary: This dataset contains Forward and Back trajectories designed to aid in the analysis of the C130 observations in missions based off Hobart during ACE-1. The plane ran circles in the boundary layer. Each series of trajectories has source altitudes of 100, 500 and 2000 meters.

title: ACE-1: Model Trajectories, Back BoM GASP (Discoverer Transitions) (Siems)
summary: This dataset contains back trajectories designed to aid in the analysis of the R/V Discoverer transition periods" as defined by Tim Bates. Five periods have been identified by Tim Bates leading to four transitions (as well as beginning andend locations as the Discoverer entered and left Hobart). For each transition
archive_note: there are 5 series of trajectories at -12

title: ACE-1: Model Trajectories, Back BoM GASP (Land) (Siems)
summary: This dataset contains Back trajectories for Macquarie Island and Cape Grim computed from the Australian Bureau of Meteorology (BoM) Global/Regional Assimilation Prognosis (GASP) Model during ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Model Trajectories, Back BoM GASP (Ship) (Siems)
summary: This dataset contains Back trajectories for the R/V Discoverer and R/V Southern Surveyor ships computed from the Australian Bureau of Meteorology (BoM) Global/Regional Assimilation Prognosis (GASP) Model during ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Model Trajectory Analysis BoM GASP (GIF)
summary: The Australian Bureau of Meteorology (BoM) routinely produced forward trajectory forecasts from its Global/Regional Assimilation Prognosis (GASP) model runs.  Two trajectory runs (out to 36 hours) were produced daily (00 and 12 UTC).  Selected points for ACE-1 were plotted by NCAR/Research Data Program on the ZEBRA workstation and archived as GIF imagery. Heights of the parcel trajectories are color coded in pressure (mb) levels.

title: COMET CASE 001 Isentropic Analysis of NCEP's NGM (Contributed)
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Nested Gridded Model data on isentropic surfaces from runs on 12, 13, and 14 March 1993.  The analysis was contributed by Dr. Steve Koch, NC State U.  The data are archived in GEMPAK grid files.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Methyl Halide Measurements (Moore)

title: VORTEX-95 NCEP 29km eta model 3-D Grids
summary: This dataset is the NCEP 29km eta model gridded analyses  and 3-hourly forecasts (out to 33 hours) collected during  the VORTEX-95 project.  The data are in GRIB format on a  skewed lat-lon grid and on sigma surfaces.  This is a VERY  high volume dataset:  one run is about 400 Megabytes(MB)!   This output includes pressure, geopotential height, temperature, u and v wind components, vertical velocity, specific humidity, precipitation, among others.  NOTE:  At the time of VORTEX-95, the 29km eta model was  being run in experimental mode, so use the model output with caution.

title: GCIP/ESOP-96 Radar: ABRFC WSR-88D Stage III Daily Precipitation
summary: This dataset contains data from the NOAA Arkansas-Red Basin River Forecast Center. The ABRFC routinely ingests WSR-88D precipitation derived products (Level III) from each of the radar sites with coverage in the Arkansas-Red River Basin (15 radars). In addition the ABRFC ingests real-time precipitation data from a total of approximately 500 gages. The ABRFC produces a number of derived or Stage" products using the radar and precipitation gage data. A Stage II product is produced by merging radar precipitation estimates  (Stage I) with ground truth data  provided by the gages. The Stage II estimates are then composited into a Stage III precipitation 4 x 4 km resolution area averaged mosaic for the Arkansas-Red River Basin. "

title: COMET CASE 010 Ship and Buoy Observations
summary: This dataset contains ship and buoy observation data in GEMPAK formatted files.  There is one file per day containing data for every sixth hour of the day.

title: COMET CASE 010 Radiosonde Data
summary: This dataset contains radiosonde observation data in GEMPAK formatted files. There is one file per day containing data for 00Z and 12Z.

title: COMET CASE 010 Upperair Profiler Data
summary: This dataset contains upperair profiler observation data in GEMPAK formatted files.  There is one file per day containing hourly data for the day.

title: COMET CASE 010 Sounding Data, Textual
summary: This dataset contains upperair sounding data in ASCII format. This data can be displayed using the Interactive Sounding Program (ISP). This dataset includes pressure, temperature, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: COMET CASE 010 NWS Textual Weather Data Products
summary: This dataset contains the text products issued by the National Weather Service. These include forecasts, watches, warnings, local and national discussions, as well as coded surface observations and upper air soundings.  The files are named based on the type of product and the issuance time.

title: COMET CASE 010 NCEP Aviation Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Aviation (AVN) model runs on 26 and 27 May 1997. The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecasts going out three days (at 00, 06, 12, 18, 24, 36, 48, 60, and 72 hours). The data are archived in GRIB files on grid number 211.

title: COMET CASE 010 NCEP Eta Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Eta model runs on 26 and 27 May 1997. The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecast times every six hours from 00 to 48 hours. The data are archived in GRIB files on grid number 211.

title: COMET CASE 010 NCEP meso-Eta Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's meso Eta model runs on 26 and 27 May 1997. The model runs are for 03Z and 15Z daily with forecast times every three hours from 00 to 33 hours. The data are archived in GRIB files on grid number 212.

title: COMET CASE 010 NCEP Medium Range Forecast Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Medium Range Forecast (MRF) model runs on 26 and 27 May 1997. The model runs are for 00Z daily with forecasts given every 12 hours and going out ten days. The data are archived in GRIB files on grid number 201.

title: COMET CASE 010 NCEP Nested Gridded Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Nested Gridded Model runs on 26 and 27 May 1997. The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecasts given every 6 hours and going out 48 hours. The data are archived in GRIB files on grid number 211.

title: COMET CASE 010 NCEP RUC Surface Analysis
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's RUC Surface Analysis for 26 and 27 May 1997. The analysis is given every hour. The data are archived in GRIB files on grid 87.

title: COMET CASE 010 NCEP Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) model runs on 26 and 27 May 1997. The model runs are every three hours with forecasts given every three hours and going out 12 hours. The data are archived in GRIB files on grid number 87.

title: COMET CASE 010 Surface Airways Observations
summary: This dataset contains surface observation data in GEMPAK formatted files.  There is one file per day containing hourly data for the day.

title: GCIP/ESOP-96 Radar: NWS/OH Gridded Precipitation (GRIB)
summary: This dataset contains hourly gridded precipitation values derived from WSR-88D reflectivity (STAGE-III) by the Arkansas-Red Basin River Forecast Center (ABRFC).  The data are on a 4km regular grid in WMO FM-92 GRIB format.  These data were received from the National Weather Service Office of Hydrology (NWS/OH).  NWS/OH provided the  processing of the ABRFC Stage-III products into the GRIB format.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Sub-Surface: NCDC Daily Soil Temperature Dataset
summary: The GCIP/NESOB-96 Sub-Surface NCDC Daily Soil Temperature Dataset contains data from the National Climatic Data Center (NCDC). This dataset was formed by extracting soil temperature data from the GCIP/Enhanced Seasonal Observing Period 1996 (GCIP/ESOP-96) NCDC Summary of the Day Cooperative Dataset for the NESOB 1996 time of interest. This dataset covers an area slightly larger than the NESOB area of interest.

title: GCIP/ESOP-95 Radar: NWS/OH Gridded Precipitation (GRIB)
summary: This dataset contains hourly gridded precipitation values derived from WSR-88D reflectivity (STAGE-III) by the Arkansas-Red Basin River Forecast Center (ABRFC).  The data are on a 4km regular grid in WMO FM-92 GRIB format.  These data were received from the National Weather Service Office of Hydrology (NWS/OH).  NWS/OH provided the  processing of the ABRFC Stage-III products into the GRIB format.

title: Lake-ICE: Wyoming King Air Raw Flight Level Data

title: Cases-97: Wyoming King Air Raw Flight Level Data

title: Lake-ICE: NOAA 12/14 AVHRR Data (TDF)

title: GCIP/ESOP-97 Surface: Rosemount, MN Surface Meteorological and Radiation Data
summary: This data set consists of surface meteorological and radiation data collected at the Rosemount, MN site operated by Dr. John Baker of the USDA/ARS.  Parameters available include temperature, vapor pressure, wind speed, incoming and outgoing shortwave radiation, and incoming and outgoing longwave radiation.

title: GCIP/ESOP-97 Radar: WSI NIDS Radar Data
summary: This dataset contains a limited set of WSR-88D Level III  data products archived from the WSI NIDS datastream for  five radars in the GCIP/ESOP-97 domain (DMX, DVN, LOT, MKX, and MPX).  The products archived are base reflectivity and velocity at the first two tilts (the next two tilts were also collected for a portion of ESOP-97), composite reflectivity, and Vertical Azimuth Display (VAD) wind profile.  Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format on  exabyte tape.  One week's data is contained on a single tape, as one Unix tar" file per day."

title: GCIP/ESOP-98 Radar: WSI NIDS Radar Data
summary: This dataset contains a limited set of WSR-88D Level III  data products archived from the WSI NIDS datastream for  five radars in the GCIP/ESOP-98 domain (DMX, DVN, LOT, MKX, and MPX).  Also, for the period December 1997 and January 1998 DTX, GRB, and GRR were collected for the Lake-ICE project.   The products archived are base reflectivity and velocity at the first four tilts, composite reflectivity, and Vertical Azimuth Display (VAD) wind profile.  Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format on  exabyte tape.  One week's data is contained on a single tape, as one Unix tar" file per day."

title: COMET CASE 001 NCEP Eta Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Eta model runs on 11, 12 and 13 March 1993. The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecast times every six hours from 00 to 48 hours.

title: COMET CASE 001 NCEP Eta Theta Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Eta Theta model runs on 11, 12 and 13 March 1993. The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecast times every six hours from 00 to 48 hours.

title: COMET CASE 001 NCEP Medium Range Forecast Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Medium Range Forecast (MRF) model run on 13 March 1993. The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecasts given every 12 hours and going out ten days.

title: COMET CASE 001 NCEP Nested Gridded Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Nested Gridded Model runs on 11, 12, 13, 14, and 15 March 1994. The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecasts given every 6 hours and going out 48 hours.

title: COMET CASE 001 NCEP Rapid Update Cycle RUC Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) model runs for 13 March 1993. The model runs are every 6 hours with forecasts given every 3 hours going out 12 hours.

title: COMET CASE 001 NWS Textual Weather Data Products
summary: This dataset contains the text products issued by the National Weather Service. These include forecasts, watches, warnings, local and national discussions, as well as coded surface observations and upper air soundings.  The files are named based on the type of product and the issuance time.

title: GCIP/ESOP-98 Surface: Princeton, MN Surface Meteorological and Radiation Data
summary: This data set consists of surface meteorological and radiation data collected at the Princeton, MN site operated by Dr. John Baker of the USDA/ARS.  Parameters available include temperature, relative humidity, wind speed, incoming and outgoing shortwave radiation, incoming and outgoing longwave radiation, snow depth, and precipitation from two sensors.  Please see the README for more details.

summary: This dataset contains the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) 405 MHZ Wind Profiler Network (NPN) hourly data from 14 sites within the LakeICE area of interest. title: GCIP/ESOP-97 Surface: NOAA/ATDD Bondville, Illinois Long Term Flux Site
summary: The NOAA/ATDD (Tilden Meyers) started operation of a long term flux monitoring site near Bondville, Illinois in 1996. Half-hourly observations of wind speed and direction, air temperature, relative humidity, pressure, incoming global radiation, incoming (and outgoing) visible radiation, net radiation, ground heat flux, precipitation, wetness, skin temperature, soil temperature (at 2, 4, 8, 16, 32 and  64 cm), average wind vector speed, kinematic shear stress, streamwise velocity variance, crosswind velocity variance, vertical velocity variance, sensible heat flux, latent energy flux, CO2 flux, downwelling longwave from the sky and soil moisture (at depths of 5, 20 and 60 cm; started 19 November 1997).  For further information on this data set see the README file.

title: GCIP/EAOP-98 Upper Air: NOAA Wind Profiler Network Hourly Winds
summary: This dataset contains the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) 405 MHZ Wind Profiler Network (WPN) hourly data from 1 site within the EAOP 1998 area of interest.  This data consists of a series of hourly observations, each containing approximately 64 levels of wind speed and direction data.  These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: UMRBPP Upper Air: Mandatory and Significant Level Sounding Data Set
summary: This data set consists of mandatory and significant level sounding data for the UMRBPP.  It contains soundings from Dodge City and Topeka, KS; Denver and Grand Junction, CO; Omaha and North Platte, NE; Aberdeen and Rapid City, SD; Riverton, WY; Bismarck, ND; and Glasgow and Great Falls, MT. The data were retrieved from NOAA/FSL for the periods 5 April to 19 April and 28 April to 5 May 1999.  For the period from 21 April to 27 April the data were retrieved from FSU.  The NOAA/FSL data are in a columnar ASCII format while those from FSU are in the GTS format.  Please see the README file for more information.

title: UMRBPP Surface: Hourly and Special METAR Surface Observation Data Set
summary: This data set consists of the hourly and special METAR surface observations from 39 sites within the UMRBPP region.  The data were retrieved from the Pennsylvania  State University for the UMRBPP period (5 April to 5 May 1999.  The data are in METAR format.  Please see the README file for more information.

title: UMRBPP Hydrology: US Bureau of Reclamation Daily Reservoir Observation Data Set
summary: This data set consists of daily observations from four United States Bureau of Reclamation reservoirs within the UMRBPP region.  Data were retrieved from the USBR for the UMRBPP period (5 April to 5 May 1999).  Please see the README file for more information.

title: SGP97 Radar: WSI NIDS Radar Data
summary: This dataset contains a limited set of WSR-88D Level III  data products archived from the WSI NIDS datastream for  radars in the SGP97 domain.  The products archived are base reflectivity and velocity at 0.5 and 1.5 degrees, composite reflectivity, and Vertical Azimuth Display (VAD) wind profile.   The sites that were archived are KAMA, KGLD, KDDC, KICT, KINX and KTLX.  Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format on  exabyte tape.  One week's data is contained on a single tape, as one Unix tar" file per day."

title: UMRBPP Upper Air: NOAA Wind Profiler Network Hourly Winds (Merriman, NE)
summary: This data set contains the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) 405 MHZ Wind Profiler Network (WPN)  hourly data from the Merriman, NE site.  Data are available for the periods from 5-19 and 22-25 April 1999.  The  profiler was not operational from 1200 UTC 19 April to 0200 UTC 22 April and from 2300 UTC 25 April to the end of the  UMRBPP period of interest and no data are available during these time periods. This data consists of a series of  hourly observations, each containing approximately 64  levels of wind speed and direction data.  These data were  not quality controlled by the University Corporation for  Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support  (UCAR/JOSS).
