summary: This dataset contains vertical profiles of temperature,  dew point, relative humidity, altitude, and pressure taken from the Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Clouds and Radiation Testbed (CART) Central Facility Atmospheric Emitted Radiation Interferometer (AERI) in Lamont, Oklahoma. Profiles are generated every eight minutes. The vertical resolution is 100 m up to 1.3 km  and 200 - 250 m above 1.3 km. See the Readme file for more details.

title: COMET CASE 017 NCEP Aviation Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Aviation (AVN) model The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecasts going out three days (at 00, 06, 12, 18, 24, 36, 48, 60, and 72 hours). The data are archived in GRIB files on grid number 211.

title: COMET CASE 017 NCEP Eta Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Eta model. The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecast times every six hours from 00 to 48 hours.

title: COMET CASE 017 NCEP meso-Eta Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's meso Eta model. The meso Eta model is run at 03Z  and 15Z daily.  The forecast goes out 33 hours and is given every three hours.  The geographic region covered is the U.S.A.  The data are archived in GEMPAK gridded files.

title: COMET CASE 017 NCEP Medium Range Forecast Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Medium Range Forecast (MRF) model. The model runs are for 00Z with forecasts given every 12 hours and going out ten days.

title: COMET CASE 017 NCEP Nested Gridded Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Nested Gridded Model The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecasts given every 6 hours and going out 48 hours.

title: COMET CASE 017 NCEP RUC Surface Analysis
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's RUC Surface Analysis The analysis is given every hour. The data are archived in GRIB files on grid 87.

title: COMET CASE 017 NCEP Rapid Update Cycle RUC Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) model.  The model runs are every 3 hours with forecasts given every 3 hours going out 12 hours.

title: GCIP/EAOP-98 Surface: NCDC Summary of the Day COOP Dataset
summary: This dataset contains the GCIP/EAOP-98 National Climatic Data Center (NCDC) Summary of the Day Co-operative (COOP) data for the EAOP-98 domain. The observations in this dataset are primarily those from the cooperative network, augmented by observations from principal observing stations operated by the NWS and other sites having highly trained observers. Quality Control for this data was provided by NCDC. No additional QC was performed by JOSS on this dataset.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Upper Air: ARM-CART MWR Vertical Profile Data Set
summary: This dataset contains vertical profiles of temperature,  water vapor density, dew point, relative humidity, altitude, and pressure taken from the Department of  Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM)  Southern Great Plains (SGP) Clouds and Radiation Testbed  (CART) Central Facility Microwave Radiometer (MWR) in  Lamont, Oklahoma. Profiles are generated hourly.  See the Readme file for more details.

title: UMRBPP Radar: NIDS NOWRAD GIF Imagery
summary: This data set contains hourly GIF images generatd from the WSI NIDS 2 km national radar mosaic for the period of the UMRBPP (5 April to 5 May 1999).  These data are provided for browse purposes.

title: UMRBPP Radar: NIDS KUDX Hourly Precipitation (PRE1) Data Set
summary: This data set contains the Nexrad Information Dissemination Service (NIDS) Hourly Precipitation Data Set.  This data set is the 1-hour surface rainfall accumulation running  total product and is generated when ever precipitation  echoes are detected.  It covers a range of 230 km with a  resolution of 1.1 by 1.1 nmi.  It is updated once every volume scan (typically every 5-10 min) and includes 16 data levels. Data are available for most periods during  the UMRBPP (5 April to 5 May 1999).  Data are available from the Rapid City, SD (KUDX) radar site.  These data are in the original NIDS format.  These data were not quality quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS). This data set is quite large both in terms of size (40 Mb) and in terms of number of files (4500).  Please take this into consideration when placing your data order.

title: UMRBPP Radar: NIDS KUDX Vertically Integrated Liquid (VIL) Data Set
summary: This data set contains the Nexrad Information Dissemination Service (NIDS) Vertically Integrated Liquid (VIL) product.  The VIL products are generated whenever precipitation  echoes are detected.  It displays VIL values summed for all elevation angles within the volume scan.  It covers a range 230 km with a resolution of 2.2 by 2.2 nmi.  It is updated once every volume scan (typically every 5-10 min) and  includes 16 data levels. The units are kg/m^2.  Data are  available for most periods during the UMRBPP (5 April to 5 May 1999).  Data are available from the Rapid City, SD (KUDX) radar site.  These data are in the original NIDS format.  These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS). This data set is quite large in terms of the number of files (4500).  Please take this into consideration when placing your data order.

title: UMRBPP Radar: NIDS KUDX Velocity Azimuth Display (VAD) Data Set
summary: This data set contains the Nexrad Information Dissemination Service (NIDS) Velocity Azimuth Display (VAD) product.  The VAD products are generated in either clear air or  precipitation mode.  It contains the current vertical wind profile and up to ten profiles from previous time periods. The profiles are in a time vs. height format.  The range is up to 70,000 feet in height.  It is updated once every  volume scan (typically every 5-10 min).  The wind speeds are in knots, the wind direction in degrees, and the height in feet above mean sea level.  Data are available for most periods during the UMRBPP (5 April to 5 May 1999) from the Rapid City, SD (KUDX) radar site.  These data are in the (KUDX) radar site.  These data are in the original NIDS original NIDS format.  These data were not quality  controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS). This data set is quite large both in terms of size (32 Mb) and the number of files (4500).  Please take this into  consideration when placing your data order.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Sub-Surface: ARM Organic Carbon and Organic Matter Soils Data Set
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Organic Carbon and Organic Matter Soils Data Set is one of the various sub-surface data sets developed for the ARM/GCIP (Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment ?GEWEX? Continental-scale International Project) 1996 Near-Surface Observation (NESOB-96) Data Set. This data set contains a summary table of the measured organic carbon percentage and the estimated organic matter percentage in the near surface soil at each of the ARM SWATS (Soil Water and Temperature System) sites at the SGP site. The soil characterizations were perfomed by Oklahoma State University. No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Sub-Surface: ARM Soil Texture Data Set
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Soil Texture Data Set is one of the various sub-surface data sets developed for the ARM/GCIP (Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment ?GEWEX? Continental-scale International Project) 1996 Near-Surface Observation (NESOB-96) Data Set. This data set contains a summary table of the percentages of sand, silt, and clay fractions in each soil layer at each of the ARM SWATS (Soil Water and Temperature System) sites at the SGP site. Also included is the corresponding USDA texture class as determined from the soil triangle". The soil characterizations were perfomed by Oklahoma State University. No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS)."

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Sub-Surface: ARM Parameters for Soil Water Retention Models Data Set
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Parameters for Soil Water Retention Models Data Set is one of the various sub-surface data sets developed for the ARM/GCIP (Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment ?GEWEX? Continental-scale International Project) 1996 Near-Surface Observation (NESOB-96) Data Set. This data set contains one table for each of the ARM SWATS (Soil Water and Temperature System) sites at the SGP site containing the fitted values of the parameters in the van Genuchten and Brooks-Corey equations for relating soil water pressure to volumetric water content. The soil characterizations were perfomed by Oklahoma State University. No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Sub-Surface: ARM Soil Bulk Density Data Set
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Soil Bulk Density Data Set is one of the various sub-surface data sets developed for the ARM/GCIP (Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment ?GEWEX? Continental-scale International Project) 1996 Near-Surface Observation (NESOB-96) Data Set. This data set contains a summary table of the bulk densities representing the average of the values obtained from the soil water retention samples at each of the ARM SWATS (Soil Water and Temperature System) sites at the SGP site. The soil characterizations were perfomed by Oklahoma State University. No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Sub-Surface: ARM Soil Particle Size Data Set
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Soil Particle Size Data Set is one of the various sub-surface data sets developed for the ARM/GCIP (Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment ?GEWEX? Continental-scale International Project) 1996 Near-Surface Observation (NESOB-96) Data Set. This data set contains tables of the laboratory data for each soil layer at each of the ARM SWATS (Soil Water and Temperature System) sites at the SGP site. The soil characterizations were perfomed by Oklahoma State University. No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Sub-Surface: ARM Soil Water Retention Data Set
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Soil Water Retention Data Set is one of the various sub-surface data sets developed for the ARM/GCIP (Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment ?GEWEX? Continental-scale International Project) 1996 Near-Surface Observation (NESOB-96) Data Set. This data set contains a table for each of the ARM SWATS (Soil Water and Temperature System) sites at the SGP site containing the observed soil water retention data as obtained from laboratory tests using pressure plates and hanging columns. The soil characterizations were perfomed by Oklahoma State University. No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: COMET CASE 017 WSI NOWRAD 2km Radar Composites of the USA

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Upper Air: ARM-CART 50 Mhz Profiler and RASS Data Set

Profiles are generated every hour. The vertical resolution of RASS virtual temperature is ~150 m. The vertical resolution of the high mode wind profiles is ~1000 m and for the low mode wind profiles it is ~300 m. See the Readme file for more details.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Upper Air: ARM-CART 915 Mhz Profiler and RASS Data Set

Profiles are generated every hour. The vertical resolution of RASS virtual temperature is 100 m. The vertical resolution of the high mode wind profiles is 200 m and for the low mode wind profiles it is 60 m. See the Readme file for more details.

title: GCIP/ESOP-97 Radar: NCRFC WSR-88D Stage III Hourly Precipitation Imagery (GIF)
summary: This data set contains data from the NOAA North Central River Forecast Center (NCRFC). The NCRFC routinely ingests WSR-88D precipitation derived products (Level III) from  each of the radar sites with coverage in the Upper  Mississippi River Basin. In addition the NCRFC ingests  real-time precipitation data from several hundred gages.  The NCRFC produces a number of derived or Stage" products  using the radar and precipitation gage data. A Stage II  product is produced by merging radar precipitation  estimates  (Stage I) with ground truth data  provided by  the gages. The Stage II estimates are then composited into  a Stage III precipitation 4 x 4 km resolution area averaged mosaic for the Upper Mississippi River Basin. "

title: GCIP/ESOP-98 Satellite: GOES-8 VIS LSA-NC Sector Images (GIF)
summary: GOES-8 Visible satellite imagery collected for the GCIP Enhanced Seasonal Observing Period 1998 (ESOP-98)  via McIDAS-X and then converted to GIF image format. These  images are at 1 km resolution and are sectors over the LSA-NC region. These data are available for browsing purposes, and should not be used for detailed scientific analyses.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Surface: Sensible, Latent and Ground Heat Flux Composite
summary: NOAA/ATDD Little Washita flux data and ARM SGP EBBR data have been composited together into one dataset. This dataset is composed of half hourly observations of latent heat flux, sensible heat flux, and the corrected soil heat flux from 5 separate sensors. These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS). However, included for checking the validity of the data are the Bowen ratio, the home_15 (Exchange Mechanism Position Indicator 1 to 15 mins) and the home_30 (Exchange Mechanism Position Indicator 15 to 30 mins). If values for home_15 or home_30 are corrupted, the latent and sensible flux fields should be considered suspect.

title: GCIP/ESOP-98 Radar: NCRFC WSR-88D Stage III Hourly Precipitation Imagery (GIF)
summary: This data set contains data from the NOAA North Central River Forecast Center (NCRFC). The NCRFC routinely ingests WSR-88D precipitation derived products (Level III) from  each of the radar sites with coverage in the Upper  Mississippi River Basin. In addition the NCRFC ingests  real-time precipitation data from several hundred gages.  The NCRFC produces a number of derived or Stage" products  using the radar and precipitation gage data. A Stage II  product is produced by merging radar precipitation  estimates  (Stage I) with ground truth data  provided by  the gages. The Stage II estimates are then composited into  a Stage III precipitation 4 x 4 km resolution area averaged mosaic for the Upper Mississippi River Basin. "

summary: This data set contains a limited set of WSR-88D Level III  data products archived from the WSI NIDS datastream for  four radars in the GCIP/EAOP-98 domain (JKL, MRX, PBZ, and RLX) for the period October 1997 to September 1998.  Also,  for the period December 1997 and January  1998 DTX, GRB, and GRR were collected for the Lake-ICE project.   The products archived are base reflectivity and velocity at the first four tilts, composite reflectivity, and Vertical Azimuth Display (VAD) wind profile.  Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format on  exabyte tape.  One week's data is contained on a single tape, as one Unix tar" file per day."

title: GCIP/EAOP-99 Radar: WSI NIDS Radar Data

The products archived are base reflectivity and velocity at the first four tilts, composite reflectivity, and Vertical Azimuth Display (VAD) wind profile.  Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format on  exabyte tape.  One week's data is contained on a single tape, as one Unix tar" file per day."

title: GCIP/EAOP-98 Sub-Surface: USDA/NRCS Soil Moisture/Soil Temperature Data (PROVISIONAL)
summary: This data set contains the USDA/NRCS Soil Moisture/Soil Temperature Network data.  Data are available only from those states within the GCIP/EOP region.  These data are provided as is and were not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS. Please see the README file for more complete  information. These data are PROVISIONAL and are subject to revision by the USDA/NRCS.

title: GCIP/EAOP-98 Radar: LMRFC WSR-88D Stage III Hourly Precipitation Imagery (GIF)
summary: This data set contains data from the NOAA Lower Mississippi River Forecast Center (LMRFC). The LMRFC routinely ingests WSR-88D precipitation derived products (Level III) from  each of the radar sites with coverage in the Lower  Mississippi River Basin. In addition the LMRFC ingests  real-time precipitation data from several hundred gages.  The LMRFC produces a number of derived or Stage" products  using the radar and precipitation gage data. A Stage II  product is produced by merging radar precipitation  estimates  (Stage I) with ground truth data  provided by  the gages. The Stage II estimates are then composited into  a Stage III precipitation 4 x 4 km resolution area averaged mosaic for the Lower Mississippi River Basin. "

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Surface: Momentum Flux Data
summary: NOAA/ATDD Little Washita momentum flux data. This dataset is composed of half hourly observations of average wind vector speed, kinematic shear stress, streamwise velocity variance, crosswind velocity variance, and vertical velocity variance. These data were not quality checked by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: SGP97 Upper Air: NOAA Wind Profiler Network Hourly Winds
summary: This dataset contains the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) 405 MHZ Wind Profiler Network (NPN) hourly data from 2 sites within the SGP 1997 area of interest.  This data consists of a series of hourly observations, each containing wind speed and direction data. These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: CASES-97: Upper Air PRELIMINARY Beaumont 5-mb CLASS soundings
summary: This is a preliminary release, please see the README file for complete information. This data set consists of CLASS soundings taken at Beaumont, Kansas for the CASES-97 program. The site was operated by the National Center for Atmospheric Research/Atmospheric Technology Division (NCAR/ ATD). These soundings have been interpolated to 5-mb vertical intervals. The quality control information is that provided by NCAR/ATD. UCAR/JOSS has not changed these soundings in any way. This data set includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude. Refer to the README file for details.

title: GCIP/EAOP-98 Hydrology: USGS Stream Flow Data
summary: This dataset contains daily observations of stream flow from the United States Geological Survey (USGS) and selected United States Army Corps of Engineers gages. title: UMRBPP Surface: Cooperative Observer Summary of the Day Data Set

title: GCIP/LSA-NW 99 Radar: WSI NIDS Radar Data
summary: This data set contains a limited set of WSR-88D Level III data products archived from the WSI NIDS datastream for four radars in the GCIP/LSA-NW 99 domain (BLX, LNX, RIW, and UDX). The products archived are base reflectivity and velocity at the first four tilts, composite reflectivity, and Vertical Azimuth Display (VAD) wind profile. Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format on exabyte tape. One week's data is contained on a single tape, as one Unix "tar" file per day.

title: SGP97 Hydrology: USGS Stream Flow Data
summary: This dataset contains daily observations of stream flow from the United States Geological Survey (USGS) and selected United States Army Corps of Engineers gages. A total of 997 stations reported within the SGP97 domain. NOTE - the streamflow data are generally not adjusted for diversions or reservoir storage.

title: SGP97 Sub-Surface: USDA/NRCS Soil Moisture/Soil Temperature Network Data (PROVISIONAL)
summary: This dataset contains the USDA/NRCS Soil Moisture/Soil Temperature Network data.  These data are provided as is and were not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS. Please see the README file for more complete information. These data are PROVISIONAL and are subject to revision by the USDA/NRCS.

title: COMET CASE 023 NCEP's Eta Model.
summary: This dataset contains data from  NCEP's Eta Model. Model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecast times every six hours from 00 to 48 hours..  The data are archived in GRIB gridded files.

title: COMET CASE 023 NCEP's Meso-Eta Model.
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Meso-Eta Model. The Meso-Eta model is run on 03Z and 15Z daily. The forecasts goes out 33 hours and is given every 3 hours. The geographic region covered is the United States .  The data are archived in GRIB gridded files.

title: COMET CASE 023 NCEP's Medium Range Forecast (MRF) Model.

title: COMET CASE 023 NCEP's Nested Gridded Model (NGM).
summary: This dataset contains data from  NCEP's Nested Gridded Model (NGM). The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecasts given every six hours going out 48 hours .  The data are archived in GRIB gridded files.

title: COMET CASE 023 NCEP's RUC surface analysis (RSAS) Model.
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's RUC surface analysis (RSAS) Model. The analysis is given every hour and is on model grid 87..  The data are archived in GRIB gridded files.

title: COMET CASE 023 NCEP's Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) Model.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Surface: Shortwave and Longwave Radiation Composite
summary: ARM SGP SIROS data, ARM SGP BSRN data, and ARM SGP 25m MFR data have been composited together into one data set. This data set is composed of 30-minute averages of observations taken either at 20 seconds (SIROS and MFR) or 60 seconds (BSRN). The SIROS data contains observations of Upwelling and Downwelling Longwave and Shortwave Irradiance. The BSRN data has Downwelling Longwave and Shortwave; and the MFR network contains Upwelling Longwave and Shortwave Irradiance.  These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Surface: Net Radiation and PAR Composite
summary: NOAA/ATDD Little Washita Flux data and derived values from ARM SGP SIROS data have been composited together into one data set. This data set is composed of 30-minute observations of Incoming PAR, Outgoing PAR, and Net Radiation from the NOAA/ATDD site, and a Net Radiation value derived from 20-second observations from the SIROS network.  These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Sub-Surface: USDA-ARS Grazinglands Research Laboratory Soil Temperature
summary: The GCIP/NESOB-96 Sub-Surface USDA-ARS Grazinglands Research Laboratory (GRL) Soil Temperature Dataset contains data from the United States Department of Agriculture-Agricultural Research Service (USDA-ARS) Grazinglands Research Laboratory (GRL). This dataset contains data for two USDA/ARS/GRL networks in the NESOB 1996 domain (100.5 W to 94.5 W longitude and 34 N to 39 N latitude) and time period (01 April 1996 through 30 September 1996).

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Radar: NIDS Radar Data
summary: This data set contains a limited set of WSR-88D Level III  data products archived from the NIDS datastream for  nine radars in the GCIP/LSA-SW domain.  The products archived are base reflectivity and velocity at 0.5 and 1.5 degrees, composite reflectivity, and Vertical Azimuth Display (VAD) wind profile.   The sites that were archived are KDDC, KICT, KINX, KFDR, KTLX, KAMA, KFTG, KGLD, and KPUX.  Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format on  exabyte tape.  One week's data is contained on a single tape, as one Unix tar" file per day."

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Radar: Composite Radar Imagery (GIF)
summary: This dataset contains images generated from the the WSI  NIDS 2 km national radar mosaic for the GCIP/NESOB-97  period.  These data are provided for data browsing purposes.

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Sub-Surface: ARM Organic Carbon and Organic Matter Soils Data Set
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Organic Carbon and Organic Matter Soils Data Set is one of the various sub-surface data sets developed for the ARM/GCIP (Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment ?GEWEX? Continental-scale International Project) 1997 Near-Surface Observation (NESOB-97) Data Set. This data set contains a summary table of the measured organic carbon percentage and the estimated organic matter percentage in the near surface soil at each of the ARM SWATS (Soil Water and Temperature System) sites at the SGP site. The soil characterizations were perfomed by Oklahoma State University. No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Sub-Surface: ARM Soil Texture Data Set
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Soil Texture Data Set is one of the various sub-surface data sets developed for the ARM/GCIP (Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment ?GEWEX? Continental-scale International Project) 1997 Near-Surface Observation (NESOB-97) Data Set. This data set contains a summary table of the percentages of sand, silt, and clay fractions in each soil layer at each of the ARM SWATS (Soil Water and Temperature System) sites at the SGP site. Also included is the corresponding USDA texture class as determined from the soil triangle". The soil characterizations were perfomed by Oklahoma State University. No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS)."

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Sub-Surface: ARM Parameters for Soil Water Retention Models Data Set
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Parameters for Soil Water Retention Models Data Set is one of the various sub-surface data sets developed for the ARM/GCIP (Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment ?GEWEX? Continental-scale International Project) 1997 Near-Surface Observation (NESOB-97) Data Set. This data set contains one table for each of the ARM SWATS (Soil Water and Temperature System) sites at the SGP site containing the fitted values of the parameters in the van Genuchten and Brooks-Corey equations for relating soil water pressure to volumetric water content. The soil characterizations were perfomed by Oklahoma State University. No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Sub-Surface: ARM Soil Bulk Density Data Set
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Soil Bulk Density Data Set is one of the various sub-surface data sets developed for the ARM/GCIP (Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment ?GEWEX? Continental-scale International Project) 1997 Near-Surface Observation (NESOB-97) Data Set. This data set contains a summary table of the bulk densities representing the average of the values obtained from the soil water retention samples at each of the ARM SWATS (Soil Water and Temperature System) sites at the SGP site. The soil characterizations were perfomed by Oklahoma State University. No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Sub-Surface: ARM Soil Particle Size Data Set
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Soil Particle Size Data Set is one of the various sub-surface data sets developed for the ARM/GCIP (Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment ?GEWEX? Continental-scale International Project) 1997 Near-Surface Observation (NESOB-97) Data Set. This data set contains tables of the laboratory data for each soil layer at each of the ARM SWATS (Soil Water and Temperature System) sites at the SGP site. The soil characterizations were perfomed by Oklahoma State University. No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Sub-Surface: ARM Soil Water Retention Data Set
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Soil Water Retention Data Set is one of the various sub-surface data sets developed for the ARM/GCIP (Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment ?GEWEX? Continental-scale International Project) 1997 Near-Surface Observation (NESOB-97) Data Set. This data set contains a table for each of the ARM SWATS (Soil Water and Temperature System) sites at the SGP site containing the observed soil water retention data as obtained from laboratory tests using pressure plates and hanging columns. The soil characterizations were perfomed by Oklahoma State University. No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/EAOP-99 Radar: LMRFC WSR-88D Stage III Hourly Precipitation Imagery (GIF)
summary: This data set contains data from the NOAA Lower Mississippi River Forecast Center (LMRFC). The LMRFC routinely ingests WSR-88D precipitation derived products (Level III) from  each of the radar sites with coverage in the Lower  Mississippi River Basin. In addition the LMRFC ingests  real-time precipitation data from several hundred gages.  The LMRFC produces a number of derived or Stage" products  using the radar and precipitation gage data. A Stage II  product is produced by merging radar precipitation  estimates  (Stage I) with ground truth data  provided by  the gages. The Stage II estimates are then composited into  a Stage III precipitation 4 x 4 km resolution area averaged mosaic for the Lower Mississippi River Basin. "

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: NOAA/ATDD Bondville, Illinois Long Term Flux Site
summary: The NOAA/ATDD (Tilden Meyers) started operation of a long term flux monitoring site near Bondville, Illinois in 1996. Half-hourly observations of wind speed and direction, air temperature, relative humidity, pressure, incoming global radiation, incoming (and outgoing) visible radiation, net radiation, ground heat flux, precipitation, wetness, skin temperature, soil temperature (at 2, 4, 8, 16, 32 and  64 cm), average wind vector speed, kinematic shear stress, streamwise velocity variance, crosswind velocity variance, vertical velocity variance, sensible heat flux, latent energy flux, CO2 flux, downwelling longwave from the sky and soil moisture (at depths of 5, 20 and 60 cm; started 19 November 1997).  For further information on this data set see the README file.

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: NOAA/ATDD Little Washita, Oklahoma Long Term Flux Site
summary: The NOAA/ATDD (Tilden Meyers) started operation of a long term flux monitoring site near the Little Washita watershed in Oklahoma in 1996. summary: This dataset contains the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) 405 MHZ Wind Profiler Network (NPN) hourly data from 2 sites within the SGP 1999 area of interest. title: SGP99 Surface: High Plains Climate Network Data
summary: This dataset contains hourly surface observations from the High Plains Climate Network. A total of 15 stations reported within the SGP99 domain. This data is provided as is" in its original format. No additional quality control was performed on this dataset by UCAR/JOSS."

title: GCIP/LSA-NW 99 Surface: NOAA/ATDD Fort Peck, Montana Long Term Flux Site
summary: The NOAA/ATDD (Tilden Meyers) started operation of a long term flux monitoring site in Fort Peck, Montana in November 1999.  Half-hourly observations of wind speed and direction, air temperature, relative humidity, pressure, incoming global radiation, incoming and outgoing visible radiation, net radiation, ground heat flux, precipitation, wetness, skin temperature, soil temperature (at 2, 4, 8, 16, 32 and 64 cm), average wind vector speed, kinematic shear stress, streamwise velocity variance, crosswind velocity variance, vertical velocity variance, sensible heat flux, latent energy flux, CO2 flux and soil moisture at 15, 30, and 60 cm. For further information on this data set see the README file.

title: Upper Air PRELIMINARY Beaumont 1.5 second PTH CLASS soundings
summary: This is a preliminary release, please see the README file for complete information. This data set consists of CLASS soundings taken at Beaumont, Kansas for the CASES-97 program. The site was operated by the National Center for Atmospheric Research/Atmospheric Technology Division (NCAR/ ATD). These data are the high resolution raw 1.5 second vertical interval pressure, temperature, and humidity observations. No quality control information have been provided with these files by either NCAR/ATD or UCAR/JOSS. This data set includes pressure, temperature, dew point, and relative humidity. Refer to the README file for details.

title: COMET CASE 026 NCEP's Nested Gridded Model (NGM).

title: COMET CASE 026 NCEP's RUC surface analysis (RSAS) Model.
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's RUC surface analysis (RSAS) Model. The analysis is given every hour and is on model grid 87..  The data are archived in GRIB gridded files.

title: COMET CASE 026 NCEP's Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) Model.
summary: This dataset contains data from  NCEP's Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) Model. The model runs are every hour with forecasts given every 3 hours going out 12 hours..  The data are archived in GRIB gridded files.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Surface: NCDC Summary of the Day COOP Dataset
summary: This dataset contains the GCIP/NESOB-96 National Climatic Data Center (NCDC) Summary of the Day Co-operative (COOP) data for the NESOB-96 domain. The observations in this dataset are primarily those from the cooperative network, augmented by observations from principal observing stations operated by the NWS and other sites having highly trained observers. Quality Control for this data was provided by NCDC. No additional QC was performed by JOSS on this dataset.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Surface: BLC/MPL Cloud Composite Dataset
summary: This dataset contains the GCIP/NESOB-96 ARMCART SGP Belfort Laser Ceiliometer (BLC) and MicroPulse Lidar (MPL) data for the NESOB-96 domain and time period. The BLC cloud heights contain a 110-meter upward vertical offset that has not been corrected in the data. These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Radar: ABRFC WSR-88D Stage III Hourly Precipitation
summary: This dataset contains data from the NOAA Arkansas-Red Basin River Forecast Center. The ABRFC routinely ingests WSR-88D  precipitation derived products (Level III) from each of the radar sites with coverage in the Arkansas-Red River Basin  (15 radars). In addition the ABRFC ingests real-time  precipitation data from a total of approximately 500 gages. The ABRFC produces a number of derived or Stage" products  using the radar and precipitation gage data. A Stage II  product is produced by merging radar precipitation  estimates  (Stage I) with ground truth data  provided by  the gages. The Stage II estimates are then composited into  a Stage III precipitation 4 x 4 km resolution area averaged mosaic for the Arkansas-Red River Basin. "

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Radar: ABRFC WSR-88D Stage III Daily Precipitation
summary: This dataset contains data from the NOAA Arkansas-Red Basin River Forecast Center. The ABRFC routinely ingests WSR-88D  precipitation derived products (Level III) from each of the radar sites with coverage in the Arkansas-Red River Basin  (15 radars). In addition the ABRFC ingests real-time  precipitation data from a total of approximately 500 gages. The ABRFC produces a number of derived or Stage" products  using the radar and precipitation gage data. A Stage II  product is produced by merging radar precipitation  estimates  (Stage I) with ground truth data  provided by  the gages. The Stage II estimates are then composited into  a Stage III precipitation 4 x 4 km resolution area averaged mosaic for the Arkansas-Red River Basin. "

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Ancillary: Station List
summary: This dataset contains a list of stations whose data are included in the GCIP/NESOB-96 data sets. This list includes station name, latitude, longitude, elevation, station type, observing network ID, and station id.

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Surface: Net Radiation and PAR Composite
summary: NOAA/ATDD Little Washita Flux data and derived values from ARM SGP SIROS and SIRS data have been composited together into one data set. This data set is composed of 30-minute observations of Incoming PAR, Outgoing PAR, and Net Radiation from the NOAA/ATDD site, and a Net Radiation value derived from 20-second observations from the SIROS and SIRS networks.  These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Surface: NCDC Summary of the Day COOP Dataset
summary: This dataset contains the GCIP/NESOB-97 National Climatic Data Center (NCDC) Summary of the Day Co-operative (COOP) data for the NESOB-97 domain. The observations in this dataset are primarily those from the cooperative network, augmented by observations from principal observing stations operated by the NWS and other sites having highly trained observers. Quality Control for this data was provided by NCDC. No additional QC was performed by JOSS on this dataset.

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Surface: Skin Temperature Composite
summary: The GCIP/NESOB-97 Surface: Skin Temperature Composite dataset is composed of 30 minute observations of skin temperaturesderived from 3 sources. These are: Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Solar and Infrared Radiation Observing System (SIROS) 10M and 25M, and the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration NOAA/Atmospheric Turbulence and Diffusion Division (ATDD) long term flux monitoring site located in the Little Washita Watershed. These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS). Standard deviations are included.

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Surface: NCDC Daily Evaporation Dataset
summary: The GCIP/NESOB-97 Surface NCDC Daily Evaporation Dataset contains data from the National Climatic Data Center (NCDC). This dataset was formed by extracting evaporation data from the GCIP/Enhanced Seasonal Observing Period 1997 (GCIP/ESOP-97) NCDC Summary of the Day Cooperative Dataset for the NESOB 1997 area and time of interest.

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Surface: Shortwave and Longwave Radiation Composite
summary: ARM SGP SIROS data, ARM SGP SIRS data, ARM SGP BSRN data, ARM SGP 25m MFR data, and HPCN data have been composited together into one data set. This data set is composed of 30-minute averages of observations taken either at 20 seconds (SIROS, SIRS and MFR) or 60 seconds (BSRN); or hourly data (HPCN). The SIROS and SIRS data contains observations of Upwelling and Downwelling Longwave and Shortwave Irradiance. The BSRN data has Downwelling Longwave and Shortwave; the MFR network contains Upwelling Longwave and Shortwave Irradiance; and the HPCN contains solar radiation equivalent to Downwelling Shortwave.  These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Surface: Sensible, Latent and Ground Heat Flux Composite
summary: NOAA/ATDD Little Washita flux data, ARM SGP EBBR data, and ARM SGP ECOR data have been composited together into one dataset. This dataset is composed of half hourly observations of latent heat flux, sensible heat flux, and the corrected soil heat flux from 5 separate sensors. These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS). However, included for checking the validity of the data are the Bowen ratio, the home_15 (Exchange Mechanism Position Indicator 1 to 15 mins) and the home_30 (Exchange Mechanism Position Indicator 15 to 30 mins). If values for home_15 or home_30 are corrupted, the latent and sensible flux fields should be considered suspect.

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Surface: Momentum Flux Composite
summary: This data set is a composite of momentum flux data from the NOAA/ATDD Little Washita site and the ECOR sites. It is composed of half hourly observations of average wind vector speed, uv covariance from the mean, kiematic shear stress, vw covariance from the mean, streamwise velocity variance, crosswind velocity variance, and vertical velocity variance. These data were not quality checked by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: COMET CASE 032 NCEP's Rapid Update Cycle (RUC) Model.

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Sub-Surface: NOAA/ATDD Little Washita 30 Min Soil Moisture
summary: The GCIP/NESOB-97 Sub-Surface NOAA/ATDD Little Washita 30 Minute Soil Moisture Dataset contains data from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration/Atmospheric Turbulence and Diffusion Division (NOAA/ATDD) Little Washita Watershed Long Term Flux Site, near Chickasha, Oklahoma. This dataset contains data for one station within the NESOB 1997 domain (100.5 W to 94.5 W longitude and 34 N to 39 N latitude) and time period (01 April 1997 through 31 March 1998).

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Sub-Surface: ARM SWATS Data (Preliminary)
summary: The Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment (GEWEX)  Continental-scale International Project (GCIP) Enhanced  Observing Period (EOP) Department of Energy (DOE)  Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great  Plains (SGP) Soil Water and Temperature System (SWATS) data set is provided as is" and was not quality controlled by  UCAR/JOSS.    The Soil Water and Temperature System is designed to  provide information about the temperature of the soil and  the status of water in the soil profile. Sensors installed  at various depths below the soil surface provide hourly  measurements of soil temperature and estimates of soil-waterpotential and volumetric water content. SWATS systems are  installed at 21 of the ARM/SGP/CART Extended Facilities  (EFs).   Please see the README file for more complete information."

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Land Characterization: EDC 1-km AVHRR Project
summary: The data set is composed of 5-channel, 10-bit, raw AVHRR data, at 1.1-km resolution (at nadir) for every daily afternoon pass over all land and coastal zones using data from NOAA's polar-orbiting TIROS. Initially the data were to be collected continuously for 18 consecutive months beginning April 1, 1992, and continuing through September 30, 1993, subsequently the period has been extended to September 30, 1996.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Land Characterization: EDC NASA Landsat Pathfinder
summary: The North American Landscape Characterization (NALC) project is a collaborative effort between the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) and the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) to provide complete coverage of the conterminous U.S. and Mexico for the purposes of mapping land cover and land cover change.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Land Characterization: EDC Conterminous US AVHRR
summary: In May 1987, the U.S. Geological Survey's EROS Data Center (EDC) began real-time reception of Advanced Very High Resolution Radiometer (AVHRR) data from operational NOAA polar orbiting satellites. EDC receives AVHRR High Resolution Picture Transmission (HRPT) data for the entire conterminous United States, southern Canada, and northern Mexico. The AVHRR Data Acquisition and Processing System (ADAPS) includes a tracking antenna, a data receiving subsystem, and a minicomputer with associated peripherals for data processing. Since the 1989 growing season EDC has used the AVHRR (1 km resolution) daily observations to produce weekly and biweekly maximum Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI) composites of the conterminous United States.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Land Characterization: USGS Land Use and Land Cover Data
summary: The Land Use and Land Cover (LULC) data files describe the vegetation, water, natural surface, and cultural features on the land surface. The United States Geological Survey (USGS) provides these data sets and associated maps as a part of its National Mapping Program. The LULC mapping program is designed so that standard topographic maps of a scale of 1:250,000 can be used for compilation and organization of the land use and land cover data. In some cases, such as Hawaii, 1:100,000 scale maps are also used.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Land Characterization: NOAA/NESDIS/ORA Land Surface Team GVI Products
summary: The third generation Global Vegetation Index (GVI) weekly composite data are produced operationally by NOAA/NESDIS and includes conversion of counts to reflectances and brightness temperatures using the post-launch calibration and non-linearity correction coefficients. Cloud flags are generated and appended to each map cell. The GVI dataset represents a sample of Global Area Coverage (GAC) observations mapped into 0.144 degree resolution maps in equal-angle projection (Plate Carree). A 7-day composite is a mosaic of observations produced by retaining data for each map cell corresponding to the maximum difference between AVHRR channels 2 and 1. Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI) is calculated from AVHRR channel 2 and 1 reflectances using the following formula: NDVI = (CH2 - CH1) / (CH2 + CH1)

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Land Characterization: GTOPO30 Global Digital Elevation Model
summary: GTOPO30 is a global digital elevation model (DEM) with a horizontal grid spacing of 30 arc seconds (approximately 1 kilometer). GTOPO30 was derived from several raster and vector sources of topographic information. For easier distribution, GTOPO30 has been divided into tiles.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Land Characterization: HYDRO 1K Elevation Derivative Database
summary: HYDRO1k is a geographic database developed to provide comprehensive and consistent global coverage of topographically derived data sets, including streams, drainage basins and ancillary layers derived from the USGS' 30 arc-second digital elevation model of the world (GTOPO30). HYDRO1k provides a suite of geo-referenced data sets, both raster and vector, which will be of value for all users who need to organize, evaluate, or process hydrologic information on a continental scale.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Sub-Surface: USDA/NRCS STATSGO Data
summary: This dataset is a remote link to the USDA/NRCS STATGO web site.  State general soil maps made by generalizing the detailed soil survey data. The level of mapping is  designed to be used for broad planning and management  uses covering state, regional, and multi-state areas.  STATSGO data are designed for use in a Geographic  Information System (GIS).  STATSGO data are available in the USGS Digital Line  Graph (DLG-3) optional distribution format. NRCS soil  map symbols are not normally carried within the DLG-3  file; however, these map symbols are made available as  a unique ASCII file when NRCS soils data are  distributed in the DLG-3 format. STATSGO data are also  available in ArcInfo 7.0 coverage and GRASS 4.13 vector formats.

Field mapping methods using national standards are used to construct the soil maps in the Soil Survey  Geographic (SSURGO) data base. Mapping scales generally  range from 1:12,000 to 1:63,360; SSURGO is the most  detailed level of soil mapping done by the Natural  Resources Conservation Service (NRCS). SSURGO digitizing  duplicates the original soil survey maps. This level of  mapping is designed for use by landowners, townships,  and county natural resource planning and management.  The user should be knowledgeable of soils data and their characteristics.

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Upper Air: ARM-CART 50 Mhz Profiler and RASS Data Set
summary: This dataset contains vertical profiles of virtual temperature and wind speed and direction taken from the Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Clouds and Radiation Testbed (CART) Central Facility 50 Mhz Profiler and Radio Acoustic Sounding System (RASS) in Lamont, Oklahoma. Profiles are generated every hour. The vertical resolution of RASS virtual temperature is ~150 m. The vertical resolution of the high mode wind profiles is ~1000 m and for the low mode wind profiles it is ~300 m. See the Readme file for more details.

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Upper Air: ARM-CART MWR Vertical Profile Data Set

Profiles are generated hourly.  See the Readme file for more details.

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Upper Air: ARM-CART AERI Vertical Profile Data Set
summary: This dataset contains vertical profiles of temperature,  dew point, relative humidity, altitude, and pressure taken from the Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Clouds and Radiation Testbed (CART) Central Facility Atmospheric Emitted Radiation Interferometer (AERI) in Lamont, Oklahoma. Profiles are generated every eight minutes. The vertical resolution is 100 m up to 1.3 km  and 200 - 250 m above 1.3 km. See the Readme file for more details.

summary: The ACE-Asia Aircraft C-130 Aerosol Fast anions and cations, 3-4 minutes (Weber) data are now available online. Airborne measurements of soluble aerosol particles were made from March 30 to May 4, 2001 using a particles-into-liquid-sampler (PILS). 124-145 LON, 23-43 LAT

title: GCIP/EOP Sub-Surface: USDA/NRCS Soil Moisture/Soil Temperature Network Data (web link)
summary: This dataset contains the USDA/NRCS Soil Climate Analysis Network (SCAN; formerly the Soil Moisture/Soil Temperature Network) data.  This data is  provided as is and was not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS. Please see the README file for more complete information.  These data are available online from the USDA/NRCS.

title: GCIP/ESOP-98 Surface: ChEAS Micrometeorological Network Data
summary: This data set is provided via a link to the ftp site at the University of Minnesota.  ChEAS is the Chequamegon  Ecosystem-Atmosphere Study and it takes place in northern Wisconsin.  The data consists of a network of micrometeorological stations located beneath various canopy types.  A variety of meteorological, soils, radiation, and flux measurements are available.  Please see the README's at the ftp site for further information.

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: ChEAS Micrometeorological Network Data
summary: This data set is provided via a link to the ftp site at the University of Minnesota.  ChEAS is the Chequamegon  Ecosystem-Atmosphere Study and takes place in northern Wisconsin (see http://ra.forest.wisc.edu/cheas).  The data  consists of a network of micrometeorological stations located beneath various canopy types.  A variety of  meteorological, soils, radiation, and flux measurements are available.  Please see the README's at the ftp site for further information.

title: GCIP/EOP Sub-Surface: PSU USDA/NRCS STATSGO Data
summary: This dataset is a remote link to the PSU Soil Information web site. The state-by-state data from the USDA/NRCS CDROM is available for downloading as Arc/Info EXPORT format files.

title: GCIP/EOP Sub-Surface: USDA/NRCS SSURGO Data
summary: This dataset is a remote link to the USDA/NRCS SSURGO web site.  Field mapping methods using national standards are used to construct the soil maps in the Soil Survey  Geographic (SSURGO) data base. Mapping scales generally  range from 1:12,000 to 1:63,360; SSURGO is the most  detailed level of soil mapping done by the Natural  Resources Conservation Service (NRCS). SSURGO digitizing  duplicates the original soil survey maps. This level of  mapping is designed for use by landowners, townships,  and county natural resource planning and management.  The user should be knowledgeable of soils data and their characteristics.

title: GCIP/EOP Sub-Surface: USDA/NRCS STATSGO Data
summary: This dataset is a remote link to the USDA/NRCS STATGO web site.  State general soil maps made by generalizing the detailed soil survey data. The level of mapping is  designed to be used for broad planning and management  uses covering state, regional, and multi-state areas.  STATSGO data are designed for use in a Geographic  Information System (GIS).  STATSGO data are available in the USGS Digital Line  Graph (DLG-3) optional distribution format. NRCS soil  map symbols are not normally carried within the DLG-3  file; however, these map symbols are made available as  a unique ASCII file when NRCS soils data are  distributed in the DLG-3 format. STATSGO data are also  available in ArcInfo 7.0 coverage and GRASS 4.13 vector formats.

title: GCIP/EOP Land Characterization: EDC 1-km AVHRR Project
summary: The data set is composed of 5-channel, 10-bit, raw AVHRR data, at 1.1-km resolution (at nadir) for every daily afternoon pass over all land and coastal zones using data from NOAA's polar-orbiting TIROS. Initially the data were to be collected continuously for 18 consecutive months beginning April 1, 1992, and continuing through September 30, 1993, subsequently the period has been extended to September 30, 1996.

title: GCIP/EOP Land Characterization: USGS Land Use and Land Cover Data
summary: The Land Use and Land Cover (LULC) data files describe the vegetation, water, natural surface, and cultural features on the land surface. The United States Geological Survey (USGS) provides these data sets and associated maps as a part of its National Mapping Program. The LULC mapping program is designed so that standard topographic maps of a scale of 1:250,000 can be used for compilation and organization of the land use and land cover data. In some cases, such as Hawaii, 1:100,000 scale maps are also used.

title: GCIP/EOP Land Characterization: NOAA/NESDIS/ORA Land Surface Team GVI Products
summary: The third generation Global Vegetation Index (GVI) weekly composite data are produced operationally by NOAA/NESDIS and includes conversion of counts to reflectances and brightness temperatures using the post-launch calibration and non-linearity correction coefficients. Cloud flags are generated and appended to each map cell. The GVI dataset represents a sample of Global Area Coverage (GAC) observations mapped into 0.144 degree resolution maps in equal-angle projection (Plate Carree). A 7-day composite is a mosaic of observations produced by retaining data for each map cell corresponding to the maximum difference between AVHRR channels 2 and 1. Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI) is calculated from AVHRR channel 2 and 1 reflectances using the following formula: NDVI = (CH2 - CH1) / (CH2 + CH1)

title: GCIP/EOP Land Characterization: GTOPO30 Global Digital Elevation Model
summary: GTOPO30 is a global digital elevation model (DEM) with a horizontal grid spacing of 30 arc seconds (approximately 1 kilometer). GTOPO30 was derived from several raster and vector sources of topographic information. For easier distribution, GTOPO30 has been divided into tiles.

title: GCIP/EOP Land Characterization: HYDRO 1K Elevation Derivative Database
summary: HYDRO1k is a geographic database developed to provide comprehensive and consistent global coverage of topographically derived data sets, including streams, drainage basins and ancillary layers derived from the USGS' 30 arc-second digital elevation model of the world (GTOPO30). HYDRO1k provides a suite of geo-referenced data sets, both raster and vector, which will be of value for all users who need to organize, evaluate, or process hydrologic information on a continental scale.

title: SGP97 Satellite: NOAA POES AVHRR GAC Data (via SAA)
summary: This dataset contains data from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) Polar Orbiting Environmental Satellites (POES) Advanced Very High Reoslution Radiometer (AVHRR) instrument.  The data are the 4 km resolution Level 1B Global Area Coverage (GAC) produced on-board the satellite by sampling the AVHRR 1 km data to 4 km by averaging along-scan groups of four samples out of five and skipping every third scan.  The data includes all five channels at 10 bit precision, with time tags, Earth location, and calibration information.  These data are available on-line from the Satellite Active Archive (SAA) at: http://www.saa.noaa.gov/help/summary/avhrr1b.html

title: SGP99 Satellite: NOAA POES AVHRR GAC Data (via SAA)
summary: This dataset contains data from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) Polar Orbiting Environmental Satellites (POES) Advanced Very High Reoslution Radiometer (AVHRR) instrument. title: GCIP/EAOP-99 Upper Air: NOAA Wind Profiler Network Hourly Winds
summary: This dataset contains the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) 405 MHZ Wind Profiler Network (WPN) hourly data from 1 site within the EAOP 1999 area of interest.  These data consist of a series of hourly observations, each containing approximately 64 levels of wind speed and direction data.  These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/ESOP-97 Upper Air: NOAA Wind Profiler Network Hourly Winds
summary: This dataset contains the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) 405 MHZ Wind Profiler Network (WPN) hourly data from 10 sites within the ESOP 1997 area of interest. title: SGP99 Radar: ABRFC WSR-88D Stage III Daily Precipitation
summary: This dataset contains data from the NOAA Arkansas-Red Basin River Forecast Center. The ABRFC routinely ingests WSR-88D  precipitation derived products (Level III) from each of the radar sites with coverage in the Arkansas-Red River Basin  (15 radars). In addition the ABRFC ingests real-time  precipitation data from a total of approximately 500 gages. The ABRFC produces a number of derived or Stage" products  using the radar and precipitation gage data. A Stage II  product is produced by merging radar precipitation  estimates  (Stage I) with ground truth data  provided by  the gages. The Stage II estimates are then composited into  a Stage III precipitation 4 x 4 km resolution area averaged mosaic for the Arkansas-Red River Basin. "

title: SGP99 Radar: ABRFC WSR-88D Stage III Hourly Precipitation
summary: This dataset contains data from the NOAA Arkansas-Red Basin River Forecast Center. The Stage II estimates are then composited into  a Stage III precipitation 4 x 4 km resolution area averaged mosaic for the Arkansas-Red River Basin. "

Other sites also occasionally other sites also released radiosonde and are included. These data have not been changed or quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS.  Refer to the README file for more details.

title: GCIP/LSA-NW 99 Upper Air: NOAA Wind Profiler Network Hourly Winds
summary: This dataset contains the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) 405 MHZ Wind Profiler Network (WPN) hourly data from 18 sites within the LSA-NW area of interest. These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/LSA-NW 99 Surface: NCDC Summary of the Day COOP Dataset
summary: This dataset contains the Continental-scale International Project (GCIP) Large Scale Area-North West (LSA-NW) National Climatic Data Center (NCDC) Summary of the Day Co-operative (COOP) data for the Enhanced Annual Observing Period - 1999 (EAOP-99) domain. The observations in this dataset are primarily those from the cooperative network, augmented by observations from principal observing stations operated by the NWS and other sites having highly trained observers. Quality Control for this data was provided by NCDC. No additional QC was performed by JOSS on this dataset.

title: GCIP/LSA-NW 99 Surface: NCEP/CPC Hourly Precipitation Data in QC format
summary: This dataset contains National Centers for Environmental Prediction/Climate Prediction Center (NCEP/CPC) Hourly Precipitation data in QC format for the GCIP LSA-NW EAOP-99 domain and time period. This dataset was formed by extracting incremental precipitation values that fell on the hour.  All raw precipitation data, including data that do not fall on the hour, can be found in the GCIP/EOP Surface: Precipitation NCEP/CPC Gage Only Hourly Dataset.

title: GCIP/LSA-NW 99 Surface: NCEP/CPC Daily Precipitation Data in QC format

This dataset was formed by extracting precipitation values with NCEP/CPC element codes of PC and PP that fall on the hour.  All raw precipitation data, including data that do not fall on the hour, can be found in the GCIP/EOP Surface: Precipitation NCEP/CPC Gage Only Daily Dataset.

title: ACE-ASIA Aircraft: Twin Otter DMA size distributions (Wang)
summary: This data set contains DMA size distribution data measured aboard 19 Twin Otter flights during ACE-Asia in April, 2001 in text matrix format.

title: ACE-ASIA Aircraft: Twin Otter Aerosol Three Wavelength Nephelometer Data (Mader/Flagan/Seinfeld)
summary: Airborne measurements of particle light scattering coefficient were measured using the Twin Otter aircraft during ACE-Asia. Measurements were made using a Model 3563 TSI three-wavelength nephelometer located onboard a modified De Havillan DHC-6 Twin Otter aircraft operated by the Center for Interdisciplinary Remotely Piloted Aircraft Studies (CIRPAS). A total of 19 Research Flights were conducted between March 31 and May 1, 2001.  The files are in .txt format.

title: ACE-ASIA Aircraft: Twin Otter Aerosol Particle Soot Photometer Data (Mader/Flagan/Seinfeld)

Measurements were made using a Particle Soot Absorption Photometer (Radiance Research, Seattle WA) located onboard a modified De Havillan DHC-6 Twin Otter aircraft operated by the Center for Interdisciplinary Remotely Piloted Aircraft Studies (CIRPAS). A total of 19 Research Flights were conducted between March 31 and May 1, 2001.  The files are in .txt format.

title: ACE-ASIA Aircraft: Twin Otter Aerosol OCEC (Mader/Flagan/Seinfeld)
summary: Airborne levels of carboneous aerosols were measured using the Twin Otter aircraft during ACE-Asia. Samples were collected onboard a modified De Havillan DHC-6 Twin Otter aircraft operated by the Center for Interdisciplinary Remotely Piloted Aircraft Studies (CIRPAS). A total of 19 Research Flights were conducted between March 31 and May 1, 2001.  This dataset contains one .txt file and one .GIF file.

title: COMET Case Study 042: Complete Dataset
summary: On 28th Jan. 2002, an Artic Front surged south across Kansas, leaving a shallow layer of sub-freezing air in it's wake. Meanwhile, an 850mb low was positioned over New Mexico. As the 850mb low moved east across New Mexico on the 29th and 30th, much warmer, moisture-laden air was transported north across the southern plains in a layer approximately 3,000 feet thick, trapping the sub-freezing layer beneath. On the evening of the 30th, the 850mb low crossed the New Mexico/ Texas border. A mid-upper level trough moving east across the southern Rockies provided sufficient lift across the region. Widespread freezing rain and sleet developed late in the afternoon of the 29th across south-central Kansas and continued through the night of the 30th, eventually changing to snow early on the morning of the 31th. The result was a a major ice accumulation of 1-2 inches on trees and power lines across south-central Kansas that severed power to much of the area.
archive_note: This CD set was not found in the EOL physical data archive.

summary: This dataset contains measurements of aerosol light scattering and backscattering as a function of relative humidity (RH) for RH between ~40 and 85%. title: GCIP/LSA-NW 99 Surface: Montana's RWIS Miscellaneous Precipitation

The GCIP LSA-NW EAOP-99 domain is approximately 90W to 115W longitude and 36N to 51N latitude.

title: COMET Case Study 043: Complete Dataset
summary: The 137,760-acre Hayman Fire transported massive amounts of heat, dust and moisture into the sky southwest of Denver. The towering smoke plume from this fire spawned nighttime thunderstorms across the Great Plains. On the night of Monday, June 10th, southwesterly winds drove the smoke and the clouds into northeastern Colorado, where showers and golf ball-sized hail were reported in Washington County near Akron. The next night, Tuesday, June 11th, west winds pushed the clouds east into Kansas, where violent weather erupted and two small tornadoes were triggered in south- central Kansas.

title: COMET Case Study 044: Complete Dataset
summary: A major outbreak of severe weather and tornadoes occured acrooss the Tennessee and Ohio valley region on the 10th- 11th, producing damage in 13 states, from the Gulf Coast to western Pennsylvania. A total of 75 tornadoes touched down on the 10th, resulting in at least 36 deaths. A tornado rated as F-4 on the Fujita Scale struck Van Wert county in Ohio. In Tennessee, the community of Mossy Grove was nearly destroyed by a mile-wide tornado that claimed 12 lives. This is the worst in November in a decade, caused by an unseasonably strong upper jet stream, as a result it drives the cold sir down from Canada, and lifts the warm moist air from the south with extra energy. A collision between a big pre-winter gush of frigid air and an unusually broad reservoir of residual tropical warmth and moisture flowing from the Gulf of Mexico triggers violent storms along a thousand mile front from Gulf Coast to Pennsylvania.

title: GCIP/LSA-NW 00 Ancillary Station List
summary: The GEWEX Continental-Scale International Project (GCIP) Large Scale Area-Northwest (LSA-NW) Enhanced Annual Observing Period (EAOP) 2000 datasets contain data collected from over ten thousand stations in the GCIP LSA-NW EAOP 2000 domain (i.e., 36N to 51N latitude and 90W to 115W longitude) for the period 01 April 2000 through 31 March 2001. The station information provided defines each station in the GCIP LSA-NW EAOP 2000 datasets with station location, name, frequency of observation, etc. For a complete description of the station information file format, refer to section 2.1.

title: GCIP/LSA-NW 00 Hydrology: USGS Streamflow
summary: The United States Geological Survey (USGS) stream flow dataset is one of various datasets provided for the GEWEX Continental-Scale International Project (GCIP) Large Scale Area-North West (LSA-NW) Enhanced Annual Observing Period (EAOP) 2000. This dataset contains stream flow data from USGS stations in the GCIP LSA-NW EAOP-00 domain for the time period (01 April 2000 through 30 September 2000) for approximately 1700 stations. The GCIP LSA-NW EAOP-00 domain is approximately 90W to 115W longitude and 36N to 51N latitude. Data are not currently available for 1 October 2000 through 31 March 2001, but will be at a later date.  No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: COMET CASE 044 GOES-8 IR .gif imagery
summary: This dataset contains GOES-8 IR imagery. Data is archived  as GIF files.

title: ACE-ASIA Surface: China Zhenbeitai Aerosol scattering and absorption (Bergin)
summary: This data set includes the aerosol light scattering coefficient, Bap, at 565nm of PM2.5 measured from Yulin, China.  Also included are measurements of the Bsp of total aerosols as well ambient meteorological conditions.

title: ACE-ASIA Surface: China Zhenbeitai Aerosol PAR (Bergin)
summary: This data set includes the Photosynthetically Active Radiation (400 - 700 nm) (PAR) measured from Yulin, China.

title: ACE-ASIA Surface: China Zhenbeitai Aerosol Optical Depth (Bergin)
summary: This data set includes the spectral aerosol optical depth (AOT) measured in clear-sky conditions from Yulin, China with a handheld sun photometer at wavelengths of 380nm, 440nm, 500nm, 675nm, and 870nm.

title: ACE-ASIA Aircraft: King Air Flight Line Data (Uchiyama, MRI and Jensen, CSIRO)
summary: This data set includes meteorology, CAPS, PMS, CN, LWC, radiation, SST and S02 data collected onboard the King Air aircraft participating in the ACE-Asia experiment.

title: GCIP/EOP Hydrology: USGS Stream Flow Data
summary: This dataset contains daily observations of stream flow from the United States Geological Survey (USGS) and selected United States Army Corps of Engineers gages. NOTE - the streamflow data are generally not adjusted for diversions or reservoir storage.

title: ACE-ASIA Surface: Zhenbeitai, PRC Aerosol Particle Samples (Arimoto)
summary: This dataset contains the result of elemental and major ion analyses of aerosol samples collected at the ACE-Asia ground station located in Zhenbeitai, China. A modified IMPROVE-type, low volume sampler was used at the Zhenbeitai station.

title: ACE-ASIA Aircraft: King Air Flight Line Data (Uchiyama, MRI and Jensen, CSIRO)
summary: This data set includes meteorology, CAPS, PMS, CN, LWC, radiation, SST and S02 data collected onboard the King Air aircraft participating in the ACE-Asia experiment. These are the original CD-ROMs provided by Jorgen Jensen, and these are not to be given out. For in house use only. Users should be directed to 69.164.

title: GCIP/EOP Sub-Surface: OKMESO Soil Moisture (1999 OCS Version 3.0)
summary: This dataset is no longer available. The data has been transferred to storm ID 21.037, and this ID remains only to link to the order history. This dataset contains the GCIP/EOP Oklahoma Mesonet 30-Minute Soil Moisture Data for 1999. It contains estimates of volumetric water content, which is a derived quantity. A full explanation of the algorithms used and the processing applied is in a document in PDF format which will be delivered along with the data. The detailed station list will be delivered along with the data, too. This dataset is provided "as is" and was not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS. This dataset is password protected. For password information, please see the contact for this dataset.

title: GCIP/GREDS Observational Data CD-ROM
summary: The data sets on this compact disc are a compilation of several geographic reference data sets of interest to the global-change research community. The data sets were chosen with input from the Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment (GEWEX) Continental-Scale International Project (GCIP) Data Committee and the GCIP Hydrometeorology and Atmospheric Subpanels. (NOTE: A README.TXT file exists in each directory, and provides an overview of the contents of the files or subdirectories in the directory)

title: ACE-1: Data Sets CD-ROM (Aerosol Characterization Experiments)
summary: The ACE-1 CD-ROM set consists of two CD-ROMs which contain data including chemistry and in situ data, soundings, amd several types of imagery collected from the C-130, the Research Vessel Discoverer, the Southern Surveyor, Cape Grim, Macquarie Island, and other surface sites. For each dataset, the data and associated documentation are both located in the same directory. In each directory, files with the ".htm" suffix have been included that allow the user to peruse the ACE-1 CD-ROMs with any web browser.

title: ACE-ASIA Surface: Jeju(Cheju)_Mtn Aerosol Single Particle Mass Spectrometer (Zelenyuh/Imre)
summary: This dataset contains a single zipped text file.  Each line contains an individual particle's information: timestamp, particle aerodynamic diameter and mass spectrum for 830,000 particles analyzed during the period 04/12/2001 to 04/28/2001.

title: NOAA/ATDD Fort Peck, Montana Flux Site
summary: The NOAA/ATDD (Tilden Meyers) started operation of a long term flux monitoring site in Fort Peck, Montana in November 1999.  Half-hourly observations of wind speed and direction, air temperature, relative humidity, pressure, incoming global radiation, incoming and outgoing visible radiation, net radiation, ground heat flux, precipitation, wetness, skin temperature, soil temperature (at 2, 4, 8, 16, 32 and 64 cm), average wind vector speed, kinematic shear stress, streamwise velocity variance, crosswind velocity variance, vertical velocity variance, sensible heat flux, latent energy flux, CO2 flux and soil moisture at 15, 30, and 60 cm. For further information on this data set see the README file.
