summary: This is a link to Radarsat Quick-look imagery for SHEBA.

title: NWS Cooperative Observer Daily Observations [NCDC]
summary: This dataset contains the original National Climatic Data Center (NCDC) Summary of the Day Co-operative (COOP) data for the NAME Tier 3 domain. The observations in this dataset are primarily those from the cooperative network, augmented by observations from principal observing stations operated by the NWS and other sites having highly trained observers. Quality Control for this data was provided by NCDC.

title: Gridded Daily Precipitation from CPC
summary: This data set contains daily gridded precipitation covering the region from 20 N to 60 N latitude and  60 W to 150 W longitude. From April 07, 1997 to  March 03, 1998, the resolution of the data is  1 degree longitude by 1 degree latitude. Since March 04, 1998, the analysis's resolution is 0.25 degree longitude by 0.25 degree latitude. The data set  contains data for the period April 07, 1998 thru  May 31, 1999, However data is missing for the period January 01, 1998 thru March 03,1998. This data can be  displayed using the GrADS software package. An example control file needed to display the data in GrADS is included in the README. Consult the README for more details.

title: WHOI Meteorological and Air-Sea Flux CD-ROM
summary: This data set contains surface meteorological and air sea flux data from the surface mooring component of the NOAA Pan American Climate Study (PACS).  Data are from two sites in the eastern tropical Pacific covering the time period April 1997 to September 1998.   This is a preliminary release of the dataset.  Please use with caution and report any errors.  Please do not post and distribute this dataset on the internet.  A complete description of the data collection and analysis is given in the PACS data report provided with the CD-ROM.

title: Central American Station List
summary: This dataset contains a list of stations whose data are included in the PACS Central American data sets.  This list includes station name, latitude, longitude, elevation, station type, observing network ID, and station id.

title: Brazilian Daily Precipitation
summary: This data set contains gridded daily precipitation data from across Brazil in binary format. This data can be displayed using the GrADS software. The Brazilian Daily Precipitation data was provided by the following institutions: CMCD/INPE, CPTEC/INPE, ANEEL, and INMET. The data cover the time period January 1, 1960 to December 31, 1997.

title: PACS QC Radiosonde Data
summary: This data set consists of soundings from Santa Cruz, Bolivia.These data were processed through automated quality control. The dataset includes pressure, temperature, humidity, winds and altitude taken at 5 seconds vertical resolution.

title: Gridded GOES West 9 Data
summary: This data set contains gridded GOES West Satellite data covering the region from 25 S to 45 N latitude and  180 W to 90 W longitude. The dataset contains data for the period June 02, 1997 to December 26, 1999. The gridded GOES data has been binned into a 0.1 degree longitude by 0.1 degree latitude grid.

title: Gridded GOES West 10 Data
summary: This data set contains gridded GOES West Satellite data covering the region from 25 S to 45 N latitude and  180 W to 90 W longitude. The dataset contains data for the period June 02, 1997 to December 26, 1999. The gridded GOES data has been binned into a 0.1 degree longitude by 0.1 degree latitude grid.

title: DMSP SSM/I Integrated Water Vapor Products data
summary:
Gridded data of retrieved column-integrated water vapor (g/m2) computed using a Schlussel algorithm, and with a spatial resolution of 0.25 x 0.25 degrees.
Data are from SSM/I instruments on multiple platforms, presently F11, F13, and F14.
Data has been gridded on a rectangular grid.

title: DMSP SSM/I Rainfall Rate Products data
summary:
Gridded data of retrieved rainfall rate (mm/hr) computed using a Ferriday algorithm, and with a spatial resolution of 0.25 x 0.25 degrees.
Data are from SSM/I instruments on multiple platforms, presently F11, F13, and F14.
Data has been gridded on a rectangular grid.

title: DMSP SSM/I Pentad and Monthly Averages
summary: Gridded data (and GIFs) of five-day and monthly averages of rainfall, cloud liquid water and integrated water vapor are produced from all available satellites (including F10, F11, F13 and F14). The data are gridded into 0.5 x 0.5 degree latitude / longitude extending from 60N to 60S.

title: GOES-West Infrared gridded data
summary:
Gridded files of 11 micron (longwave) infrared window channel.
Radiance values are gridded on a spatial resolution of 0.1 x 0.1 degrees.
Images are at 0000 UTC.

title: GOES-West Visible gridded data
summary:
Gridded files of the 0.52-0.72 micron visible channel.
Radiance values have a spatial resolution of 0.1 x 0.1 degrees.
Images are at 0000 UTC.

title: GOES-West Water Vapor gridded data
summary:
Gridded files of (upper-level) water vapor 6.7 micron channel.
Radiance values have a spatial resolution of 0.1 x 0.1 degrees.
Images are at 0000 UTC.

title: DMSP SSM/I Monthly Averages Cloud Liquid Water (Gif)
summary: Gif images of gridded monthly averages of cloud liquid water from all available satellites (including F10, F11, F13 and F14). The data are gridded into 0.5 x 0.5 degree latitude / longitude extending from 60N to 60S.

title: DMSP SSM/I Monthly Averages Integr Water Vapor (Gif)
summary: Gif images of gridded monthly averages of integrated water vapor from all available satellites (including F10, F11, F13 and F14). The data are gridded into 0.5 x 0.5 degree latitude / longitude extending from 60N to 60S.

title: DMSP SSM/I Monthly Averages Retrieved Rainfall(Gif)
summary: Gif images of gridded monthly averages retrieved rainfall from all available satellites (including F10, F11, F13 and F14). The data are gridded into 0.5 x 0.5 degree latitude / longitude extending from 60N to 60S.

title: DMSP SSM/I Pentad Averages Cloud Liquid Water (Gif)
summary: Gif images of gridded pentad average of cloud liquid water from all available satellites (including F10, F11, F13 and F14). The data are gridded into 0.5 x 0.5 degree latitude / longitude extending from 60N to 60S.

title: DMSP SSM/I Pentad Average Integr Water Vapor (Gif)
summary: Gif images of gridded pentad averages of integrated water vapor from all available satellites (including F10, F11, F13 and F14). The data are gridded into 0.5 x 0.5 degree latitude / longitude extending from 60N to 60S.

title: DMSP SSM/I Pentad Averages Retrieved Rainfall (Gif)
summary: Gif images of gridded pentad average of retrieved rainfall from available satellites (including F10, F11, F13 and F14). The data are gridded into 0.5 x 0.5 degree latitude / longitude extending from 60N to 60S.

title: NCEP/CPC Mexico Unified Daily Precipitation Data (1989-1999)
summary: This data set contains combined daily precipitation data from across Mexico from the CPC and JOSS datasets. Data for both the CPC and JOSS datasets were kindly provided by Art Douglas (Creighton Univ.) The data cover the time period January 1991 to April 1999.

title: NCEP/CPC Mexico Unified Daily Precipitation Station List
summary: This dataset contains a list of stations whose data are included in the PACS Mexican data sets.  This list includes station name, latitude, longitude, elevation, station type, observing network ID, and station id.

title: Diego Garcia Meteorology Surface Observations
summary: This data set contains the Diego Garcia Meteorology Surface Observations. No additional quality control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: GTS Rawinsonde Constant Pressure Plots (GIFS)
summary: This data set contains the GTS Rawinsonde Constant Pressure Plots. No additional quality control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: GTS Rawinsonde Observations
summary: This dataset consists of sounding data that were collected from the global network of regular reporting stations. This data represents mandatory and significant levels only. The data was contained in daily files which are in GEMPAK format.  No additional quality control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: GTS Surface Hourly Observations
summary: This dataset contains the global hourly surface observations for each day. These data are contained in daily files which are in GEMPAK format. No additional quality control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: GTS Surface Ship Observations
summary: This dataset contains the GTS Surface Ship Observations data. These data are contained in daily files which are in GEMPAK format. No additional quality control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: GTS Surface Synoptic Observations
summary: This dataset contains the GTS Surface Synoptic Observations data. This data is contained in daily files which are in GEMPAK format. No additional quality control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: Diego Garcia Meteorology Daily Tropical Outlook (GIFS)
summary: This data set contains the Diego Garcia Meteorology Daily Tropical Outlook GIF Imagery.

title: Diego Garcia Meteorology Daily Operations Area Forecast
summary: This data set contains the Diego Garcia Meteorology Daily Operations Area Forecasts.

title: POES NOAA AVHRR and TOVS
summary: This dataset contains the POES NOAA AVHRR and TOVS satellitedata.

title: Meteosat-5
summary: This dataset contains the Meteosat-5 satellite data.

title: POES NOAA AVHRR (JPEGs)
summary: This dataset contains the POES NOAA AVHRR (JPEGs) satellite imagery.

title: POES NOAA SST (JPEGs)
summary: This data set contains the POES NOAA Sea Surface Temperature SST satellite imagery. No additional quality control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: Meteosat-5 (JPEGs)
summary: This data set contains the Meteosat-5 IR, visible, and water vapor satellite imagery. Please be aware that there are no images for the time period between 1999/01/02 and 1999/01/20.  No additional quality control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: ECMWF Regional Streamline Analysis
summary: This dataset contains the Model ECMWF Regional Streamline GIFs for the INDOEX project.

title: NOGAPS Global Grids (GRIB)
summary: This dataset contains the model NOGAPS global grids data in GRIB format collected during the INDOEX time period.

title: NOGAPS Global Grids (GEMPAK)
summary: This dataset contains the model NOGAPS global grids data in GEMPAK format collected during the INDOEX time period.

title: NSF C-130 Aerosol Particle Size Distribution [Clarke]
summary: This data set contains aerosol particle size data obtained with an optical particle counter (OPC) aboard the NCAR C-130Q aircraft. No additional quality control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: Ron Brown Meteorology Rawinsonde Soundings [Dickerson]
summary: This dataset consists of rawinsonde data collected during  the INDOEX cruise of the NOAA Ship Ron Brown. Each datafile contains the ships location, the sonde's UTC release time, and a vertical profile of pressure, temperature, humidity,  latitude and longitude, total wind speed and direction,  and U and V wind components, every 10 seconds during the  sonde's ascent.

title: FSU Trajectories, Backward (GIFs)
summary: This dataset contains the Model FSU Backward Trajectory GIF imagery for the INDOEX project.

title: FSU Trajectories, Forward (GIFs)
summary: This dataset contains the Model FSU Forward Trajectory GIF imagery for the INDOEX project.

title: NOGAPS Regional Grids (GIFs)
summary: This dataset contains the Model NOGAPS Regional Grids GIF imagery for the INDOEX project.

title: AVN Analysis Regional Grids (GIFs)
summary: This dataset contains the model AVN analysis regional grids imagery collected during the INDOEX time period.

title: Diego Garcia Rawinsonde Mandatory/Significant Level Profiles
summary: This data set contains the Diego Garcia Rawinsonde Profiles. No additional quality control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: Upper Air - Leon High Resolution Soundings
summary: This data set consists of CLASS soundings taken at Leon, Kansas for the CASES-99 program. The site was operated by the National Center for Atmospheric Research/Atmospheric Technology Division (NCAR/ATD). UCAR/JOSS has not changed these soundings in any way. This data set includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude. Refer to the README file for details.

title: Upper Air - Beaumont High Resolution Soundings
summary: This data set consists of CLASS soundings taken at Beaumont, Kansas for the CASES-99 program. The site was operated by the National Center for Atmospheric Research/Atmospheric Technology Division (NCAR/ATD). UCAR/JOSS has not changed these soundings in any way. This data set includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude. Refer to the README file for details.

title: Upper Air - Eldorado High Resolution Soundings
summary: This data set consists of CLASS soundings taken at Eldorado, Kansas for the CASES-99 program. The site was operated by the National Center for Atmospheric Research/Atmospheric Technology Division (NCAR/ATD). UCAR/JOSS has not changed these soundings in any way. This data set includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude. Refer to the README file for details.

title: Upper Air - Smileyberg High Resolution Soundings
summary: This data set consists of CLASS soundings taken at Smileyberg, Kansas for the CASES-99 program. The site was operated by the National Center for Atmospheric Research/Atmospheric Technology Division (NCAR/ATD). UCAR/JOSS has not changed these soundings in any way. This data set includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude. Refer to the README file for details.

title: Satellite - GOES-8 McIDAS Area File Data
summary: This dataset contains GOES-8 Imagery of the CASES-99 area and midwestern US. These data are in McIDAS AREA file format. Data was collected for VIS, IR and Water Vapor channels on approximately half-hour intervals during the project.

title: Satellite - NOAA 14, 15 Level 1b Data Files
summary: This dataset contains polar-orbiter passes of the midwest US region by NOAA 14 and 15 satellites. This data was collected by Marv Wesley and his group at Argonne National Laboratory. The data is in NOAA Level 1B format.

title: High Plains Climate Network Data in QC Format
summary: This dataset contains hourly surface observations from the High Plains Climate Network. A total of 94 stations reported within the CASES-99 domain. No additional quality control was performed on this dataset by UCAR/JOSS.

title: Composite Radar Imagery (GIF)
summary: This dataset contains images generated from the the WSI NIDS 2 km national radar mosaic for the GCIP/EOP period. One image per day is loaded with a 48 hour delay.  These data are provided for data browsing purposes.

title: High Plains Climate Network Data
summary: This data set contains hourly resolution surface meteorological data from the High Plains Climate Network (HPCN).  The HPCN includes data from a number of state agricultural networks in the High Plains region (a total of 136 stations). Times are reported in local standard time, and offsets to UTC are in section 2.2, with other station information. This data set covers the period from 1 January 2001 to March 2003. The data are in columnar ASCII format.

title: NOAA P-3 Meteorology Navigation and State Parameters - Standard Tape Format [NOAA/AOC]
summary: The EPIC Aircraft: P-3 Meteorology Navigation and State Parameters dataset in NOAA/AOC Standard Tape format is one of several datasets archived by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS) in support of the Eastern Pacific Investigation of Climate (EPIC) project.  The data were collected by the National Oceanic and Atmospherc Administration Aircraft Operations Center P-3 aircraft (NOAA/AOC).

title: POES NOAA Composite SST Imagery [NESDIS]
summary: This dataset is a collection of Sea Surface Temperature images taken by the POES Satellite for the EPIC project.

title: QuikSCAT SeaWinds Imagery [OSU]
summary: The dataset contains EPIC 2001 satellite QuikSCAT imagery in GIF format from 06 Aug to 14 Nov 2001.

title: Galapagos Meteorology Rawinsondes (hi-res) [Esbensen]
summary: This Dataset consists of rawinsonde data collected from Galapagos during EPIC. Each datafile contains the sonde's UTC release time, and a vertical profile of pressure, temperature, humidity,  latitude and longitude, total wind speed and direction,  and U and V wind components, every 10 seconds during the  sonde's ascent.

title: NCEP AVN Analysis Charts (Streamline/Isotachs)
summary: This dataset consists of 00 UTC and 12 UTC NCEP Aviation (AVN) model analysis of the streamlines/isotachs at 850 and 200mb.

title: New Mexico Monitored Climate Station Network Data [NMSU]
summary: This data set contains hourly resolution surface meteorological data from the New Mexico Monitored Climate Station Network.  These stations are located across the state of New Mexico.  This data set covers the period from 1 May to 30 June 2002 and includes 20 stations.  The data are in columnar ASCII format.

title: Mobile Data [Purdue University]
summary: This dataset contains raw GPS data collected by Purdue University.  GPS readings were taken from various stations from June 6 to June 12.  Included with the data is a readme in .pdf format with start and end times and approximate locations for each observation.

title: NWS Cooperative Observer Daily Observations [NCDC]
summary: This dataset contains the National Climatic Data Center (NCDC) Summary of the Day Co-operative (COOP) data for the IHOP_2002 domain. The observations in this dataset are primarily those from the cooperative network, augmented by observations from principal observing stations operated by the NWS and other sites having highly trained observers. Quality Control for this data was provided by NCDC.

title: NWS Cooperative Observer 15-min Precipitation Data [NCDC]
summary: This dataset contains 15 minute precipitation data from the National Climatic Data Center (NCDC) Cooperative (COOP) data for the IHOP_2002 domain. The observations in this dataset are primarily those from the cooperative network, augmented by observations from principal observing stations operated by the NWS and other sites having highly trained observers. Quality Control for this data was provided by NCDC.

title: NWS Cooperative Observer 60-min Precipitation Data [NCDC]
summary: This dataset contains 60 minute precipitation data from the National Climatic Data Center (NCDC) Cooperative (COOP) data for the IHOP_2002 domain. The observations in this dataset are primarily those from the cooperative network, augmented by observations from principal observing stations operated by the NWS and other sites having highly trained observers. Quality Control for this data was provided by NCDC.

title: Falcon H20 DIAL Imagery [DLR]
summary: This dataset includes H20 DIAL Imagery of measurements taken from the Falcon aircraft during the IHOP_2002 project.  The dataset includes Atmospheric Backscatter plots and Water Vapor Mixing Ratio plots.  Images are available for days 2002-05-24, 2002-05-25, 2002-05-29 and 2002-06-09.  Tables of time intervals are also available for 2002-05-29 and 2002-06-09.

title: Rawinsonde West Texas Mesonet SkewT Imagery (Lubbock) [Texas Tech]
summary: This dataset contains Rawinsonde West Texas Mesonet SkewT Imagery from Texas Tech.

title: Falcon H20 DIAL Data [DLR]
summary: This dataset contains H20 and ABS (Atmospheric Backscatter) data in ascii format from the Falcon flight missions during the IHOP_2002 field project.  Data is available for 2002-05-24, 2002-05-25, 2002-05-29 and 2002-06-09.  Tables of time intervals for each Leg are also available for 2002-05-29 and 2002-06-09.

title: Texas West Texas Mesonet Data [Texas Tech]
summary: This data set contains 5-minute resolution surface meteorological data from the West Texas Mesonet operated by Texas Tech.  The West Texas Mesonet includes 31 stations in the region around Lubbock, Texas.  This data set covers the period from 1 May to 30 June 2002.  The data are in comma-delimited ASCII format.

title: Falcon Navigation and State Parameter Data [DLR]
summary: This data set contains Falcon Navigation Data for the IHOP region.  This data set covers the period from 17 May to 15 June 2002.  The data are in ASCII format.

title: Falcon HRDL Data [NOAA/ETL]
summary: This dataset contains vertical velocity data, horizontal velocity data, and select water vapor flux data from the Falcon flight missions during the IHOP_2002 field project.  Data are available for 2002-06-02, 2002-06-03, 2002-06-06, 2002-06-07, 02002-06-09, and 2002-06-14.

title: Airborne Lidar-Derived Boundary Layer Depth Data [PSU]
summary:
This dataset contains PBL depths retrieved from airborne lidar backscatter data collected during the IHOP experiment, 13 May to 25 June 2002. The data are in ASCII format. Data are available from IHOP missions flown on the the following days:

May 19,20,21,25,27,28,29,30,31
June 03,06,07,09,14,16,25.

title: P-3 CNRS Leandre II Data [CNRS]
summary: This dataset contains CNRS Leandre II data recorded during P-3 flights. The LEANDRE II Water Vapor DIAL system aboard the NRL P-3 was operated during the International H20 Project (IHOP_2002) field experiment from May 19th through June 25th 2002. This dataset contains data from May 22nd through June 19th 2002.

title: High Plains Climate Network Data
summary: This data set contains hourly resolution surface meteorological data from the High Plains Climate Network (HPCN).  The HPCN includes data from a number of state agricultural networks in the High Plains region (a total of 136 stations). Times are reported in local standard time, and offsets to UTC are in section 2.2, with other station information. This data set covers the period from 1 June 2002 to July 2002. The data are in columnar ASCII format.

title: Automated Weather Observing System (AWOS) Iowa 1-min Data
summary: This data set contains 1 minute resolution surface meteorological data from the Automated Weather Observing System (AWOS) in Iowa. This data set covers the period from 1 June 2002 through 31 July 2002.

title: NWS Cooperative Observer Daily Observation Data
summary: This data set contains daily observations of precipitation, maximum and minimum temperature, as well as other parameters from the National Weather Service Cooperative Network.  These stations are located across the SMEX02 region.  This data set covers the period from 1 June to 31 July 2002.

title: NWS Cooperative Observer Hourly Precipitation Data
summary: This data set contains hourly resolution precipitation data from the National Weather Service Cooperative Network.  These stations are located across the SMEX02 region.  This data set covers the period from 1 June to 31 July 2002.

title: NWS Cooperative Observer 15-Minute Precipitation Data
summary: This data set contains 15-minute resolution precipitation data from the National Weather Service Cooperative Network.  These stations are located across the SMEX02 region.  This data set covers the period from 1 June to 31 July 2002.

title: USDA/NRCS Soil Climate Analysis Network (SCAN) Data
summary: This data set contains hourly resolution surface meteorological and soils data from the United States Department of Agriculture Natural Resources Conservation Service (USDA/NRCS) Soil Climate Analysis Network (SCAN).  This data set includes data from the SCAN stations in the SMEX02 region for the period from 1 June to 31 July 2002.  The data are columnar ASCII format.

title: NWS Mandatory/Significant Level Radiosonde Data
summary: This data set contains hourly resolution radiosonde data.  The data are from WMO stations in the SMEX02 region for the period from 1 June to 31 July 2002.  The data are columnar ASCII format.

title: P-3 General Information, Mission Summaries
summary:
This dataset contains the summaries of the P-3 aircraft missions flown during SALLJEX. These HTML files contain details of each flight.

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055)

title: Meteorology Universidad de Chile MM5 Forecast Products

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: Meteorology CPTEC (Brazil) Forecast Products: Global 80 km

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

summary:
This dataset contains the AVN model GIF images generated during the SALLJEX field campaign. (These images are the same as found in the SALLJEX Field Catalog.)

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: Meteorology CIMA Universidad de Buenos Aires LAHM Forecast Products
summary:
This dataset contains the LAHN model GIF images generated during the SALLJEX field campaign. (These images are the same as found in the SALLJEX Field Catalog.)

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: Meteorology CPTEC (Brazil) Forecast Products: Eta 40 km
summary:
This dataset contains the CPTEC 40 km model GIF imagery generated during the SALLJEX field campaign. (These images are the same as found in the SALLJEX Field Catalog.)

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: Meteorology University of Maryland Forecast Products
summary:
This dataset contains the Forecast model output data (control and data files) for experiments 1 and 2 taken at the University of Maryland on January 17, 2003 as part of the South American Low Level Jet Experiment (SALLJEX).

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: Meteorology Universidad de So Paulo RAMS Forecast Products
summary:
This dataset contains the Forecast model output data (both control and data files) for experiments 1 and 2 run by the University of Sao Paulo for January 17, 2003 as part of the South American Low Level Jet Experiment (SALLJEX).

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: Dourados (Brazil) Surface Data
summary:
This data set contains surface data from the Dourados site during the South American Low Level Jet Experiment (SALLJEX) collection period. The data are will be delivered in both MS Excel Spreadsheet and comma separated value ASCII formats. The column headers of the spreadsheets are in Portuguese.

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: Rio Branco (Brazil) Surface Data
summary:
This data set contains surface data from the Rio Branco site during the South American Low Level Jet Experiment (SALLJEX) collection period. The data will be delivered in both MS Excel Spreadsheet and comma separated value ASCII formats. The column headers of the spreadsheet are in Portuguese.

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: Meteorology University of Utah Global Forecast Products (experiments 1,3,4)
summary:
This dataset contains the Forecast model output data (control and data files) for experiments 1, 3, and 4 taken at the University of Utah for January 17, 2003 as part of the South American Low Level Jet Experiment (SALLJEX). These contain 5 day forecast results, because the forecast sensitivity to SALLJEX observations grows slowly.

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: Meteorology Universidad de So Paulo MM5 Forecast Products (experiment 3)
summary:
This dataset contains the Forecast model output data (both control and data files) for experiment 3 run by the University of Sao Paulo for January 17, 2003 as part of the South American Low Level Jet Experiment (SALLJEX). Both coarse mesh and find mesh resolutions are included.

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: Meteorology CIMA Universidad de Buenos Aires RAMS Forecast Products (experiments 3,4)
summary:
This dataset contains the UBA-CIMA_rams Forecast model output data (both control and data files) for experiments 3 and 4 run by the Universidad de Bueno Aires for January 17, 2003 as part of the South American Low Level Jet Experiment (SALLJEX).

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: OKMESO Site Photos and Reports
summary: The Oklahoma Mesonet technicians completed Spring Pass 2001 in late June, Summer Pass 2001 in late September, and Fall Pass 2001 in late December.  All 114 stations were visited during a 3-month period, and general site maintenance and inspections were performed. Over 1500 site photos were taken to document the appearance of the stations before and after each technician's visit.  These CDs were created to organize the multitude of information gathered during each of these year 2001 Passes.  You will find links to a list of accomplishments from the Pass, site photos, the site visitation forms on which the technician listed his/her notes, and other findings from the site visit. This dataset is password protected. For password information, please see the contact for this dataset.

title: WMI Lear Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics Data [WMI]
summary: The data is from the missions for the WMI Learjet for the BAMEX 2003 project.

title: Texas West Texas Mesonet Data [Texas Tech]
summary: This data set contains 5-minute resolution surface meteorological data from the West Texas Mesonet operated by Texas Tech. The West Texas Mesonet includes 38 stations in the region around Lubbock, Texas. This data set covers the period from 1 May to 31 July 2003. The data are in comma-delimited ASCII format.

title: SPC BAMEX Forecast Discussion and Charts [SPC]
summary: These are the SPC BAMEX Forecast Discussion and Charts for June 9 to July 3, 2003.  The data includes both gif images of the BAMEX area and HTML files of the forecast discussions.

title: Wisconsin Automated Weather Observation Network (AWON)
summary: This data set contains hourly surface meteorological data from the Wisconsin Automated Weather Observation Network (AWON) stations located across Wisconsin. This data set covers the period from 15 May through 15 July 2003. The data are in ASCII format.

title: NWS Cooperative Observer Daily Observations [NCDC]
summary: This data set contains daily observations of precipitation, maximum and minimum temperature, as well as other parameters from the National Weather Service Cooperative Network

title: NWS Cooperative Observer 15-minute Precipitation Data [NCDC]
summary: This data set contains 15-minute resolution precipitation data from the National Weather Service Cooperative Network. These stations are located across the BAMEX region. This data set covers the period from 20 May to 7 July 2003

title: NWS Cooperative Observer Hourly Precipitation Data [NCDC]
summary: This data set contains hourly resolution precipitation data from the National Weather Service Cooperative Network. This data set covers the period from 20 May to 07 July 2003.

title: NOAA P-3 Radar Imagery (Lower Fuselage C-band) [AOC]
summary: This dataset contains the lower fuselage radar and the tail doppler radar images from some of the missions flown for BAMEX. The data are in both JPG and PDF format.

title: Station List
summary: This dataset contains station information for the Bow Echo and Mesoscale Convective Vortex Experiment (BAMEX 2003). The station information provided defines over 20,000 stations in the BAMEX domain and time period, including mesonet, precipitation, sonde, and hydrology stations. Note that some station types, such as radar and lidar, are not included. Refer to the documentation provided with the station data for information on those stations.

title: NWS Cooperative Observer 15-Minute Precipitation Data
summary: This data set contains 15-minute resolution precipitation data from the National Weather Service Cooperative Network.  These stations are located across the SMEX03 region.  This data set covers the period from 1 June to 31 July 2003

title: NWS Cooperative Observer Hourly Precipitation Data
summary: This data set contains hourly resolution precipitation data from the National Weather Service Cooperative Network.  These stations are located across the SMEX03 region.  This data set covers the period from 1 June to 31 July 2003.

title: GTS Surface Observation Plots (GIFS)
summary: This dataset consists of GIF plots produced every 6 hours, showing all reported hourly, synoptic, and ship reports in the Maldives and vicinity region. No additional quality control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: ECMWF Regional Grids
summary: This dataset contains the Model ECMWF Regional Grids GIFs for the INDOEX project.

summary: This dataset contains the backward model ECMWF trajectories data in GIF format collected during the INDOEX time period.

title: ECMWF Trajectories, Forward

summary: This dataset contains Berlinor data from the Boulder Workshop, 2001.

summary: This dataset contains ZEBRA generated composites of GOES-E satellite imagery and LF C-band radar imagery from the N42 and N43 aircraft.

title: NCAR/NSF C-130 Chemistry Peroxides Data [Heikes]
summary:
The gas phase peroxide data reported herein were obtained using the method described in Lee et al., J. Atmos. Ocean. Tech., 1995, flown on board the NCAR C-130 platform during the RICO, Rain in Cumulus over the Ocean, experiment between December 3, 2004, and January 27, 2005, based out of Antigua. Hydrogen peroxide is symbolically represented by H2O2. Methylhydroperoxide is symbolically given by CH3OOH. The measurements are given as molecular mixing ratios; molecules of specific gas per molecules of whole air times 1,000,000,000,000. or ppt-v. The partial pressure of a specific gas can be calculated by: P(H2O2) = MixingRatio(pptv) * P(air) /1,000,000,000,000.

The goal of RICO was a detailed understanding of rain formation in shallow warm" cumulus clouds

peroxides are directly related to particulate sulfate formation.

<li> Remove H2O2 data during noted periods of inlet condensation; primarily during initial decent after 1st high altitude circle at 5km and 1/2 way through first lower altitude circle.
<li> Corrected limit of detection of methylhydroperoxide (15 -> 30 ppt) and its estimated uncertainty

title: R/V Seward Johnson Rawinsonde Data [UNOLS]
summary: This is one of the upper air data sets developed for the Rain in Cumulus Over the Ocean (RICO) project. This data set includes the high vertical resolution (2 second) rawinsonde data from the Research Vessel (R/V) Seward Johnson. A total of 88 soundings were released from 31 December 2004 to 24 January 2005. Soundings were typically released four to six times per day.

title: OLD DATA! GCIP/EOP Sub-Surface: ARM SWATS Data (Preliminary)
summary: <font color=red>These data have been replaced by another dataset!</font> The Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment (GEWEX)  Continental-scale International Project (GCIP) Enhanced  Observing Period (EOP) Department of Energy (DOE)  Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great  Plains (SGP) Soil Water and Temperature System (SWATS) data set is provided as is" and was not quality controlled by  UCAR/JOSS.    The Soil Water and Temperature System is designed to  provide information about the temperature of the soil and  the status of water in the soil profile. Sensors installed  at various depths below the soil surface provide hourly  measurements of soil temperature and estimates of soil-waterpotential and volumetric water content. SWATS systems are  installed at 21 of the ARM/SGP/CART Extended Facilities  (EFs).   Please see the README file for more complete information."

title: OLD DATA! SGP97 Sub-Surface: OKMESO Soil Moisture (OCS ver 3.0)
summary: ****This data set is no longer available. The data has been transferred to storm ID 25.043, and this ID remains only to link to the order history.**** This data set contains the Oklahoma Mesonet 30-Minute Soil Moisture Data for 1998. It contains estimates of volumetric water content, which is a derived quantity. For password information, please see the contact for this dataset.

This data set contains the Oklahoma Mesonet 30-Minute Soil Moisture Data for 1998. It contains estimates of volumetric water content, which is a derived quantity. A full explanation of the algorithms used and the processing applied is provided in a document in PDF format which will be delivered along with the data order. title: SST and Tropical Cyclone Heat Potential Analysis Imagery [NOAA/AOML]
summary: This dataset contains daily Sea Surface Temperature (SST) and Tropical Cyclone Heat Potential Analysis Imagery from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) Atlantic Oceanographic and Meteorology Laboratory (AOML).

title: Mexico San Felipe, Baja California Meteorological Data [CICESE]
summary:
This dataset contains meteorological data from San Felipe, Baja California covering the time period May through October 2004.

This dataset was updated on 31 January, 2006.

title: VORTEX NSSL Mobile Mesonet Data
summary: 15 Mobile mesonets were in operation during the Verification of the Origins of Rotation in Tornadoes Experiment (VORTEX) for the development of very high spatial and temporal resolution meteorological measurements. Vehicles consist of an instrument mast, instruments and an archive/display. Data consists of pressure, temperature, humidity and wind speed/direction. Errors during movement have been minimized. A Global Positioning System is used to obtain time, location and backup heading information (while moving).

title: VORTEX-95 NSSL Mobile Mesonet Data
summary: 15 Mobile mesonets were in operation during VORTEX for the development of very high spatial and temporal resolution meteorological measurements.  Vehicles consist of an  instrument mast, instruments and an archive/display.  Data consists of pressure, temperature, humidity and wind speed/ direction.  Errors during movement have been minimized. A Global Positioning System is used to obtain time,  location and backup heading information (while moving).

title: ATLAS: 1998 Arctic Region Climate System Model (ARCSyM) (Lynch)
summary: atlas arcsym dummy dataset for testing

title: Station List
summary: The North American Monsoon Experiment (NAME) 2004 Data sets contain data collected from over 38000 stations in the NAME Tier 3 domain and time period. The station information provided defines each station in the NAME datasets with station location, name, frequency of observation, etc.

title: Mexican UNAM R/V El Puma Meteorological and Navigational Parameters
summary:
This dataset contains atmospheric measurements and data obtained during a cruise of the Research Vessel (R/V) El Puma - UNAM. in the Eastern Pacific. The measurements were part of the North American Monsoon Experiment (NAME). The cruise occurred from 4 August 2004 through 17 August 2004.

This dataset contains two types of data files. The COMPLETO_ST#.txt files contain meteorological data for the complete time period 4 August 2004 through 17 August 2004 for station ST#. The ST#.txt files contain data saved for each day for the station ST#. The ship's log file is in Excel format.

title: Mexican UNAM R/V El Puma Radiometer Data
summary:
This dataset was collected from a radiometer installed on a mast on the R/V El Puma - UNAM .
The datasets consist of 1 minute averages for 24 hour periods for 4 different wavelengths,  and a Q value of overall energy budget.  These data are stored in Excel files.

title: NOAA/ESRL/PSD NAME Supersite (Obispo) RASS Data
summary: This dataset contains RASS data from the NOAA/ESRL/PSD NAME Supersite (Obispo). This dataset consists of text files in columnar form, with header information in each file. Currently, there is no other documentation, since this information is included in the header of each file.

title: NOAA/ESRL/PSD NAME Supersite (Obispo) 449 MHz Profiler Data
summary: This dataset contains 449 MHz Profiler data from the NOAA/ESRL/PSD NAME Supersite (Obispo).  This dataset consists of text files in columnar format, with header information in each file.  This dataset only covers 6 August 2004 through 20 September 2004.  According to the data source,  all data prior to 6 August was bad and have been dropped from this dataset..    Also according to the data source, the header in each data file incorrectly indicates that these files contain Altair RASS data instead of 449 MHz Profiler data.

title: NOAA/ESRL/PSD NAME Supersite (Obispo) 915 MHz Profiler Data
summary: These data are 915 MHz  Profiler data. This dataset consists of  text files in columnar form, with header information in each file.

title: NOAA/ESRL/PSD NAME Supersite (Obispo) Meteorological Data
summary: This dataset contains the surface meteorological data collected from the Estacion Obispo Supersite for NAME.

title: NOAA/ESRL/PSD NAME Supersite (Obispo) Surface Disdrometer DSD Estimates (Realtime)
summary: This dataset contains the surface disdrometer data collected from the Estacion Obispo Supersite for NAME.

title: Mexican Navy SEMAR R/V Altair Ceilometer Data [NOAA/ESRL/PSD]
summary:
There are many different types of files included in this dataset.  The .zip files contain the raw data from the ceilometer in daily files.  This includes codes for cloud base heights, housekeeping information, 
and the profile of backscatter intensity. The .asc files are daily files of the cloud height information. The ceiliometer images are daily jpegs of time-ht cross sections of the backscatter and can be used as references to look at clouds on a daily basis.

The altair_leg1_report.pdf report applies only to Leg 1 of the NAME04 Altair cruise. No such report exists for leg2.

title: National Water Level Observation Network (NWLON) Meteorological Data
summary: This data set contains hourly resolution surface meteorological and oceanographic data from the National Water Level Observation Network(NWLON) which is operated by the National Ocean Service Center for Operational Oceanographic Products and Services (CO-OPS).  These data were retrieved from the National Data Buoy Center (NDBC).  This data set includes data from the 29 stations located along the coast of theGulf of Mexico and the southern US Atlantic coast.  This data set covers the period from 1 January to 31 December 2005.  The data are in space delimited ASCII format.  NCAR/EOL conducted no additional quality control on these data.

title: NDBC Buoy & Station Data
summary: National Buoy Data Center operates a network of 6 moored buoys and 8 coastal stations in the Florida area.  Data consist of temperature, barometric pressure, wind speed/ direction (3-10 m), sea surface temp and wave energy  spectra at 1 h intervals (every 0.5 h for two buoys).   Winds derived from 8 min averages (buoys) or 2 min averages (coastal).  Many stations include tide gages.

title: Tampa Bay Oceanography Project
summary: NOAA's National Ocean Service Tampa Bay Oceanography Project(TOP) data consist of: current (Doppler profiles), water level,water temperature and conductivity, wind speed/ direction, solar radiation, barometric pressure and relativehumidity (all 10 min, except water level is 6 min).

title: CaPE MIT Lincoln Laboratory FLOWS Mesont
summary: FAA-Lincoln Laboratory Operational Weather Studies (FLOWS) Mesonet data consist of temperature, relative humidity, barometric pressure, rainfall and wind speed/direction (100 ft) at  16 stations in the vicinity of the Orlando International Airport for CaPE.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim Meteorological Data (Hourly)
summary: This dataset contains routine continuous meteorological measurements at hourly intervals from the Australian Bureau of Meteorology (BoM) Cape Grim baseline monitoring station during ACE-1. These data consist of time, scalar and vector wind, temperature, relative humidity, barometric pressure, rainfall, absolute humidity, baseline statistics, and scalar and vector wind (50 m). Hourly statistics of these parameters are available off-line by request. This dataset was processed with limited quality control following the ACE-1 field phase.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim Meteorological Data (1-minute)
summary: This dataset consists of routine continuous meteorological measurements at one-minute resolution collected at the Australian Bureau of Meteorology (BoM) Cape Grim baseline monitoring station during ACE-1. These data consist of time, temperature, wet bulb depression, barometric pressure, baseline switch, wind direction and speed (10 and 50 m), temperature (50 m), and relative humidity (50 m). Minute statistics of these parameters are available off-line by request. This dataset was processed with no quality control following the ACE-1 field phase.

title: ACE-1: Macquarie Island Meteorological Data [10-minute]
summary: This dataset consists of routine continuous meteorological measurements at ten-minute resolution collected at the Australian Bureau of Meteorology (BoM) Macquarie Island station during ACE-1. This dataset was processed with no quality control following the ACE-1 field phase.

title: NCDC Surface Land Data, Hourly (TD3280)
summary: Wind direction/speed, ceiling height, visibility. dry bulb  temperature, wet bulb temperature, dew point temperature,   sea level and station pressure, cloud data, and present     weather.  Manual and automatic observations from about 300  NWS, FAA, Coast Guard, and DOD sites. (NCDC element format)

title: STORM-FEST Canadian Surface Land, Hourly
summary: The Canadian AES routinely collected data from an existing network of hourly observer stations.  Data consists of sky conditions, wind speed/direction, visibility, temperature  (dry/wet), dewpoint, current weather and sea level/station pressure. Canada by AES.

title: CaPE FAA LLWAS Data
summary: FAA Low Level Wind Shear Alert System (LLWAS) at Orlando  Airport provides wind shear and turbulence observations.  18 stations located  around the airport produce 30-sec  running averages of wind speed and direction (at 125 ft.)  every 10-sec.

title: NCDC Hourly Surface Land
summary: Wind direction/speed, ceiling height, visibility. dry bulb temperature, wet bulb temperature, dew point temperature, sea level and station pressure, cloud data, and present weather.  Manual and automatic observations from about 1200 NWS, FAA,  Coast Guard, and DOD sites.

title: NCDC First Order Summary, Daily (TD3210)
summary: A network of NWS first order and FAA stations over the United States measured temperature (max/min/mean), average relative humidity, average dewpoint, degree days, weather type, average/gust wind, 24 h precipitation, % sunshine, skycover, river height and average sea level/station pressure.

title: NCDC Cooperative Summary, Daily (E-BUFR)
summary: Daily maximum and minimum temperatures, precipitation,  snowfall, and snowdepth at about 2000 stations in the  midwest.  A few dozen stations also report evaporation and  a handful report soil temperatures.

title: NCDC Cooperative Summary, Daily (TD3200)
summary: Daily maximum and minimum temperatures, precipitation, snow-fall, and snowdepth at about 8000 stations in the continen- tal U.S.  About 100 stations also report evaporation and a  few dozen report soil temperatures.

title: STORM-FEST Canadian Daily Summary Obs
summary: Over 3000 volunteer observer stations across Canada provide daily observations of maximum/minimum temperature, snowfall,snow depth and total precipitation.  A few sites also reportevaporation and ground state.

title: NCDC Precipitation, 15-Minute (E-BUFR)
summary: 15-minute precipitation from stations in the U.S. with      Fischer-Porter or Universal rain gauges.  (E-BUFR format)

title: NCDC Precipitation, 15-Minute (TD3260)
summary: 15-minute precipitation from about 3000 stations in the     U.S. with Fischer-Porter or Universal rain gauges.          (NCDC Element format)

title: NCDC Precipitation, Hourly (E-BUFR)
summary: Hourly precipitation from stations in the U.S.. (E-BUFR     format).

title: NCDC Precipitation, Hourly (TD3240)
summary: Hourly precipitation from about 5000 stations across the    continental U.S. (NCDC Element format)

title: NCDC Charts of Observed Snow-cover
summary: Prepared automatically at NMC based on the 12 UTC surface observations and archived at NCDC on 35 mm microfilm.  The total snow depth and 6 hour increase are plotted to the  nearest whole inch.  Trace amounts are also plotted.

title: CaPE Surface Energy Budget Data
summary: Special 7 station surface energy budget network data consistof surface energy fluxes using the Bowen ratio method (5 stn) or the eddy correlation method (2 stn).  Also, each station measured wind speed/direction (5 stn), temperature, relative humidity and precipitation.  Data averaging intervals varied from 6 - 15 min depending upon the instrumentation.  Manual daily gravimetric soil moisture measurements were made when possible.

title: Oklahoma Mesonet
summary: This dataset covers the state of Oklahoma (30 km spacing) and generates reports every 5-min. The instruments are identical to those used in the mobile mesonets. Data consists of pressure, temperature, relative humidity, and wind speed/direction that are polled every 3 sec and are reported as 5-min averages. Additionately, tipping bucket raingauges (0.25 mm), insolation, and soil temperature were measured at each site.

title: CaPE TRMM Raingage Data
summary: The NASA/GSFC Tropical Rainfall Measuring Mission (TRMM) Program data consist of precipitation data from 22 tipping bucket raingage locations in the Cape Canaveral area. Data are 1 min averages.

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: SURFRAD Radiation Data
summary: NOAA/ARL/SRRB operates a network of 4 Surface  Radiation sites in the U.S.  Data are available via anonymous ftp.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim Radon Measurements (Whittlestone)
summary: This dataset consists of continuous measurements of radon (222) taken at Cape Grim by Stewart Whittlestone (ANSTO).  The data contain 30-min integrated measurements of radon in mBq m-3 and time at the start of each measurement period. Instrument resolution time was 45 minutes.  This dataset was processed and quality-controlled following ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Meterological and Chemical Measurements [1-minute] (Johnson)
summary: This dataset consists of continuous meteorological and chemistry measurements taken aboard the R/V Discoverer by Jim Johnson and Tim Bates (NOAA/PMEL). This dataset consists of time, wind speed and direction (relative to the ship only), ultrafine condensation nuclei (> 3 nm), precipitation, and solar radiation measurements. The dataset contains 1-min averages of these parameters. This dataset was processed and quality controlled following the ACE-1 field phase.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Meterological and Chemical Measurements [30-minute] (Johnson)
summary: This dataset consists of continuous meteorological and chemisty measurements taken aboard the R/V Discoverer by Jim Johnson and Tim Bates (NOAA/PMEL).  These data consist of time, ship location, air temperature and humidity, wind speed and direction (true and relative), barometric pressure, rainfall, solar radiation, ultrafine condensation nuclei (> 3 nm), and radon. The data contain 30-min averages of these parameters. This dataset was processed and quality controlled following the ACE-1 field phase.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Seawater and Chemisty Measurements [30-minute] (Johnson)
summary: This dataset consists of continuous seawater and chemistry measurements taken aboard the R/V Discoverer by Jim Johnson and Tim Bates (NOAA/PMEL). These data consist of time, ship location, ship speed and heading, sea surface temperature (SST), salinity, nitrate, and chlorophyll measurements. The dataset contains 30-min averages of these parameters. This dataset was processed and quality controlled following the ACE-1 field phase.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 Filter Chemistry Samples (PRELIMINARY) (Huebert)
summary: This dataset contains filter and single-stage impactor samples taken aboard the C-130 aircraft by Barry Huebert (University of Hawaii Manoa) during ACE-1. Filter and impactor deposits were analyzed by ion chromatography for common inorganic ions and methansulfonates. The data consist of 26 columns including flight number, date/time of sample start/end, substrate, sampler, and concentrations/errors of the following substances: chloride, nitrate, sulfate, sodium, ammonium, potassium, magnesium, calcium, and non sea-salt sulfate. All concentrations are in picomoles of analyte per mole of air drawn through the filter (parts per trillion on a mole basis). Errors are calculated from detection limits and variation in procedural blanks. The data were processed and quality assured by the University of Hawaii.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Spectroradiometer Measurements (300-598nm) (Johnson)
summary: This dataset contains spectroradiometer measurements (300 to 598 nm) collected aboard the NOAA R/V Discoverer by James Johnson (NOAA/PMEL) during the ACE-1 cruise. A Licor 1800 Spectroradiometer with an 8 nm bandwidth was used to measure spectrally resolved solar irradiance. This data contains day of year in UTC (decimal of 15-minute averages), and data at 2 nm intervals (from 300 to 598 nm) in units of watts/meter-2/nm. This dataset was processed and quality controlled by PMEL.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 DMA Size Distribution Data (Clarke)
summary: This dataset consists of dry (rh = 3-25%) particle size distributions measured with the Radial Differential Mobility Analyzer (RDMA) instrument aboard the C-130 during ACE-1. Particle size range is from 0.01 - 0.284 um.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 OPC Size Distribution Data (Clarke)
summary: This dataset consists of dry (rh =25%) particle size  distributions measured with the laser optical particle  counter aboard the C-130 during ACE-1. Particle size range  is approximately 0.15 - 8.00 um.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Spectroradiometer Measurements (600-850nm) (Johnson)
summary: This dataset contains spectroradiometer measurements (600 to 850 nm) collected aboard the NOAA R/V Discoverer by James Johnson (NOAA/PMEL) during the ACE-1 cruise. A Licor 1800 spectroradiometer with an 8 nm bandwidth was used to measure spectrally resolved solar irradiance. This data contains day of year in UTC (decimal of 15-minute averages), and data at 2 nm intervals (from 600 to 850 nm) in units of watts/meter-2/nm. This dataset was processed and quality controlled by PMEL.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Nitric Oxide Measurements (Johnson)
summary: This dataset contains nitric oxide measurements (chemiluminescence method) collected aboard the NOAA R/V Discoverer by James Johnson (NOAA/PMEL) during the ACE-1 period. The data contains day of year in UTC (decimal of hourly averages), and Nitric Oxide (NO) in pptv. The data were processed by PMEL to remove measurements potentially affected by ship exhaust, and quality assured using nighttime analysis to determine the NO artifact. This dataset is still considered preliminary pending further analysis of instrument uncertainties and correlation with other available data.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Ozone Measurements (Johnson)
summary: This dataset contains ozone measurements from two analyzers were collected aboard the NOAA R/V Discoverer by James Johnson (NOAA/PMEL) during the ACE-1 period. The data contain day of year in UTC (decimal of 30-min averages), ozone (ppb), latitude, longitude. The raw data (one-minute averages) were quality assured, calibrated, and 30-min averages produced by NOAA/PMEL.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Carbon Monoxide Measurements (Johnson)
summary: This dataset contains carbon monoxide measurements (gas chromatograph based system) collected aboard the NOAA R/V Discoverer by James Johnson (NOAA/PMEL) during the ACE-1 period. The data contains day of year in UTC (decimal of 6-hourly averages), and carbon monoxide (CO) in ppb. The data were processed and quality assured by PMEL and averaged into 6-hourly averages.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Ozonesonde Measurements (Johnson)
summary: This dataset contains ozonesonde profile measurements collected aboard the NOAA R/V Discoverer by James Johnson (NOAA/PMEL) and Sam Oltmans (NOAA/CMDL) during the ACE-1 cruise. Sixteen releases were made using EN-SCI electrochemical concentration cell ozonesondes which typically reached altitudes of 32 to 37 km. The data contains time in minutes following release, pressure (mb), altitude (km), potential temperature (K), ambient temperature (C), dew point temperature (C), relative humidity (%), ozone partial pressure (mPa), ozone mixing ratio (PPM), day of year (UTC), and latitude/longitude. In addition, the readme" file contains summary information for each release including times/locations
begin_date: estimate of column ozone above the profile
end_date: and total column ozone. The raw data were processed and interpolated onto 250 m altitude increments. Some data points were removed when affected by ship pollution and replaced (interpolated) using a straight line fit. These data are considered PRELIMINARY as further corrections may be applied in the future. "

title: ACE-1: Macquarie Island Radon Measurements (Whittlestone)
summary: This dataset consists of continuous measurements of radon (222) taken at Macquarie Island by Stewart Whittlestone (ANSTO).  The data contain 30-min integrated measurements of radon in mBq m-3 and time at the start of each measurement period. Instrument resolution time was 45 minutes.  This dataset was processed and quality controlled following ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Macquarie Island DMS Measurements (Swan)
summary: This dataset consists of atmospheric concentrations of Dimethylsulfide (DMS) samples taken at Macquarie Island by Hilton Swan (AGAL) during ACE-1. This DMS data defines the start/stop times (UTC) for each sample and is reported as ng/m3 and nmol/m3. Certain meteorological parameters were also recorded, from the 1-minute average Automatic Weather System (AWS), at the start of each DMS sample and these are also included in the dataset. Analytically the DMS measurements were obtained following oxidant and moisture removal from the air stream. Methylethyl sulphide was introduced with each sample as an internal standard, and a pulsed PFD was used for the selective detection of DMS. The data were processed and quality controlled during the ACE-1 field program, and the instrumentation was comparatively compared with similar instrumentation operating at Cape Grim before and after ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer SO2 Measurements [PRELIMINARY] (Saltzman)
summary: This dataset consists of preliminary sulphur dioxide (SO2) concentration measurements (fluorescence based HPLC system) taken aboard the NOAA R/V Discoverer by Eric Saltzman (University of Miami) during the ACE-1 cruise. These data consist of time in UTC (julian decimal day) and SO2 in pptv. The data was filtered for stack gas contamination using wind speed and direction and averaged into 30-minute bins (approx. 3 measurements per bin).  The data was processed and quality controlled following the ACE-1 field phase. While this dataset is PRELIMINARY, it is not expected to change significantly.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim Aerosol Ion Data(Sievering)
summary: This dataset consists of high volume (1.15 m3min-1) impactor measurements of size distributed aerosol ions taken at Cape Grim by H. Sievering and students (University of Colorado-Denver) during ACE-1. The equivalent height of sampling was 120-130 m above sea level. The data set contains coarse sea salt aerosol data in four size cuts (0.9-2.3, 2.3-4.5, 4.5-8, and >8 microns ambient diameter), a fine size cut (0.4-0.9 microns ambient dia.) of mixed sea salt and accumulation mode aerosols, and a very fine size cut (<0.4 microns ambient dia.) of predominantly accumulation mode aerosols. Calculated non-sea-salt SO4(nssSO4) is also presented. All ion data are in units nmol m-3. This dataset was processed and quality controlled following ACE-1. An update of this dataset regarding size cuts may be provided in the future.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Impactor (2-stage) Data (Quinn)
summary: This dataset consists of 2-stage Impactor Data collected aboard the R/V Discoverer by P. Quinn (NOAA/PMEL) during ACE-1. Ion concentrations are given in ng/m3. Submicron values represent the ion concentration in all particles with aerodynamic diameters < 1.0 microns. Super micron values are for particles with aerodynamic diameters > 1 micron and < 10 microns. Diameters are given for the relative humidity of the sampled air stream. These diameters are given for a flow rate of 30 lpm and are subject to change after calibration of the collection efficiency of the impactor jet plate. This calibration is planned for the Fall, 1996.  Uncertainties associated with the ion concentrations range from +/- 5 to 25%. Please refer to the readme" file for a complete list of parameters and ions in this dataset."

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Impactor (7-stage) Data (Quinn)
summary: This dataset consists of 7-stage Impactor Data collected aboard the R/V Discoverer by P. Quinn (NOAA/PMEL) during ACE-1. These data contain ion concentration in ng/m3 for each stage. Diameters for aerodynamic D50 (micron) and dlogDp are reported at the relative humidity of the sampled air stream. (These diameters are given for a flow rate of 23 lpm and are subject to change after calibration of the collection efficiency of each jet plate. This calibration is planned for Fall, 1996). Please refer to the readme" file for a complete list of parameters and ions found in this dataset. "

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Aerosol Size Distributions Data (Quinn)
summary: This dataset consists of Aerosol Size Distributions Data collected aboard the R/V Discoverer by P. Quinn (NOAA/PMEL) during ACE-1. The data are compiled in 30 minute averages from 15 minutes before to 15 minutes after the half hour.  The time is given as decimal day of year (JDAY).

summary: This dataset consists of Total Aerosol Light Scattering, Submicon Aerosol Light Scattering, and ABS(soot) data collected aboard the R/V Discoverer by P. Quinn (NOAA/PMEL) during ACE-1. The data are compiled in 60 minute averages.  The time is given as decimal day of year (JDAY).

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Aerosol Optical Depth (Quinn)
summary: This dataset consists of hand-held sun photometer measurements made aboard the R/V Discoverer during both Legs 1 and 2. These measurements were made in conjunction with the ACE-1 project.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Gas Phase NH3 Concentrations Data (Quinn)
summary: This dataset consists of measured atmospheric gas phase NH3 concentrations and calculated air/sea NH3 fluxes data collected aboard the R/V Discoverer by P. Quinn (NOAA/PMEL) during ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Impactor Data (leg 1) for Gravimetric Analysis [PRELIMINARY] (Quinn)
summary: This dataset consists of 2-stage impactor data collected aboard the R/V Discoverer by P. Quinn (NOAA/PMEL) during ACE-1 for gravimetric analysis.  These data are PRELIMINARY and are from leg 1.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Impactor Data (leg 2) for Gravimetric Analysis (Quinn)
summary: This dataset consists of 2-stage impactor data collected aboard the R/V Discoverer by P. Quinn (NOAA/PMEL) during ACE-1 for gravimetric analysis.  These data are from leg 2.

title: ACE-1: Southern Surveyor Radon Measurements (Whittlestone)
summary: This dataset consists of continuous measurements of radon (222) taken aboard the Southern Surveyor research vessel by Stewart Whittlestone (ANSTO).  The data contain 30-min integrated measurements of  start of each measurement period. Instrument resolution time was 45 minutes.  This dataset was processed and quality-controlled following ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer 2-stage Impactor Data (leg 1) [PRELIMINARY] (Quinn)
summary: This dataset consists of 2-stage impactor data collected aboard the R/V Discoverer by P. Quinn (NOAA/PMEL) during ACE-1.  These data are PRELIMINARY and are from leg 1.

title: ACE-1: Southern Surveyor Chlorophyll Measurements (ASCII)
