title: ACE-1: Southern Surveyor Hydrology Measurements (ASCII)
summary: This dataset contains hydrology data measured from the Southern Surveyor during ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Southern Surveyor Underway Data (ASCII)
summary: This dataset contains data from the Southern Surveyor while underway during ACE-1. Fields contained in this dataset include: Date, latitude, longitude, speed, heading, depth, air temperature, wind speed and direction, PAR, thermosalinograph temperature and salinity, and flouresence.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer 7-stage Impactor Data (leg 1) [PRELIMINARY] (Quinn)
summary: This dataset consists of 7-stage impactor data collected aboard the R/V Discoverer by P. Quinn (NOAA/PMEL) during ACE-1.  These data are PRELIMINARY and are from leg 1.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Surface Seawater pH and Total Ammonia (Quinn)
summary: This dataset consists of Surface Seawater pH and total ammonia data measured onboard the R/V Discoverer by P. Quinn (NOAA/PMEL) during ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Nonmethane Hydrocarbon Data - Air Measurements [Version 3.0] (Prinn)
summary: This dataset consists of the Nonmethane Hydrocarbon Air Measurements taken from the bow of the R/V Discoverer by R. Prinn during ACE-1. (Version 3.0)

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Nonmethane Hydrocarbon Data - Equilibrator Measurements [Version 4.0] (Prinn)
summary: This dataset consists of the Nonmethane Hydrocarbon Dataset Measured from headspace of the equilibrator on the R/V Discoverer by R. Prinn during ACE-1. (Version 4.0)

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Aerosol Ion Data (leg 1) (Sievering)
summary: This dataset consists of high volume (1.15 m3min-1) impactor measurements of size distributed aerosol ions taken aboard the Discoverer ship by H. Sievering and J. Slavich in collaboration with NOAA/PMEL over the South Pacific (30 S-40 S, 160W - 155E). The dataset contains six size cuts of aerosol data (<0.4, 0.4-0.9, 0.9-2.3, 2.3-4.5, 4.5-8, and >8 microns ambient dia.) All ion data are in units of nmol m-3. An update of the data regarding size cuts may be provided in the future.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer NO measured by chemiluminescence (Carsey)
summary: Nitrogen oxides were measured by a chemiluminescence instrument aboard the NOAA R/V Discoverer. This dataset consists of concentrations for NO and estimated error for each time.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer NO2 measured by chemiluminescence (Carsey)
summary: Nitrogen oxides were measured by a chemiluminescence instrument aboard the NOAA R/V Discoverer. This dataset consists of concentrations for NO2 and estimated error for each time.

title: ACE-1: Baring Head Radon Measurements (Whittlestone)
summary: This dataset consists of continuous measurements of radon (222) taken at Baring Head by Stewart Whittlestone (ANSTO).  The data contain 30-min integrated measurements of radon in mBq m-3 and time at the start of each measurement period. Instrument resolution time was 45 minutes.  This dataset was processed and quality controlled following ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer NOy measured by chemiluminescence (Carsey)
summary: Nitrogen oxides were measured by a chemiluminescence instrument aboard the NOAA R/V Discoverer. This dataset consists of concentrations for NOy and estimated error for each time.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer CO2 Measurements (Feely)
summary: This dataset contains measurements of CO2 taken aboard the R/V Discoverer during ACE-1. Richard Feely (PI) reports that the air values are not trustworthy south of 40 degrees southlatitude. The air data are noisy, which happens when the air lines get filled with sea spray during bad weather. The water data look fine according to R. Feely.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer CTD Data (Johnson)
summary: This dataset contains measurements of pressure, temperature, conductivity, depth, salinity, chlorophyll, and density obtained by a CTD device aboard the R/V Discoverer during ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim Peroxides Data (Ayers)
summary: This dataset consists of continuous measurements of peroxides taken at the Cape Grim Monitoring station by G.P. Ayers and R.W. Gillett (CSIRO). The data represents total peroxides"
archive_note: which in clean southern hemisphere marine air approximates H2O2 + 0.25CH3OOH for the liquid/air flow ratio used in the measuring device.  Data consist of time (julian day and hour) and hourly means of peroxides in units of pptv. This dataset was processed and quality controlled following the ACE-1 field phase."

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 GC Sample Inventory (Blake)
summary: This dataset consists of an inventory of Gas Chromatograph (GC) samples taken aboard the C-130 aircraft by D. Blake (University of California/Irvine) during ACE-1. This inventory consists of sample ID followed by start and stop sample times. Sample times vary but approximate 40 second intervals. These samples are currently being analyzed by the GC and data will be provided in the near future.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 Cloud Microphysics Data Plots (Lagrangian A + B) (Siems)
summary: An analysis of the cloud microphysics observations made aboard the C-130 aircraft for the Lagrangian experiments.  Observations are made from the FXXP and 260X probe.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 Cloud Microphysics Analysis (Lagrangian B) (Krummel)
summary: An analysis of the cloud microphysics observations made aboard the C-130 aircraft for the Lagrangian experiments.  Observations are made from the FXXP and 260X probe.

title: Aircraft C-130 Composite Particle Probe Spectra (Baumgardner)
summary: A composite size distribution synthesized from measurements with the C-130 PCHSP, FSSP-300, FSSP-100 and 260-X. Data collected on flights #4 - #28. This composite size distribution represents a reprocessing of the FSSP-300, FSSP-100 and 260-X measurements.

title: Aircraft C-130 MASP Statistical Cloud Pass Data (Baumgardner)
summary: Multiangle Aerosol Spectrometer Probe (MASP) statistical cloud pass data collected by Baumgardner.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 GC Data (Blake)
summary: This dataset consists of Gas Chromatograph (GC) samples taken aboard the C-130 aircraft by D. Blake (University of California/Irvine) during ACE-1. Sample times vary but approximate 40 second intervals.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 Ocean Color Data (Porter)
summary: This dataset consists of measurements of upwelling radiance made from the C-130 aircraft during ACE-1. The data was collected with a spectrophotometer covering the range from 311 to 1132 nm. Users interested in studying cloud reflectance with this data (this was not the original goal of the experiment) should contact the PI for further considerations on this matter (see contact information above).

title: ACE-1: Discoverer DMS Measurements (Bates)
summary: This dataset consists of continuous air and seawater DMS (dimethylsulfide) concentrations and flux measurements taken aboard the R/V Discoverer by Tim Bates (NOAA/PMEL). These data consist of time (julian day), location (lat/lon) and 30-min averages of seawater and atmospheric DMS concentrations and flux calculation. Air samples were collected from 14 m ASL and are reported in units of nmol per cubic meter at standard temperature (25 deg C) and pressure (101.3 kPa). Seawater samples were collected from a depth of 5 m and are reported in units of nmol per cubic meter. The flux of DMS from the ocean to the atmosphere in micromoles per square meter per day was calculated using the exchange coefficients of Wanninkhof (1992). This dataset was processed and quality controlled following the ACE-1 field phase.

title: PRELIMINARY
summary: PRELIMINARY data superceded by 11.76

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim Individual Particle Data - Size/Shape (Anderson) PRELIMINARY
summary: PRELIMINARY data superceded by 11.76

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim MOUDI Data (Huebert)
summary: This dataset consists of impactor chemical data obtained by 8-stage Micro-Orifice Uniform Deposit Impactors (MOUDIs) at Cape Grim during ACE-1. Samples were generally changed daily, though not on a fixed schedule. Some effort was taken to coordinate sample times with meteorological changes. Sampling was continuous whether or not baseline conditions existed.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim MOUDI mass data (Huebert)
summary: This dataset consists of impactor mass data obtained by 8-stage Micro-Orifice Uniform Deposit Impactors (MOUDIs) at Cape Grim during ACE-1. Samples were generally changed daily, though not on a fixed schedule. Some effort was taken to coordinate sample times with meteorological changes. Sampling was continuous whether or not baseline conditions existed. The impactor samples that were weighed were all dedicated to organic analysis, rather than the inorganic analysis used in the other cascade impactor dataset submitted to CODIAC. Therefore, while these samples were typically coordinated with the inorganic samples, they were NOT the same samples.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim PALMS mass spectrometry data (Murphy)
summary: This dataset consists of mass spectra measurements for about 20,000 individual particles sampled at Cape Grim during ACE-1. These data were obtained with the Particle Analysis by Laser Mass Spectrometry (PALMS) Instrument. This instrument measured either the positive or negative ion spectrum of each particle after it is hit with a pulse from a 193 nm excimer laser.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim Individual Particle Data (Anderson)
summary: This dataset consists of particle measurements taken at Cape Grim monitoring station by J. Anderson. Samples were collected on dual, in-line Nuclepore filters with 8 micron and 0.2 micron pores. The files contain both composition and size data.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim Particle Concentration Data (Covert)
summary: This Dataset consists of continuous measurements of particle number concentration taken at Cape Grim monitoring station by Dave Covert (University of Washington). The data represents the number of particles per cubic centimeter in two size bins ( > 3 nm, > 10 nm) @ 20 deg C and ambient pressure. The particle counts have been interpolated over 15-min intervals (beginning at the indicated UTC times). This dataset was processed and quality controlled following the ACE-1 field phase.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 Suggested Averaging Times (Huebert)
summary: Suggested averaging times for C-130 Data from Barry Huebert.  Includes Huebert Impactor sampling times and flight leg statistics; also leg average locations and times for trajectory analyses.  This dataset is also viewable by going to the ACE-1 Project Description page, selecting Description/Summary"
archive_note: and then clicking on "ACE-1 C-130 Suggested Averaging Times from Barry Huebert"."

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim Filter Samples (Huebert)
summary: Cape Grim filter samples from Barry Huebert.  As a quality control check, two filters were being exposed at all times.  A set of criteria, described in the file, was used to choose which of those numbers would best represent any given time interval.  All concentrations are in ppt molar ratio.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim Ion Chromatography Measurements (Cainey)
summary: Cape Grim Ion Chromatography results (obtained using a Dionex DX500) for four impactor samples during ACE-1. The impactor used was an eleven stage Micro-Orifice Uniform Deposition Impactor (MOUDI). The dataset contains sample dates, volume sampled, size ranges for each stage, and the volume of water the sample was extracted in.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim Ozone Measurements (Galbally)
summary: This Dataset consists of continuous measurements of ozone concentration taken at Cape Grim monitoring station. It should be noted that whilst the data have been edited to remove bad data caused by known instrument malfunctions, a detailed item-by-item examination of the data has not been performed.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim NOx Measurements (Galbally)
summary: This Dataset consists of continuous measurements of NO, NO2, and NOx concentrations taken at Cape Grim monitoring station. Whilst the data have been edited to remove bad data caused by known instrument malfunctions, a detailed item-by-item examination of the data has not been performed.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim VOC Measurements (Galbally)
summary: This Dataset consists of measurements of Volatile Organic Compounds (VOC) taken at Cape Grim monitoring station. Whilst the data have been edited to remove bad data caused by known instrument malfunctions, a detailed item-by-item examination of the data has not been performed.

title: ACE-1: Macquarie Island Particle Concentration (>10nm) [PRELIMINARY] (Kreidenweis)
summary: This dataset consists of particle number concentration data (> 10 nm) collected at Macquarie Island by Sonia Kreidenweis and Fred Brechtel (Colorado State University).  The data contain time (ending at the stamped UTC time) and particle counts > 10 nm (N/cm3). The particle counts have been integrated over 1 minute intervals. This dataset has not been edited for baseline, local contamination or other meteorological conditions but calibration times and other non-valid, non-atmospheric data have been removed by the PIs. This results in a non-continuous time record which would need to be accounted for during any averaging procedure.

title: ACE-1: Macquarie Island Particle Concentration (>3nm) [PRELIMINARY] (Kreidenweis)
summary: This dataset consists of particle number concentration data (> 3 nm) taken at Macquarie Island by Sonia Kreidenweis and Fred Brechtel (Colorado State University).  The data contain time (ending at the stamped UTC time) and particle counts > 3 nm (N/cm3). The particle counts have been integrated over 1 minute intervals. This dataset has not been edited for baseline, local contamination or other meteorological conditions, but calibration times and other non-valid, non-atmospheric data have been removed by the PIs. This results in a non-continuous time record which would need to be accounted for during any averaging procedure.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer H-TDMA 035nm Aerosol Data (leg 1)(Swietlicki)
summary: This dataset contains measurements from the Hygroscopic Tandem Differential Mobility Analyser (H-TDMA) aboard the NOAA R/V Discoverer during the ACE-1 voyage from Seattle, USA to Hobart, Australia. Measurements at 35nm dry sizes were performed at 90% relative humidity. These data consist of date/time (UTC), relative humidity (DMA2), julian day, run no., dry size, lst hydroscopic peak parameters (aerosol fraction, beta factor, growth dispersion factor), 2nd and 3rd hydroscopic peak parameters (if observed), and latitude/longitude. This dataset was quality assured and fulfilled a number of criteria based mainly on temperature and relative humidity stability in DMA2 and influence from ship pollution.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim CCN data (Gras)

title: ACE-1: Macquarie Island CCN data [NIWA] (Harvey)
summary: This dataset contains measurements of Cloud Condensation Nuclei (CCN) taken at the Macquarie Island Clean Air Laboratory by Mike Harvey (New Zealand National Institute for Water and Atmospheric Research ?NIWA?) during ACE-1. The data consist of date/time (UTC), chamber supersaturation (%), event log, CCN number (cm-3), and active pixels (CCD camera). This dataset was processed and quality controlled by NIWA following the ACE-1 collection period.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim CCN and CN Data (Hudson)
summary: This dataset contains measurements of CCN and CN concentrations from Cape Grim during ACE-1 provided by the Desert Research Institute (DRI) by Jim Hudson.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim Particle Size Distribution Data (Wiedensohler)
summary: This dataset contains continuous measurements of Particle Size Distribution data collected at Cape Grim during ACE-1 by A. Wiedensohler and F. Stratmann (Institute for Tropospheric Research ?IFT?). For these particle size distribution measurements, a Twin Differential Mobility Particle Sizing (DMPS) system consisting of two Vienna-type Differential Mobility Analyzers (DMAs) and two Condensation Particle Counters (CPCs, TSI 3035 and TSI 3010) was used. Measurements were performed in the particle size regime 3 < dp < 750 nm.  The measured raw distributions were inverted using the new data inversion algorithm developed at the IFT. During the inversion the DMA transmission efficiencies and the CPC counting efficiencies were accounted for. The data consist of date/time, cabin temperature (K), cabin pressure (mb), number of size bins, midpoint particle diameter (nm), and discrete size distribution (#/cm3).

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim, Macquarie Island, Discoverer Radon Back Trajectory Summary (Whittlestone)
summary: Back trajectory data calculated for three platforms by Stewart Whittlestone (ANSTO).  Data for Cape Grim, Macquarie Island, and the Discoverer.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim DMS Measurements (Gras)
summary: This dataset consists of atmospheric concentrations of Dimethylsulfide (DMS) samples taken at Cape Grim during ACE-1. This DMS data defines the start/stop times (UTC) for each sample and is reported as ng/m3 and nmol/m3. The data were processed and quality controlled during the ACE-1 field program and the instrumentation was compared with similar equipment operating at Macquarie Island before and after ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Macquarie Island Bulk Aerosol Chemistry Data (Dick)
summary: This dataset contains results of IC analysis of low volume Fluoropore aerosol filters collected at Macquarie Island (Clean Air Lab.), using a filter stack to seperate sub- and super-micron radius aerosols.

title: Lake-ICE: GOES-8 VIS, IR, and WV Satellite Data (AREA)
summary: This dataset contains GOES-8 satellite data for the Lake-ICE/Snowband Project. The data is in compressed McIDAS area file format. The WV, IR and VIS were archived at 30 minute intervals except during the rapid scan events. Rapid Scan Data is available for Jan 10-14, 21, 23 in a companion dataset (14.22)

title: Lake-ICE: GOES-8 Rapid Scan Satellite Data (AREA)
summary: This dataset contains GOES-8 satellite data for the Lake-ICE/Snowband Project during periods when rapid scan was running. The data is in compressed McIDAS area file format. Rapid Scan is available for Jan 10-14, 21, 23.

title: Ron Brown Meteorology Microwave Radiometer (20, 31, 90 GHz) Tau cruise [Fairall]
summary: This dataset contains microwave radiometer data at 20, 31, and 90 GHz taken aboard the NOAA R/V Ron Brown during the Tau cruise just after R/V Ron Brown's participation in Eastern Pacific Investigation of Climate (EPIC) 2001. The readme contains information on the formating of the data.

title: Ron Brown Meteorology Microwave Radiometer (23, 31 GHz) Tao cruise [Fairall]
summary: This dataset contains microwave radiometer data at 23 and 31 GHz taken aboard the NOAA R/V Ron Brown. During the Tao cruise of R/V Ron Brown's participation in Eastern Pacific Investigation of Climate (EPIC) 2001. The readme contains information on the formating of the data.

title: TOGA COARE soundings from Kanton
summary: This dataset consists of sounding data from Kanton in the Phoenix Islands (WMO 91701). Soundings were taken twice per day (00 and 21 UTC) during the IOP. UCAR/JOSS conducted no quality control on these data. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude taken at a variable vertical resolution. Refer to the station README file for details. NOTE: This dataset has been updated (5/2/2002) with corrected data for the humidity measurement errors of the Vaisala RS 80 radiosonde (Wang et al 2002). Please see the README for details.

title: TOGA COARE soundings from R/V Keifu Maru
summary: This dataset consists of sounding data from aboard the Research Vessel (R/V) Keifu-Maru which was operated by Japan. The R/V was in TOGA-COARE domain during the period from 3 November to 16 November 1992. Soundings were taken four times per day (00, 06, 12, and 18 UTC) during participation in the IOP. UCAR/JOSS conducted no quality control on these data. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude taken at a variable vertical resolution. Refer to the station README file for details. NOTE: This dataset has been updated (5/2/2002) with corrected data for the humidity measurement errors of the Vaisala RS 80 radiosonde (Wang et al 2002). Please see the README for details.

title: TOGA COARE soundings from Kota Kinabalu
summary: This dataset consists of sounding data from Kota Kinabalu in Malaysia (WMO 96471). Soundings were taken four time per (00, 06, 12, and 18 UTC) during the IOP, however the 06 and 18 UTC releases contain only wind information. UCAR/JOSS conducted no quality control on these data. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude taken at a variable vertical resolution. Refer to the station README file for details. NOTE: This dataset has been updates (5/2/2002) with corrected data for the humidity measurement errors of the Vaisala RS 80 radiosonde(Wang et al 2002). Please see the README for details.

title: TOGA COARE soundings from Kapingamarangi
summary: This dataset consists of Integrated Sounding System (ISS) sounding data from Kapingamarangi Island (WMO 91434) in the Caroline Islands which was operated by the National Center for Atmospheric research/Surface and Sounding Systems Facility (NCAR/SSSF). Soundings were taken twice daily (00 and 12 UTC) during the EMP and four times daily (00, 06, 12, and 18 UTC) during the IOP. UCAR/JOSS conducted no quality control on these data. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude taken at 10 second vertical intervals. Refer to the station README file for details. NOTE: This dataset has been updated (4/18/2002) with corrected data for the humidity measurement errors of the Vaisala RS80 radiosonde (Wang et al 2002). Please see the new Readme file for additional information.

This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude taken at 10 second vertical intervals. title: TOGA COARE soundings from Tarawa
summary: This dataset consists of sounding data from Tarawa, Kiribati (WMO 91610). Soundings were taken twice per day (00 and 12 UTC) during the IOP. Some soundings were also taken during the EMP. UCAR/JOSS conducted no quality control on these data. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, and relative humidity taken at 10 second vertical intervals. No wind data were collected at this site. Refer to the station README file for details. NOTE: This dataset has been updated (5/2/2002) with corrected data for the humidity measurement errors of the Vaisala RS 80 radiosonde(Wang et al 2002). Please see the README for details.

title: TOGA COARE CSU Merged Radiosonde/Profiler Dataset
summary: This dataset contains high resolution radiosonde thermodynamic data along with merged radiosonde and profiler winds at six ISS sites and Biak. This dataset was created to mitigate limitations in the radiosonde dataset due to missing and bad wind observations. Soundings in this dataset are in the generic CLASS format and have been archived as compressed ASCII. This dataset has been developed by Paul Ciesielski and others at Colorado State University. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude. NOTE: Many soundings contained within this dataset are undergoing correction for a known dry bias.

title: NCDC NWS Rawinsonde (mand/sig lvls)
summary: Pressure, height, temperature, relative humidity, and wind  speed and direction, at mandatory and significant levels.   Both standard and supplementary soundings are included.     (E-BUFR format)

title: ACE-1: Upper Air, Smart" Balloon Data (Businger)"
summary: Constant-level smart" balloons were used to track air masses during the ACE-1 multi-flight lagrangian missions by Steve Businger and Mark Geldmeier (U of Hawaii). These balloons were released from the R/V Discoverer and transmitted position and meteorological data to receiving equipment on the C-130 aircraft. This dataset consist of four balloon flights during the last two lagrangian missions. The data contain balloon number
maximum_latitude:
and a number of balloon housekeeping parameters.

"

title: NCDC Wind Profiler Network, RASS_6
summary: Radio Acoustic Sounding System (RASS) 6-minute averaged virtual temperature and signal power data. Available only from selected NOAA Profiler Network sites.

title: NCDC Wind Profiler Network, RASS_60
summary: Radio Acoustic Sounding System (RASS) 60-minute averaged virtual temperature and signal power data. Available only from selected NOAA Profiler Network sites.

title: STORM-FEST University of Wisconsin High-Resolution Interferometer Data
summary: The University of Wisconsin operated a High-resolution interferometer as part of the STORM-FEST boundary layer network near Seneca KS.  It provided vertical profiles of temperature and moisture every 12 min from calibrated  infrared downwelling radiance spectra.  Operated nearly continuously except for during rain/snow and calibration.

title: NASA/KSC Profiler Data
summary: NASA/KSC wind profiler primarily operated during CaPE in    standard 3-moment mode at a range of 2 to 18.6 km and 50 m  vertical resolution.  Data consists of vertical profiles of return power, radial velocity and moment variance.  Other   research modes (i.e. various vertical resolutions) are also available.

title: NCDC Wind Profiler Network, Control_6
summary: Engineering status bytes, communications status, network    status, and other information not directly related to       individual data elements.

title: NCDC Wind Profiler Network, Control_60
summary: Engineering status bytes, communication status, network     status, and other status information not directly related   to individual data elements.

title: NCDC Wind Profiler Network, Moments_6
summary: All six-minute 0th, 1st, and 2nd moment information for     three beams (north, east and vertical), modes (high/low),   and gates as well as data availability indicators.

title: NCDC Wind Profiler Network, Moments_60
summary: Hourly averaged 0th, 1st, and 2nd moment information for    three beams (north, east and vertical), modes (high/low),   and gates as well as data availibility indicators.

title: NCDC Wind Profiler Network, Spectrum_6
summary: This dataset contains a diagnostic spectrum which can       rotate any 6 minute period to any beam, gate, or mode.

title: NCDC Wind Profiler Network, Surface_6
summary: Surface data averaged over the previous 6 minute time       interval at a wind profiler site.  Data includes surface    pressure, temperature, dew point, wind speed and direction, and precipitation.

title: NCDC Wind Profiler Network, Surface_60
summary: Surface data averaged over the previous hour at a wind      profiler site.  Data includes surface pressure, temperature,dew point, wind speed and direction, and precipitation.

title: NCDC Wind Profiler Network, Winds_60
summary: This dataset contains  winds averaged over an hour time     period.  Components in u, v, and w directions, and relavent quality control indicators for all levels of the wind       profiler data.

title: NCDC Science-Quality Real Time Upper Air
summary: This dataset contains operational upper-air soundings of    pressure, temperature, moisture, u & v winds, and height at mandatory and significant levels.  Data covers the U.S.,    Canada, Mexico, the Caribbean, and selected Pacific Island  stations.  A hydrostatic consistency test has been performed

title: STORM-FEST NCAR/DSS NMC Soundings
summary: Pressure, hydrostatic height, temperature, dew point depression, wind speed and direction at mandatory and significant levels at official U.S. and Canadian sites across North America.

title: NWS Rawinsonde (mandatory/sig levels)
summary: Pressure, height, temperature, dew point depression, wind   speed and direction, and elapsed time since release at man- datory and significant levels. Both standard and supplemen- tary soundings are included.  These data are subject to     standard NCDC processing procedures.  (NCDC element format)

title: CASES-97: Hemispheric Sky Imager Cloud Fraction Retrievals
summary: This dataset contains the NOAA/ARL/SRRB Hemispheric Sky Imager Cloud Fraction Retrievals, both raw and processed data. The cloud fraction files are in ASCII format, with the extension "cfp." Please see the read-me file for more info. These data are provided as a single tar file.

title: CASES-97: Hemispheric Sky Imager Sky Cover Images (JPEG)
summary: Sky Cover Images from the Hemispheric Sky Imager, in JPEG format.
archive_note: NOTE that this dataset is being replaced by 20.016 Hemispheric Sky Imager (HSI) Imagery.

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: Precipitation NCEP/EMC Ancillary Catalog of Available GCIP Precipitation Data-2001
summary: This data file contains a catalog of the National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP) Environmental Modeling Center (EMC) GCIP Precipitation datasets available for the time period January 1, 1992 thru December 31, 2001. For data collected during 2002 or later, please see the GCIP/EOP Surface: Precipitation NCEP/EMC Ancillary Catalog of Available GCIP Precipitation Data2002-. This dataset is provided as is and in its original format. *The readme file is the catalogue.* To order any of the datasets listed in this catalogue please see the CODIAC listing of GCIP/EOP datasets (including GCIP/EOP Surface: NCEP 4KM GRIB Dataset, GCIP/EOP Surface: NCEP Preview GIF Imagery,  GCIP/EOP Surface: NCEP Daily Precipitation Gage Dataset, and GCIP/EOP Surface: NCEP Hourly Precipitation Gage Dataset.)

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: NOAA/ATDD Walker Branch Watershed Flux Tower Data Set
summary: This data set contains data from the Walker Branch watershed flux tower operated by NOAA/ATDD near Oak Ridge, Tennessee.  Observations are available every 30-min of a wide variety of meteorological, flux, radiation, soil, and carbon dioxide measurements.  Please see the README for further details.

title: GCIP/EOP Model: Mississippi Basin Averaged Daily ECMWF Reanalysis Files (1985-1993)
summary: This dataset contains daily data from 1985 to 1993 for the energy and water budgets for the sub-basins of the Mississippi (the Arkansas-Red, the upper Missouri, the upper Mississippi, the Ohio, and the lower Mississippi and Tennessee Rivers) from the European Centre for Medium-Range Weather Forecasts (ECMWF) reanalysis ?ERA15?, and from observations of precipitation and streamflow.  The original ECMWF model data were computed on-line with an hourly time scale, but have been summed or averaged up to the daily timescale, because the model has significant precipitation errors in the diurnal timescale which largely disappear on the daily timescale (Betts et al, 1998, 1999).  This also reduces the data volume by a factor of 24. See the README file for more details.

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: Precipitation NCEP/CPC Unified Raingauge Dataset
summary: This dataset contains the National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP) Climate Prediction Center (CPC) Unified Raingauge Dataset. This dataset has been developed by NCEP/CPC from multiple sources of U.S. raingauge data. The files are compressed using the UNIX compress" command and "uncompress" must be used before decoding. This dataset is provided as is and was not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS."

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: Precipitation NCEP/EMC Preview Imagery (GIF) 1998-2001
summary: This dataset contains the National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP) Environmental Modeling Center (EMC) GIF Imagery including Hourly Stage IV GIF, Daily Stage IV GIF, and Daily RFC GIF. Depending on the time period selected, all three GIF types may or may not be available. Please see the GCIP/EOP: Surface NCEP Ancillary Catalogue of Available GCIP Precipitation Data (NCEP/EMC). This dataset is provided as is and was not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS. These data are available for browsing purposes.  Dataset is available for on-line download.

title: GCIP/EOP Land Characterization: EROS Data Center Aggregated Land Cover Data
summary: The land cover classes developed under the coordination of the international Geosphere-Biosphere Programme Data and Information System (IGBP-DIS) have been analyzed for a study area that includes the Conterminous United States and portions of Mexico and Canada. The 1-km resolution data available from the IGBP-DIS global 1 km land cover data set have been analyzed to produce a 20-km resolution grided data set that includes the three most dominant land cover classes within each 20-km grid cell. Additionally, the fractional area associated with each of the three most dominant land cover classes as well as teh area covered by water, was computed for each 20-km grid cell. The fractional green vegetation cover (fgreen) associated with each of the three most dominant land cover classes per grid cell was computed on a monthly basis. The mean and standard deviation of fgreen were developed from monthly values of the normalized difference vegetation index from 5-years (1993, 1995-98) of data derived from 1-km resloution NOAA-AVHRR data.

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: NOAA/ATDD Walker Branch Watershed Flux Tower Data
summary: This data set contains data from the Walker Branch watershed flux tower operated by NOAA/ATDD near Oak Ridge, Tennessee.  Observations are available every 30-min of a wide variety of meteorological, flux, radiation, soil, and carbon dioxide measurements.  Please see the README for further details.

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: Niwot Ridge, CO Flux Tower Data
summary: The Niwot Ridge Colorado flux tower sites is part of the Ameriflux network of towers.
archive_note: Data and information were available online via remote link to CDIAC.

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: Shidler, OK Flux Tower Data
summary: The Shidler Oklahoma flux tower sites is part of the Ameriflux network of towers.
archive_note: Data and information were available online via remote link to CDIAC.

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: Ponca City, OK Flux Tower Data
summary: The Ponca City Oklahoma flux tower sites is part of the Ameriflux network of towers.
archive_note: Data and information were available online via remote link to CDIAC.

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: Park Falls, WI Flux Tower Data
summary: The Park Falls Wisconsin flux tower sites is part of the Ameriflux network of towers.
archive_note: Data and information were available online via remote link to CDIAC.

title: GCIP/EOP Sub-Surface: Illinois Soil Moisture Data
summary: This data set consists of total soil moisture measured at 19 stations in the state of Illinois, USA, from 1981 to November 2001, measured with the neutron probe technique, calibrated with gravimetric observations. The data are measured for the top 10 cm of soil, and then for 20 cm layers (e.g., 10-30 cm, 30-50 cm, ...) down to a depth of 2 m. The vegetation at all stations is grass, except for one station with bare soil measurements, at the same location as a grass-covered station. The measurements are at approximately monthly intervals.

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: Precipitation NCEP/EMC Ancillary Catalog of Available GCIP Precipitation Data2002-
summary: This data file contains a catalog of the National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP) Environmental Modeling Center (EMC) GCIP Precipitation datasets available for the time period January 1, 2002 on. For data collected previous to 2002, please see the GCIP/EOP Surface: Precipitation NCEP/EMC Ancillary Catalog of Available GCIP Precipitation Data-2001. This dataset is provided as is and in its original format. *The readme file is the catalogue.* To order any of the datasets listed in this catalogue please see the CODIAC listing of GCIP/EOP datasets (including GCIP/EOP Surface: NCEP 4KM GRIB Dataset, GCIP/EOP Surface: NCEP Preview GIF Imagery,  GCIP/EOP Surface: NCEP Daily Precipitation Gage Dataset, and GCIP/EOP Surface: NCEP Hourly Precipitation Gage Dataset.)

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: Hourly 4x4 Radar-Based Precipitation Database for the Mississippi River Basin
summary: This dataset contains hourly 4km resolution radar-based precipitation for the Mississippi River Basin for the GCIP EOP (January 1996 to December 2000). This dataset was developed by the University of Iowa IIHR Hydrosciences and Engineering in conjuction with the Princeton University Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering. The data are derived from input composite reflectivity maps from the Global Hydrology Resource Center.  Included with the data are tools for database manipulation and documentation.   UCAR/JOSS has performed no Quality Control on this dataset.

title: GCIP/WEBS CDROM
summary: This CD provides a water and energy budget synthesis (WEBS) for the Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment's (GEWEX's) Continental Scale International Project (GCIP). The synthesis includes a brief description of the Mississippi River Basin climate, physiographic characteristics, available observations, representative types of models used for GCIP investigations, as well as a comparison of water and energy variables and budgets from models and observations for the recent period.

title: GCIP/EAOP-98 Surface: NOAA/ATDD Walker Branch Watershed Flux Tower Data Set
summary: This data set contains data from the Walker Branch watershed flux tower operated by NOAA/ATDD near Oak Ridge, Tennessee.  Observations are available every 30-min of a wide variety of meteorological, flux, radiation, soil, and carbon dioxide measurements.  Please see the README for further details.

title: SGP97 Surface: Precipitation NCEP/CPC Gage Only Daily Dataset
summary: The Climate Prediction Center (CPC), a component of the National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP) acquires gage-based precipitation reports in near real-time from several thousand sites across the contiguous 48 states of the USA. There are approximately 5,800 daily rain gage reports per day out of a total available set of 9,000. These daily precipitation reports are collected by the 12 River Forecast Centers (RFC) and sent to NCEP. This dataset contains the NCEP Daily Precipitation Gage Data. This dataset is provided as is and was not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS.

title: SGP97 Surface: Precipitation NCEP/CPC Gage Only Hourly Dataset
summary: The Climate Prediction Center (CPC), a component of the National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP) acquires precipitation reports in near real-time from several thousand sites across the contiguous 48 states of the USA. Approximately 3000 automated, hourly rain gage observations are available in the US via the GOES Data Collection Platform (DCP) administered by the NWS Office of Hydrology (OH). These hourly reports are transmitted continuously throughout the day to NCEP in a SHEF-encoded message. This dataset contains the NCEP Hourly Precipitation Gage Data. This dataset is provided as is and was not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS.

title: SGP97 Sub-Surface: PSU Soil Properties Data
summary: This data set was developed by the EOS IDS Team at Penn State for the Southern Great Plains 1997 (SGP-97) project. The following data coverages are available: DEM, Landcover and Landuse, Gauge Stations, Available Water Capacity, Bulk Density, Depth to Bedrock, Hydrologic Soils Group, Mapunits, Percent Water, Porosity, Rock Fragment Class, Rock Volume, Soil Fractions, and Surface Soil Texture. This data set is available from NASA/GSFC via the "download" link below.

title: CaPE NCDC NWS Tampa Bay RADAP II Data
summary: The existing NWS Tampa Bay WSR-57 radar was equipped with a second generation RAdar DAta Processor (RADAP II).  RADAP IIautomatically controls radar operation and aquires approx.  10 min tilt sequence volume scan data at a resolution of 2 deg by 1 nautical mile range from 10 - 125 nautical miles. Data consists of low level PPI and volumetric reflectivity.

title: CaPE NWS Melbourne WSR-88D Radar Data
summary: The NWS Melbourne WSR-88D Doppler radar was installed duringCaPE, but was not fully operational.  It was not operated instandard volume scan modes nor was the data routinely  archived.  It was operated sporadically in test mode and as such, any data should be used with extreme caution.  ContactMelbourne NWS directly for further details.

title: NWS Radar Summary Charts
summary: Hourly Radar summary charts on 35 mm microfilm.  Data con-  tain analyzed areas, lines, and cells of precip that includethe base, top, intensity, intensity change (+,-), movement, and precip type.  Charts are prepared at NMC.

title: NCDC WSR-88D (NEXRAD) Level II Data
summary: Level II data are digital base data output from the Radar Data Acquisition processors in polar form.  These data are processed by meteorological and hydrological analysis algorithms to produce Level III data (products).

title: NWS Radar Scope Reflectivity Film
summary: 16 and 35 mm film of PPI reflectivity data at individual    WSR-57 radar sites. When echoes are present frames are takenat least every 5 minute and sometimes as often as every 40  seconds.  Radar overlays and grid maps for these sites are  also available.

title: WSR-88D Operational Products(ArchiveIII)
summary: Non-Precipitation Mode: reflectivity, velocity, and spectrumwidth; Composite reflectivity; Digital precip array & radar coded message; and VAD winds.  Precipitation Mode: same as  non-precip. mode and vertically integrated liquid, sig. wx  overlay, echo tops, 1-hr precip. & severe wx analysis.

title: CaPE FAA TDWR Program Research Radar
summary: FAA TDWR radars operating in the vicinity of the Orlando    Airport under MIT/LL coordination included FL-2 (S-band),   FL-3, UND and MIT Enterprise (all C-band) and ASR.  Final   processed data includes reflectivity, radial velocity and   time series.

title: NWS Manually Digitized Radar Data
summary: NWS radar data for the  U.S. is routinely digitized by NMC  and distributed over weather data commincations networks.   Final datasets consist of digital files, hard copy hourly   NWS radar summary charts (35 min past hour), and 35-mm micro-film copies of these hourly charts.

title: VORTEX NOAA WP-3D Radar Data
summary: NOAA operated a WP-3D research aricraft during VORTEX.  It carries 2 radars: A non-coherent horizontally scanning  lower fuselage radar and a 3 cm wavelength vertically  scanning tail Doppler radar.  Both radars are three-axis  stabilized.

title: VORTEX Cimarron Doppler Radar
summary: Cimarron ia a 10 cm wavelength multiparameter Doppler radar that provided data on target storms during VORTEX.  Data collected consists of reflectivity and velocity spectra as well as multiparameter information.

title: CaPE USAF Patrick Radar Data
summary: The USAF Patrick Radar (WSR-74C) at Patrick AFB provided    routine PPI scans to support aircraft operations during     CaPE. Data consists of horizontal relectivity processed and archived in McGill format. Software are available for       conversion to UF.  Data continuous during Lear jet filghts.

title: CaPE NMIMT Mobile Radar Data
summary: New Mexico Institute of Mining and Technology (NMIMT)  mobile X-band, 3-cm wavelength, dual polarization, coherent and incoherent radar operated in conjunction with the CP-2 radar.  Data consists of raw time series and parallel  channel housekeeping data. Not fully operational until near end of CaPE.

title: UMRBPP Surface: NCEP Stage IV 4 KM GRIB Data Set
summary: The National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP) is a component of the Climate Prediction Center (CPC). A prototype, real-time, hourly, multi-sensor National Preciptation Analysis (NPA) has been developed at NCEP in cooperation with the Office of Hydrology (OH). This analysis merges two data sources that are currently being collected in real-time by OH and NCEP. Hourly digital precipitation (HDP) radar estimates are created by the WSR-88D Radar Product Generator on a 131 X 131 4-km grid centered over each radar site. Data analysis routines, including a bias correction of the radar estimates using rain gage data, have been adapted by NCEP on a national 4-km grid from algorithms developed by OH and executed regionally at NWS River Forecast Centers (RFC). This data set contains the NCEP 4 KM GRIB Data including multi-sensor analysis (gage and unbiased radar), gage-only analysis, radar estimate, and radar estimate after bias removal. Depending on the time period selected, all four types may or may not be available. This data set is provided as is and was not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS.

title: UMRBPP Surface: NCEP Precipitation Gage Station List
summary: This data file contains the station information for the  Climate Prediction Center (CPC) National Centers for  Environmental Prediction (NCEP) Gage Data Sets. This data  set is provided as is and in its original format.

title: UMRBPP Surface: NCEP Stage IV Preview GIF Imagery
summary: This data set contains the Climate Prediction Center (CPC) National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP) GIF Imagery including Hourly Stage IV GIF, Daily Stage IV GIF, and Daily RFC GIF. Depending on the time period selected, all three GIF types may or may not be available. This data set is provided as is and was not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS.

title: UMRBPP Surface: NCEP Daily Gage Precipitation Data Set
summary: The Climate Prediction Center (CPC), a component of the  National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP)  acquires gage-based precipitation reports in near real-time from several thousand sites across the contiguous 48 states of the USA. There are approximately 5,800 daily rain gage  reports per day out of a total available set of 9,000.  These daily precipitation reports are collected by the 12  River Forecast Centers (RFC) and sent to NCEP. This data  set contains the NCEP Daily Precipitation Gage Data. This  data set is provided as is and was not quality controlled  by UCAR/JOSS.

title: UMRBPP Surface: NCEP Hourly Gage Precipitation Data Set
summary: The Climate Prediction Center (CPC), a component of the  National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP)  acquires precipitation reports in near real-time from  several thousand sites across the contiguous 48 states of  the USA. Approximately 3000 automated, hourly rain gage  observations are available in the US via the GOES Data  Collection Platform (DCP) administered by the NWS Office  of Hydrology (OH). These hourly reports are transmitted  continuously throughout the day to NCEP in a SHEF-encoded  message. This data set contains the NCEP Hourly  Precipitation Gage Data. This data set is provided as is  and was not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS.

title: UMRBPP Surface: Meteorological Tower Data Set
summary: The Upper Missouri River Basin Pilot Project (UMRBPP) Meteorological Tower Data Set contains 15-min mean observations of wind speed (at 60 and 100 feet), wind direction (at 100 feet), and temperature, relative humidity, and pressure (at the tower base) from three sites in the UMRBPP region.  See the README for further information.

title: UMRBPP Upper Air: Custer, SD Profiler Wind Profiles Data Set
summary: The Upper Missouri River Basin Pilot Project (UMRBPP) Custer, South Dakota Profiler Wind Profiles data set contains profiles of wind speed and direction at 30 minute intervals from 31 March to 10 May 1999.  Data are available in two modes.  In one mode measurements are available  every 100 m in the vertical up to 2500 m and in the other mode measurements are available every 400 m up to 4600 m above the ground.  UCAR/JOSS performed no additional  quality control on these data.  See the README for further information.

title: UMRBPP Upper Air: Custer, SD Microwave Radiometer Water Vapor Profiles Data Set
summary: The Upper Missouri River Basin Pilot Project (UMRBPP) Custer, South Dakota Microwave Radiometer Water Vapor  Profiles Data Set contains vertical profiles of water vapor taken at 30 minute intervals from 31 March to 10 May 1999. UCAR/JOSS performed no additional quality control on these data.  See the README for further information.

title: UMRBPP Upper Air: Custer, SD High Resolution Rawinsonde Data Set
summary: This is one of the sounding datasets developed for  The Upper Missouri River Basin Pilot Project (UMRBPP). The dataset consists of research  soundings from Custer, South Dakota and contains vertical profiles  of pressure, temperature, dew point, humidity, U and V wind components, total wind speed and  direction, and latitude and longitude taken every 10  seconds after the sonde's release time. The soundings  were typically released at 00 and 12 UTC, but there  were occasional releases at 06 and 18 UTC. Note:  since the files are loaded in the database using the  actual release times, use the hour just before or the hour a couple hours before UTC release time,when  attempting to browse this dataset. UCAR/JOSS performed  an automated quality control on this data.  See the  README for further information.

title: UMRBPP Upper Air: Four Corners High Resolution Rawinsonde Data Set
summary: This is one of the sounding datasets developed for the  Upper Missouri River Basin Pilot Project (UMRBPP).  The dataset consists of research soundings form the  Four Corners site and contains vertical profiles of  pressure, temperature, dew point, humidity,  U and V wind components, total wind speed and  direction,  and latitude and longitude taken every 10  seconds after the sonde's release time. The soundings were typically released at 00 and 12 UTC, but there were  occassional releases at 06 and 18 UTC. Note: since the files are loaded in the database using the actual release time, use the hour just before or a couple hours before the UTC release time when attempting to browse the dataset. UCAR/JOSS performed automated quality control on this data. See the README for further information.

title: UMRBPP Aircraft: UND Citation Aircraft Flight Parameters CDROM
summary: This CD-ROM contains data collected from the University of North Dakota Citation II Weather Research Aircraft during the Upper Missouri River Basin Pilot Project (UMRBPP). Data are available for the eight flights the Citation undertook during this period. Two types of data are included on this CD: a high rate data set (25 Hz) and a low rate data set (4 Hz). See the README for further information.

title: GCIP/LSA-NW 99 Surface: AgriMet Hourly Surface Data in QC Format
summary: The Great Plains Region AgriMet data Network (AgriMet) Hourly Surface Data in QC format is one of several surface datasets provided in the GEWEX Continental-Scale International Project (GCIP) Large Scale Area-North West (LSA-NW) Enhanced Annual Observing Period (EAOP) 1999.  This dataset contains data for the GCIP LSA-NW EAOP-99 domain and time period.  These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: GCIP/LSA-NW 99 Surface: AgriMet Specials" Surface Data in QC Format"
summary: The Great Plains Region AgriMet data Network (AgriMet) Specials" Surface Data in QC format is one of several surface datasets provided in the GEWEX Continental-Scale International Project (GCIP) Large Scale Area-North West (LSA-NW) Enhanced Annual Observing Period (EAOP) 1999.  This dataset contains data for the GCIP LSA-NW EAOP-99 domain and time period.  These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS). "

title: NOAA TOVS Digital Soundings
summary: Two NOAA polar orbiting satellites carried the TOVS system during STORM-FEST.  TOVS carried: High Resolution Infrared Radiation Sounder (HIRS/2) measured incident radiation primarily in the IR; Microwave Sounding Unit (MSU) a passivescanning microwave spectrometer with 4 channels;  Stratospheric Sounding Unit (SSU), a step-scanning far- infrared spectrometer with 3 channels; Solar Backscattered Ultraviolet system (SBUV/2) maps total ozone concentrations and vertical ozone distirbutions.  Up to 4 overpasses of theSTORM-FEST region were made daily (1600 km swath).

title: NOAA AVHRR Digital Imagery (LAC)
summary: Two NOAA polar orbiting satellites carried the AVHRR sensor during STORM-FEST.  AVHRR has five spectral channels in the visible, near-infrared and infrared. Data consists of 1 km resolution HRPT or LAC and 4 km resolution GAC imagery over a 1600 km swath.  Up to 4 overpasses of the STORM-FEST  region occur daily.

title: STORM-FEST DMSP OLS Digital Imagery
summary: DMSP is comprised of three near polar orbiting satellites that provide images in two spectral bands: visible (0.56 km)and infrared (2.78 km) from an Operational Linescan System. There are up to 4 overpasses of the STORM-FEST region daily.

title: STORM-FEST DMSP OLS Transparencies
summary: DMSP is comprised of three near ploar orbiting satellites that provide images in two spectral bands: visible (0.56 km)and infrared (2.78 km) from an Operational Linescan System. There were up to 4 overpasses of the STORM-FEST area daily.

title: GOES-7 VAS Derived Products Data
summary: The GOES-7 VISSR Atmospheric Sensor allowed for the derivation of (for clear/partly cloudy conditions) cloud cover, earth/cloud temperatures, cloud type, cloud motion derived winds, stereo derived cloud-top heights, water vaporand temperature fields, improved surface temperatures and vertical profiles of temperature and moisture. Also,  precipitable water was derived.  The  parameters able to be derived depends on the mode of operation of the satellite (normal/RISOP).

title: GOES-7 VISSR Cloud Motion Vectors
summary: Cloud motion vectors are derived from successive pairs of   VISSR images by both manual and automated techniques.  This process is performed every 12 hours.  Each vector includes  date/time, lat/lon, pressure altitude and cloud motion wind speed and direction.

title: GOES-7 Satellite Winds (SATWND)
summary: GOES winds, both cloud drift and water vapor drift. Gradientwinds from VAS soundings.  The horizontal spacing is on the order of 2 degrees.  In NMC Office Note 29 format.

title: STORM-FEST GOES-7 VAS Dwell Soundings
summary: The GOES-7 VISSR Atmospheric Sensor allowed for the derivation of Dwell Soundings consisting of vertical  profiles of temperature and moisture.  The interval and  number of dwell soundings depended on whether the satellite was in normal or RISOP operations.  Data are available from NOAA/NESDIS

title: STORM-FEST DMSP SSM/I Digital Data
summary: The USAF/DMSP consists of 3 near polar orbiting satellites that provided global microwave data from the SSM/I.  SSM/I provides water vapor measurements (1400 km swath) at three frequencies (19.35, 37.0, 85.5 GHz).  Up to 4 overpasses of the STORM-FEST region were made daily.

title: CaPE GOES-7 VAS Dwell Sounding Data
summary: All routine GOES-7 VISSR Atmospheric Sounder Dwell Sounding (DS) data are archived at NESDIS.  The interval and number  of dwell soundings and derived products (i.e. cloud         parameters) depends on the mode of operations (normal versusRISOP).

title: CaPE NOAA AVHRR Imagery and TOVS Data
summary: AVHRR imagery of the Florida region was collected from the 3NOAA polar orbiting satellites (up to 6 overpasses daily)   during CaPE.  Imagery (5 spectral channels) includes LAC    (1 km) and GAC (4 km) resolutions.  TOVS sensor data and    sounding products are available from the same overpasses.

title: CaPE DMSP OLS Imagery
summary: DMSP is comprised of three near polar orbiting satellites   that provide images in two spectral bands: visible (0.56 km)and infrared (2.78 km) from an Operational Linescan System. There were up to 6 overpasses of the Florida area daily.

title: CaPE French SPOT Satellite Data
summary: French SPOT polar orbiting satellite imagery (HRV sensor) over the Florida region support ground-based hydrologic and vegetation measurements. Data includes 4 clear air overpass high resolution (20 m) visible and near-infrared (3 total wavelength bands) color stereoscopic imagery over a 950 km pass swath. Used to produce the NDVI values over the CaPE region.

title: Triple Hot Film Anemometer Measurements Compared to Sonic Anemometer Measurements in CASES-99 [Miller]
summary: This dataset consists of an Excel spreadsheet and comma delimited ASCII format files containing data from sonic anemometers, triple hot film anemometers, single cold film anemometers, and pneumatic sheath systems during the CASES-99 project.  The data were recorded at 2 different heights.  For more information please see the read-me file.

title: FMCW (UMASS) Radar Data Plots [Fraiser]
summary: This dataset contains FMCW Data Plots for selected time periods during each CASES-99 IOPs. A companion dataset (45.301) contains netCDF data files for each IOP.

title: Eddy Correlation Data (Processed) [Hartogensis]
summary: This dataset contains ASCII data collected by two eddy correlation systems, one at 10m height and one at 3m. These systems consisted of a CSAT3 sonic, a KH2O Krypton fast response hygrometer, and a FW05 Thermocouple all from Campbell Scientific. The processed data contains 5 and 30 minute fluxes computed from the raw 20Hz data with software developed at Wageningen University.

title: Scintillometer - Large Aperture [Hartogensis]
summary: This dataset contains ASCII data collected by a large aperture scintillometer during CASES-99. The scintillometer was oriented in a NNE-SSW direction with a path lenght of 420 m. Data was collected at 1 second intervals averaged to 1 minute samples for this dataset.

title: Scintillometer - Split Beam Laser [Hartogensis]
summary: This dataset contains ASCII data collected by a Split Beam Laser Scintillometer during CASES-99. The scintillometer was oriented in a NE-SW direction with a path lenght of 112 m. Data was collected at 6 second intervals for this dataset. Data are available for nighttime periods only.

title: Radiation, THP and Soil Sensor 1-min Data [Hartogensis]
summary: This dataset contains ASCII data collected by a variety of sensors contributed both by Russ Qualls and Wageningen University. The sensors included in this dataset are an albedometer, a pyrgeometer, an infrared Thermometer and 2 temperature humidity probes for Radiation. The soil sensors consisted of 6 soil thermometers, 2 soil heat flux plates, a soil temerature probe and a soil moisture probe. This dataset contains 1 minute average data for selected sensors. A companion dataset (45.605) contains 10 minute average data for these sensors.

title: Radiation, THP and Soil Sensor 10-min Data [Hartogensis]
summary: This dataset contains ASCII data collected by a variety of sensors contributed both by Russ Qualls and Wageningen University. The sensors included in this dataset are an albedometer, a pyrgeometer, an infrared Thermometer and 2 temperature humidity probes for Radiation. The soil sensors consisted of 6 soil thermometers, 2 soil heat flux plates, a soil temerature probe and a soil moisture probe. This dataset contains 10 minute average data for selected sensors. A companion dataset (45.604) contains 1 minute average data for these sensors.

title: Lidar - University of Iowa Water Vapor Data [Eichinger]
summary: This dataset contains lidar water vapor measurements in the boundary layer and analyses in multiple formats as part of CASES-99.  The data are located on a CD and have multiple formats.

title: Gulley Substudy Array - Handar Sonic Winds [Mahrt]
summary: This dataset contains horizontal wind components measured with Handar 425A 2D sonic anemometers and 555A data loggers with expanded memory modules  and PCMCIA SRAM cards. The sampling and logging rate was 0.5 hertz. A total of 5 sonics were deployed at 5 different locations. measurement height was 1.0 m above ground at all locations. For more information, see the readme file.

title: Gulley Substudy Array - Ground-Based Air Temperature [Mahrt]
summary: This dataset contains air temperature measured with slow response  thermistors and data loggers from Onset Computer Corp. (HOBO H8  External Sensors and HOBO 4-Channel External Logger). The sensor  range is 0C to +44C, accuracy plus/minus 0.3C at +20C, resolution  plus/minus 0.2C at +20C, response time in air 5 minutes. The sampling  and logging rate was one value every 5-minutes. A total of 8 ground based thermistors were deployed at 8 different locations. The  measurement height was 50 cm above ground. These measurements were  made in the gully portion of the CASES-99 network. For more information please see the readme file.

title: Gulley Substudy Array - 10 m Tower Air Temperatures [Mahrt]
summary: This dataset contains air temperature measurements made by  8 thermistors deployed in the vertical on the 10 m tower  deployed by the group from the Universitat de Barcelona, Spain  (Maria Rosa Soler). These thermistors were installed at heights of  20 cm, 30 cm, 50 cm, 1 m, 2.5 m, 4.2 m, 6.4 m and 9.7 m. These measurements were made in the gully portion of the  CASES-99 network. For more information please see the readme file.

title: Microbarograph Stations - Differential Pressure [Nappo]
summary: The ATDD-microbarograph network was designed to monitor the temporal and spatial characteristics of gravity waves and other coherent, i.e., non-turbulent atmospheric pressure perturbations.  These perturbations are obtained as pressure differences between the static atmospheric pressure and a reference pressure as described in Section 3.  Microbarographs were located at CASES-99 towers 1, 4, 5, 7, 8, and 9. Differential pressure data were recorded continuously from 3 October to 31 October, 1999.  Data sampling was at 10 Hz from which 10-second averages were calculated and recorded.  For more information, please see the readme file.

title: Tower - 10 Meter 10-second Data (ASCII) [Soler]
summary: This dataset contains data from the instrumented tower provided by Maria Soler.  The sub-gully study consists in a 10 m tower instrumented with: Three levels, 1.06, 3.07 and 9 m of slow response measurements of temperature, wind speed and di rection, and humidity. Two sonic anemometers were implemented at 1.75 and 7.4 m respectively.  T he measurements also include net radiation at 1.06 m, ground heat flux at 8 cm, four soil temper ature sensors at 1.5, 6, 14, 28, and two moisture sensors at 14 and 28 cm, respectively.

title: Tower - 10 Meter 5-minute Data (ASCII) [Soler]
summary: This dataset contains data from the instrumented tower provided by Maria Soler.  The sub-gully study consists in a 10 m tower instrumented with: Three levels, 1.06, 3.07 and 9 m of slow response measurements of temperature, wind speed and di rection, and humidity. Two sonic anemometers were implemented at 1.75 and 7.4 m respectively.  T he measurements also include net radiation at 1.06 m, ground heat flux at 8 cm, four soil temper ature sensors at 1.5, 6, 14, 28, and two moisture sensors at 14 and 28 cm, respectively.

title: Tower Thermocouple Data [Sun]
summary: This dataset contains 5 and 20 Hz data obtained from thermocouples mounted on an instrumented tower. During CASES-99 there were 34 levels of thermocouples, 32 on the NCAR ATD main tower and 2 near the ground but slightly offset from the main tower. The 34 levels of thermocouples cover the vertical range of 0.23m to 58.1m. The air temperature observed with the thermocouples were recorded at 5 samples per second (5-Hz).  Detailed information on instruments and data processing can be found at:    http://www.mmm.ucar.edu/science/abl/cases/

title: Boundary-Layer Depth [Mahrt]
summary: The following file includes the latest estimates of the boundary-layer depths at the main tower. UCAR/JOSS conducted no quality control on these data. This dataset was taken for the Cooperative Atmospheric Surface Exchange Study October 1999 (CASES-99).

title: North Slope: Chandalar Shelf Temp & Soil Moisture Excel Data
summary: This dataset includes temperature and soil moisture data from the North Slope Site of Alaska. For more information, see the readme file.

title: North Slope: Deadhorse Temp & Soil Moisture Excel Data
summary: This dataset includes temperature and soil moisture data from the North Slope Site of Alaska. For more information, see the readme file.

title: North Slope: Franklin Bluffs Temp & Soil Moisture Excel Data

title: SGP99 Surface: Precipitation NCEP/CPC Gage Only Hourly Dataset
summary: The Climate Prediction Center (CPC), a component of the National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP) acquires precipitation reports in near real-time from several thousand sites across the contiguous 48 states of the USA. Approximately 3000 automated, hourly rain gage observations are available in the US via the GOES Data Collection Platform (DCP) administered by the NWS Office of Hydrology (OH). These hourly reports are transmitted continuously throughout the day to NCEP in a SHEF-encoded message. This dataset contains the NCEP Hourly Precipitation Gage Data. This dataset is provided as is and was not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS.

title: SGP99 Upper Air: DOE ARM SGP High-Resolution (2 second) Soundings
summary: This data set contains upper air soundings taken at the DOE Atmospheric Radiation Measurement - Clouds and Radiation Testbed (ARM-CART) site in Kansas and Oklahoma. Data from five ARM-CART sites have been included. This data set includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude. See the Readme file for more details.

title: CaPE Electric Field Mill (Ground-based)
summary: The USAF and NASA/KSC operates a network of 31 electric field mills in the KSC/CCAFS area; these measure electric field (volts/meter) at 60 points per second time resolution.Collected primarily from 1400-2359 UTC daily, but extended times during adverse weather.

title: CaPE ONERA Interferometer Data
summary: The French ONERA Interferometer was installed at the end of CaPE to identify lightning sources and channels.  The       Interferometer operated at 110 MHz and consisted of two     ground stations: one azimuth/elevation station SW of Orlandoairport and one azimuth only station SSE of Orlando airport.Data consists of 2D plan-view flash density plots (30 min), 2D flash resolved data (nearest sec) and 3D flash/time      resolved data (nearest sec).

title: CaPE NMIMT Interferometer Data
summary: NMIMT two-dimensional interferometer was operated at KSC from 9-19 August 1991, after CaPE it was moved to Orlando airport. It operated at 274 MHz with 1 microsecond resolution utilizing 5 antennas. Data consists of time, electric field change, phase data, electric field and housekeeping parameters. change, phase data, e-field etc.

title: CaPE Still/Streak Photography
summary: Still and streak photography of rocket triggered lightning  was performed by SUNYA to document upward propagating       leaders, the structure of individual leader steps, and the  variation of leader steps with height.  Photography was     obtained by video, 35mm and several high speed cameras at   two fixed sites in the RTLP area.

title: CaPE High Speed Photography
summary: NOAA/NSSL operated a high speed motion analyzing system     (Kodak Ektapro 1000) with image intensifier which provided  video observations of lightning development (1000 frames/sec) in an all sky mode.  Also, photography was obtained using a high speed fastax camera (2000 frames/sec). Stereoscopic  video photography was taken at two sites in the RTLP area.

title: CaPE MIT/LL Corona Point Data
summary: MIT/LL operated a 13 station network of corona points in a small area around the Orlando International airport. The corona point network monitered the polarity of the surface electric field and lightning activity within 10-15 km of thesensors with a sampling frequency of 1 Hz.

title: CaPE Electric Field Mill Data (Airborne)
summary: The NASA Lear Jet, SDSM&T T-28, the NCAR King Air, and the NCAR Sailplane were equipped with 4 to 8 field mills to obtain two to three components of the electric field during flight at 1 sec intervals. See individual aircraft dataset descriptions for further information and contacts.

title: CaPE Lightning Location and Protection
summary: The LLP network provided data on the location, time, and  characteristics (polarity and stoke multiplicity) of  cloud-to-ground lightning events determined from a solution of various fixed stations. A 6-station smaller scale  network is located at KSC and a larger scale network is  throughout Florida as part of the national network.  Record per lightning strike.

title: CaPE NASA/KSC LDAR
summary: NASA/KSC implemented a new Lightning Detection And Ranging  (LDAR) system in the KSC/CCAFS area. LDAR is a seven-stationVHF, time of arrival network (100 microsecond) capable of   detecting both cloud-to-ground and intra-cloud lightning in 3 dimensions.

title: CaPE Rocket Triggered Lightning & Sondes
summary: A RTLP campaign overlapped with CaPE from August through September at the water" site on Mosquito Lagoon.  Two  rocket systems were used: French classical
archive_note: unspooling  triggering wire (1-1.5 km) and U.S. Army folding fin  aircraft rockets (5-6 km).  Data includes return stroke  current waveforms (5-10 ns per sample) and continuing  current waveforms (1 microsecond). "

title: CaPE New Mexico Insitute of Mines and Technology Wideband Electric Field-Change Data
summary: NMIMT installed a variable gain Wideband Field Change Recording System station at KSC (2 km from the RTLP site). Data was collected to support RTLP as well as coordinated storm measurements with CaPE investigators. Wideband (2MHz)measurements of electric field during entire lightning flash

title: STORM-FEST NASA ER-2 Aircraft Data
summary: NASA/Ames Research Center operated an ER-2 stratospheric jet (max altitude 65 kft).  Nine flights were taken during  STORM-FEST from 14 February to 14 March.  Data was collectedby Millimeter Imaging Radiometer, Advanced Microwave  Precipitation Radiometer, Lightning Instrument Package, Highresolution Interferometer Sounder, Microwave Temperature Sounder and the Wildfire Spectrometer.

title: CaPE ACARS Data

title: VORTEX-94 NOAA WP-3D Aircraft Data

The aircraft routinely measures flight level state  parameters (temperature, moisture and winds) and basic  microphysical variables (liquid water and PMS probe data)  as well as data collected by its two radars.

title: VORTEX SDSMT T-28 Aircraft Data
summary: SDSMT T-28 aircraft was used to document the microphysical characteristics of storms in the Cimarron radar coverage area.  Microphysical and electrical characteristics were measured using a variety of instruments in the updraft and lower anvil regions.  Flight levels vary from 10000-25000 ft
