title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 DRI CCN and CN Data (Horizontal legs) (Hudson)
summary: Cloud Condensation Nuclei (CCN) and Condensation Nuclei (CN) measurements obtained by the Desert Research Institute (DRI - Hudson) from the NCAR C-130 during ACE-1. Concentrations are per cubic centimeter normalized to sea-level pressure. The data presented here are ambient, unprocessed measurements. All other measurements that were obtained during the project have been removed from these files. These data were obtained during approximately horizontal flight legs. A companion dataset is available that contains data only for the cloud-free portions of these legs.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 DRI CCN and CN Data (Horizontal legs - Cloud Free) (Hudson)
summary: Cloud Condensation Nuclei (CCN) and Condensation Nuclei (CN) measurements obtained by the Desert Research Institute (DRI - Hudson) from the NCAR C-130 during ACE-1. Concentrations are per cubic centimeter normalized to sea-level pressure. The data presented here are ambient, unprocessed measurements. All other measurements that were obtained during the project have been removed from these files. These data were obtained during approximately horizontal flight legs when the aircraft was outside of clouds. A companion dataset is available that contains in-cloud and cloud free data.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 DRI CCN and CN Data (Aircraft Soundings) (Hudson)
summary: Cloud Condensation Nuclei (CCN) and Condensation Nuclei (CN) measurements obtained by the Desert Research Institute (DRI - Hudson) from the NCAR C-130 during ACE-1. Concentrations are per cubic centimeter normalized to sea-level pressure. The data presented here are ambient, unprocessed measurements. All other measurements that were obtained during the project have been removed from these files. These data were obtained during aircraft soundings. A companion dataset is available that contains data for only the cloud-free portions of these soundings.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 DRI CCN and CN Data (Aircraft Soundings - Cloud Free) (Hudson)
summary: Cloud Condensation Nuclei (CCN) and Condensation Nuclei (CN) measurements obtained by the Desert Research Institute (DRI - Hudson) from the NCAR C-130 during ACE-1. Concentrations are per cubic centimeter normalized to sea-level pressure. The data presented here are ambient, unprocessed measurements. All other measurements that were obtained during the project have been removed from these files. These data were obtained during aircraft soundings. A companion dataset is available that contains both in-cloud and cloud free data for these soundings.

title: Aircraft C-130 OH, H2SO4, MSA Measurements (Eisele)
summary: This dataset consists of measurements of OH, H2SO4, and MSA made from the C-130 aircraft during ACE-1. This dataset differs from the preliminary one in several ways. First, the calibration for OH was changed. Previously a value of 5.5 x 10-20 molec/cm2 was used for the H2O absoption cross section at 1849 nm. Recent work however at NCAR and Harvard indicate that the reported value should be higher. A value of 7.2 x 10-20 molec/cm2 was used in this analysis. Secondly, the values presented in the preliminary dataset were calculated using a calibration constant measured at sea-level, where an altitude dependent calibration constant was used in this analysis.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 RCAD Aerosol Measurements PRELIMINARY (Russell)
summary: This dataset contains measurements of aerosol size distribution made with the Radially-Classified Aerosol Detector (RCAD) aboard the C-130 Aircraft during ACE-1.

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 SO2 and DMS Measurements (Bandy)
summary: This dataset consists of measurements of SO2 and DMS obtained by gas chromatography - mass spectrometry aboard the C130 aircraft during ACE-1. The samples for SO2 and DMS were independent but were collected simultaneously. The precision of the measurements is about 1 part-per-trillion by volume (pptv). Data are available for flights 11-28.

title: CaPE NASA ER-2 Data
summary: NASA/Ames Lockheed ER-2 is a stratospheric recon jet and wasavailable from 18 July - 17 August 1991.  In addition to    housekeeping parameters, there are 3 primary instrument     packages: MAMS, AMPR and LIP.  Secondary instrumentation    included HIS and MTS.  Resolution depends on the instrument package.

title: CaPE SDSMT T-28 Aircraft Data
summary: SMT North American T-28 is specially armored and was available for all of CaPE.  Measurements included  housekeeping and state parameters, particle spectra, liquid water content, rain/precipitation particles, ice/water  discrimination photography and 2-3 components of the  electric field vector all with 1 second resolution.

title: Western Arctic Biomass Data
summary: This data consists of compiled bethic biomass from the northern Bering, Chukchi, East Siberian and Beaufort seas for input into ArcView, a Geographical Information System (GIS). The data are in Microsoft Access 2000 format. For more information, please see the readme file.

title: Arctic Nutrient Database 1997-1998 (Ruble)
summary: This data set contains water salinity, PO4, SiO3, NO2, NO3, and NH4 content measured at various Arctic stations. For more information, please see the readme file. This data set is in Microsoft Access 2000 format.

title: DYCOMS-II Aircraft: C-130 Cloud Condensation Nuclei (CCN) Level-I Data (Snider)
summary: The Cloud Condensation Nuclei (CCN) Level-I Data is one of several data sets collected as part of the Dynamics and Chemistry of Marine Stratocumulus Phase II: Entrainment Studies (DYCOMS-II) project. Included in the data set are CCN data from 10 research flights (mostly at night) and one test flight. The CCN data are availible for the complete duration of all research flights where the altitude does not exceed 2000 m. The data cover the period from 7 - 28 July.

title: DYCOMS-II Aircraft: C-130 Cloud Droplet Spectrum Fast-FSSP (Brenguier/Burnet)
summary: Fast-FSSP (FFSSP) data were acquired during the DYCOMS-II field campaign in Summer 20001. There were 10 research flights studying stratus clouds. FFSSP data is available for almost the complete duration of the last 8 flights (from RF03 to RF10) except for flights RF04 and RF08 for which some cloudy legs are missing. Available time sections for each flight are listed in Table 1 of the readme file.

title: DYCOMS-II Aircraft: Dimethyl Sulfide (DMS) Data
summary: The DYCOMS-II Aircraft: Dimethyl Sulfide dataset is one of several aircraft data sets collected on the C-130 aircraft as part of the Dynamics and Chemistry of Marine Stratocumulus Phase II:  Entrainment Studies (DYCOMS-II) project.  Dimethyl Sulfide measurements were taken onboard the NSF/NCAR C-130 from July 10-July 28, 2001. Data is in .txt format.

title: C-130 Cloud Counterflow Virtual Impactor (Twohy)
summary: The DYCOMS-II Aircraft: Cloud Counterflow Virtual Impactor (CVI) dataset is one of several aircraft data sets collected on the C-130 aircraft as part of the Dynamics and Chemistry of Marine Stratocumulus Phase II: Entrainment Studies (DYCOMS-II) project. Cloud droplet number (as number of residual particles after evaporation) and condensed water content measurements were taken using the CVI onboard the NSF/NCAR C-130 from July 13-July 28, 2001. Data are columnar ascii format.

title: DYCOMS-II Aircraft: C-130 Aerosol LAS-AIR Optical Particle Counter (Twohy)
summary: The LAS-AIR is a commercial instrument (PMS Model 1001) that measured the size distribution of particles between about 0.1 to > 3 microns diameter in 8 size channels. During DYCOMS, the LAS-AIR was one of a number of instruments sampling off the solid diffuser inlet (SDI) which was mounted on the right side of the C-130 aircraft. To dry the sample and prevent coincidence at high concentrations, the LAS-AIR sample stream was diluted with dry nitrogen in a 5:1 ratio (5 parts N2 to 1 part sample). All flow rates were monitored and maintained with constant volume flow controllers. The LAS-AIR samples over a 6 sec interval, so the data rate is once every 6 seconds. Rather than using the manufacturer's calibration, size limits were calibrated using monodisperse ammonium sulfate aerosol. Additional information on the LAS-AIR itself can be found on the PMS website at http://www.pmeasuring.com/particle/products/aerosol/docs/lasair

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Aerosol Single particle aerosol composition (Prather)
summary: The Ship Ron Brown Aerosol Single particle aerosol composition dataset is an offline data set.  The files are in several formats, on CD-ROMs.

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Meteorology Rawinsonde (Johnson)
summary: This dataset consists of rawinsonde data collected during  the ACE-ASIA cruise of the NOAA Ship Ron Brown. Each datafile contains the ships location, the sonde's UTC release time, and a vertical profile of pressure, temperature, humidity,  latitude and longitude, total wind speed and direction,  and U and V wind components, every 10 seconds during the  sonde's ascent.

title: ACE-1: Model Trajectories, Back NCEP MRF for Discoverer Transit (ASCII) (Kapustin)
summary: This dataset contains Back trajectories for the R/V Discoverer. These trajectories were calculated with the NOAA HYSPLIT 3.2 code using the NMC Global Data Assimilation System Medium Range Forecast model (MRF). 9-day back trajectories are computed at 00Z and 12Z daily, originating at the ship with a source altitude of 100 m and an averaging period of 24 hrs. This dataset contains ASCII files which describe the latitude, longitude and pressure level of trajectory points. A companion dataset contains gif images of each of these trajectories.

title: ACE-1: Model Trajectories, Back NCEP MRF for Discoverer Transit (GIF) (Kapustin)
summary: This dataset contains Back trajectories for the R/V Discoverer. These trajectories were calculated with the NOAA HYSPLIT 3.2 code using the NMC Global Data Assimilation System Medium Range Forecast model (MRF). 9-day back trajectories are computed at 00Z and 12Z daily, originating at the ship with a source altitude of 100 m and an averaging period of 24 hrs. This dataset contains GIF images of each trajectory. A companion dataset includes ASCII listings of latitude, longitude, and pressure for each trajectory point.

title: ACE-1: Model Trajectories, Back BoM GASP (C130) divergence rates and subs. velocities (Siems)
summary: Divergence rates and subsidence velocities were calculated for times during ACE-1 when the C-130 was flying cirles in the boundary layer. These were calculated by simply following the actual subsidence/ascent on numerical (GASP/HYSPLIT) trajectories. These values agree well with the synoptic meteorology.

title: ACE-1: Model Trajectories, Back BoM GASP (C130) for Huebert's suggested avging times (Siems)

title: GOES-East Mid- to Upper-level Wind Imagery (derived from WV and IR channels) [Bates]
summary: This is the Mid- to Upper-level Wind imagery data derived from the WV and IR channels and collected from the GOES-8 satellite during the EPIC time period.

title: NOAA P-3 Meteorology Lower Fuselage C-Band Radar Composite Imagery [NOAA/AOC]
summary: This dataset consists of composite radar data analysis. It contains reflectivity maps composed from data collected by the tail radar onboard the P3-N43 during EPIC-2001.

title: Ron Brown Near-Surface Mean Meteorology and Fluxes (5-min) - Leg 1 [Fairall]
summary: This dataset contains data collected aboard the ship Ron Brown for EPIC. The data are made up of computations of bulk meteorological variables and fluxes derived from the ETL system based on preliminary analysis done during Leg 1 of the EPIC2001 cruise. Most quantities given are subject to future modification based on accounting for other sources of data and revised calibrations. No direct turbulent flux calculations are included in this present data.

title: Ron Brown Near-Surface Mean Meteorology and Fluxes (5-min) - Leg 2 [Fairall]
summary: This dataset contains data collected aboard the ship Ron Brown for EPIC. The data are made up of computations of bulk meteorological variables and fluxes derived from the ETL system based on preliminary analysis done during Leg 2 of the EPIC2001 cruise. Most quantities given are subject to future modification based on accounting for other sources of data and revised calibrations. No direct turbulent flux calculations are included in this present data.

title: Ron Brown Near-Surface Mean Meteorology and Fluxes (30-min) - Leg 1 and Leg 2 [Fairall]
summary: This dataset contains computations of bulk meteorological variables and fluxes derived  the ETL system based on preliminary analysis done during Leg 1 and Leg 2 of the EPIC2001 cruise and the PACS TAO maintenance cruise that followed.  Most quantities given are subject to future modification based on accounting for other sources of data and revised calibrations.  No direct turbulent flux calculations are included in this present data.

title: Ron Brown Meteorology Ceilometer - Leg 2 [Weller]
summary: This dataset contains hourly ceilometer data, 10 minute ceilometer data, 15 second ceilometer data, and cloud fraction statistics. The hourly ceilometer data, 10 minute ceilometer data, and cloud fraction statistics were generated from the 15 second ceilometer data. The dataset was collected during leg 2 of the EPIC2001 cruise.

title: Ron Brown Cruise Reports - Leg 1 [Fairall]
summary: This report documents the work done on cruise RB-01-08 of the NOAA R/V Ron Brown. This was Leg 1 of R/V Ron Brown's participation in Eastern Pacific Investigation of Climate (EPIC) 2001, a study of air-sea interaction, the atmosphere, and the upper ocean in the eastern tropical Pacific. The science party included groups from the Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution (WHOI), NOAA Environmental Technology Laboratory (ETL), the University of Washington (UW), the University of California, Santa Barbara (UCSB), and the University Nacional Autonoma de Mexico (UNAM). This is a collection of 7 reports submitted to JOSS from various groups.

title: Ron Brown Cruise Reports - Leg 2 [Weller]
summary: This report documents the work done on cruise RB-01-08 of the NOAA R/V Ron Brown. This was Leg 2 of R/V Ron Brown's participation in Eastern Pacific Investigation of Climate (EPIC) 2001, a study of air-sea interaction, the atmosphere, and the upper ocean in the eastern tropical Pacific. The science party included groups from the Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution (WHOI), NOAA Environmental Technology Laboratory (ETL), the University of Washington (UW), the University of California, Santa Barbara (UCSB), and the University Nacional Autonoma de Mexico (UNAM). The work done by these groups is summarized in this report. In addition, the routine underway data collected while aboard R/V Ron Brown is also summarized here.

title: Ron Brown Meteorology Ceilometer - Leg 1 [Fairall]
summary: This dataset contains hourly ceilometer data, 10 minute ceilometer data, 15 second ceilometer data, and cloud fraction statistics. The hourly ceilometer data, 10 minute ceilometer data, and cloud fraction statistics were generated from the 15 second ceilometer data. The dataset was collected during leg 1 of the EPIC2001 cruise.

title: NSF C-130 Aerosol UNAM Aerosol Measurement System [Baumgardner]
summary: This dataset consists of UNAM aerosol measurement system data taken aboard the NCAR C-130 aircraft.

title: Ron Brown Meteorology Lidar Mini-MOPA Doppler - Leg 1 [Intrieri]
summary: Vertical Profiles of wind velocity and direction are produced from doppler lidar mearsurements taken aboard the Ron Brown from Sept 12 to Oct 05 2001.  The VAD technique (Browning and Wexler, 1968) was employed to process wind information taken in scanning mode to produce the high-resolution vertical profiles. All velocities are in m/s and heights in meter.

title: Ron Brown Meteorology Lidar Mini-MOPA Doppler - Leg 2 [Intrieri]
summary: Vertical Profiles of wind velocity and direction are produced from doppler lidar mearsurements taken aboard the Ron Brown from Oct 08 to Oct 22 2001.  The VAD technique (Browning and Wexler, 1968) was employed to process wind information taken in scanning mode to produce the high-resolution vertical profiles. All velocities are in m/s and heights in meter.

title: QuikSCAT SeaWinds Raw Data [OSU]
summary: This dataset contains EPIC 2001 satellite QuikSCAT SeaWinds raw data in ASCII format from 10 September to 24 October 2001.

title: QuikSCAT Smoothed Data [OSU]
summary: This dataset contains EPIC 2001 satellite QuikSCAT SeaWinds smoothed data from 10 September to 24 October 2001.

title: TRMM [OSU]
summary: This dataset contains EPIC 2001 satellite TRMM data from 10 September to 24 October 2001.

title: NOAA P-3 Oceanography AXBT Profiles [RSMAS]
summary: The EPIC Aircraft P-3 Oceanography AXBT Profiles (RSMAS) dataset is one of several datasets archived by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS) in support of the Eastern Pacific Investigation of Climate (EPIC) project. These data were collected and Quality Controlled by the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration Aircraft Operations Center P-3 Aircraft. The Probe type for this DataSet was AXBT - Airborne eXpendable BathyThermograph. No additional Quality Control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: Galapagos Meteorology Observations [NOAA/AL]
summary: The EPIC Surface Based Galapagos Meteorology Observations (NOAA/AL) dataset is one of several datasets archived by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS) in support of the Eastern Pacific Investigation of Climate (EPIC) project. These data were collected by the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration Aeronomy Lab wind Profiler. No Quality Control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: PSU 1-km Multi-Layer Soil Characteristics Dataset
summary: Pennsylvania State University (PSU)/Earth System Science Center (ESSC) has developed a 1-km multi-layer soil characteristics dataset based on the USDA STATSGO data. The data includes STATSGO Mapunits, soil texture class, depth-to-bedrock, sand/silt/clay fractions, rock fragment class, rock fragment volume, bulk density, porosity, hydrologic soil groups, and available water capacity. This data set is available at PSU via the "download" link below.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Sky Camera (Cloud) Images (Johnson)
summary: This data set contains images of the sky at 30 minute intervals as seen from the NOAA ship R/V Discoverer during the Aerosol Characterization Experiment -1 (ACE-1) project. Images are included during the transit from Seattle as well as in the main project area around Tasmania. These data are in jpg image format and were provided by NOAA/PMEL.

title: CPTEC Control Analysis (initial data for experiment 4)
summary:
This data set is provided by the CPTEC/INPE-Brazil and contains the initial and boundary conditions in binary files to be used as input to the models for experiment #4. A GRADS control file is included.

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: Meteorology CPTEC (Brazil) Reanalysis Subset of Global Model
summary:
This data set is provided by the CPTEC/INPE-Brazil and contains the Forecast Products model Reanalysis output data (control and data files) as part of the South American Low Level Jet Experiment (SALLJEX).

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: Mexican CICESE R/V Francisco de Ulloa CTD Data
summary: This dataset contains Conductivity-Temperature-Depth (CTD) data for the NAME cruises of the CICESE Research Vessel (R/V) Francisco de Ulloa in the Gulf of California.  The cruise lasted from 5 June to 18 June 2004 and 7  July to 20 July 2004.  There are 370 CTD measurements included in this dataset.

title: Mexican UNAM R/V El Puma Aerosol Data
summary:
This data set is collected from the Mexican Navy ship El Puma.  Data were collected roughly every 8 hours
and consist of a single Excel file listing Date, Time and CO2 concentration in ppb.  Niskin bottles from a CTD-Rosette system provided sampled from between surface to 30-60 meters and above the mixed layer.

title: Buoy 32302 (18.0S 85.1W) Meteorological Data [NOAA/NDBC]
summary: This data set contains moored buoy data from station 32302 located at 18.0S Latitude and 85.1W Longitude covering the time period from Feb 01,1986 thru Apr 03,1995. The data was obtained from the National Data Buoy Center. This dataset is one of many archived by the University Corporation of Atmospheric Research/Joint Office Of Science Support (UCAR/JOSS) in support of the Pan American Climate Studies (PACS) program. These data have undergone no quality control.  See the README for more details.

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: Precipitation NCEP/EMC 4 KM Gridded Dataset (GRIB)
summary:
This dataset is now available online under the GCIP/EOP project via the following NCEP 4 KM GRIB datasets:
  • gage-only analysis(pre-2002) (2002-present)
  • multi-sensor analysis (gage and unbiased radar)(pre-2002) (2002-present)
  • radar estimate (pre-2002) (2002-present)
  • radar estimate after bias removal (pre-2002) (2002-present)
    and
  • gage-only analysis using 24 hour accumulated (RFC") data (pre-2002) (2002-present)

This dataset contains the National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP) Climate Prediction Center (CPC) 4 KM GRIB dataset. A prototype
end_date: multi-sensor National Preciptation Analysis (NPA) has been developed at NCEP in cooperation with the Office of Hydrology (OH).  This analysis merges two data sources that are currently being collected in real-time by OH and NCEP.  Hourly digital precipitation (HDP) radar estimates are created by the WSR-88D Radar Product Generator on a 131 X 131 4-km grid centered over each radar site. Data analysis routines
minimum_latitude: including a bias correction of the radar estimates using rain gage data
minimum_longitude: have been adapted by NCEP on a national 4-km grid from algorithms developed by OH and executed regionally at NWS River Forecast Centers (RFC). This dataset contains the NCEP 4 KM GRIB Data including multi-sensor analysis (gage and unbiased radar)
spatial_type: and radar estimate after bias removal. Depending on the time period selected
frequency_id: all four types may or may not be available. Please see GCIP/EOP: Surface NCEP Ancillary Catalogue of Available GCIP Precipitation Data (NCEP/CPC). This dataset is provided as is and was not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS."

title: GCIP/EOP Surface: Precipitation NCEP/EMC Preview Imagery (GIF)
summary:
*** Please note that this dataset is now available online under the GCIP/EOP project at GCIP/EOP Surface: Precipitation NCEP/CPC Preview Imagery (GIF) 1998-2001 and GCIP/EOP Surface: Precipitation NCEP/CPC Preview Imagery (GIF) 2002-present. ***

This dataset contains the National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP) Climate Prediction Center (CPC) GIF Imagery including Hourly Stage IV GIF, Daily Stage IV GIF, and Daily RFC GIF. Depending on the time period selected, all three GIF types may or may not be available. Please see the GCIP/EOP: Surface NCEP Ancillary Catalogue of Available GCIP Precipitation Data (NCEP/CPC). This dataset is provided as is and was not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS.

title: Council Climate NCAR ISS RASS Virtual Temperatures (ASCII)
summary: This dataset contains Radio Acoustic Sounding System (RASS) virtual temperatures collected at the Council, Seward Peninsula, Tundra Site (C2) during the Arctic Transitions in the Land-Atmosphere System (ATLAS) program 1999 summer field campaign. These data were collected by the National Center for Atmospheric Research (NCAR) Atmospheric Technology Division (ATD) Integrated Sounding System (ISS). These data are available in ASCII text files and have not been quality controlled.

title: Council Climate NCAR ISS 915 Mhz Profiler Winds (ASCII)
summary: This dataset contains 30 minute consensus winds data collected at the Council, Seward Peninsula, Tundra Site (C2) during the Arctic Transitions in the Land-Atmosphere System (ATLAS) program, 1999 summer field campaign. These data were collected by the National Center for Atmospheric Research (NCAR) Atmospheric Technology Division (ATD) 915 MHz wind profiler as part of the Integrated Sounding System (ISS). These data are available in ASCII text format and have not been quality controlled.

title: Council Climate NCAR ISS RASS Virtual Temperatures for Tundra Site (C2) (ASCII)
summary: This dataset contains vertical profiles of virtual temperature collected at the Tundra Site (C2) on the Council, Seward Peninsula during the Arctic Transitions in the Land-Atmosphere System (ATLAS) project, 2000 summer field campaign. These data were collected by the National Center for Atmospheric Research (NCAR) Atmospheric Technology Division (ATD) using the Integrated Sounding System (ISS) Radio Acoustic Sounding System (RASS). These data are available in ASCII text format and have not been quality controlled.

title: Council Climate NCAR ISS 915 Mhz Profiler Winds for Tundra Site(C2)(ASCII)
summary: This dataset contains 30 minute consensus winds data collected at the Council, Seward Peninsula, Tundra Site (C2) during the Arctic Transitions in the Land-Atmosphere System (ATLAS) program, 2000 summer field campaign. These data are available in ASCII text format and have not been quality controlled.

title: Council Climate NCAR ISS High Resolution Soundings for Tundra Site(C2)(ASCII)
summary: This dataset contains rawinsonde derived atmospheric profiles taken at the Tundra Site (C2) on the Council, Seward Peninsula for the Arctic Transitions in the Land-Atmosphere System (ATLAS) project during the 2000 summer field campaign. The data were collected by the National Center for Atmospheric Research (NCAR) Atmospheric Technology Division (ATD) using NCAR's integrated sounding system (ISS). The sonde files contain vertical profiles of pressure, temperature, relative humidity, dew point, wind speed and direction, U and V wind components, altitude, and position (latitude and longitude), measured every second during the sonde's ascent. Data is available on the following days: June 29-30, July 1, 2, and 6-12. See the README for additional information.

title: Ron Brown Meteorology Rawinsonde (hi-res) - Leg 1 [Petersen]
summary: This Dataset consists of rawinsonde data collected during the EPIC cruise of the NOAA Ship Ron Brown. Each datafile contains the ships location, the sonde's UTC release time, and a vertical profile of pressure, temperature, humidity,  latitude and longitude, total wind speed and direction,  and U and V wind components, every two seconds during the  sonde's ascent.

title: Ron Brown Radiation Fluxes - Leg 1, Leg 2 (BNL) [Reynolds]
summary: This dataset contains data collected aboard the ship Ron Brown for EPIC. This dataset includes four files:  rb0108_rad.txt -- ship nav, longwave (PSP), longwave (PIR), pitch/roll; rb0108_frsr -- Fast Rotating Shadowband Radiometer data: global  and sky irradiances, aerosol optical thickness (AOT) (415, 500, 610, 670,870, 940 nm); summary_rad.jpg -- data summary plot; track_rb0108.jpg -- trackline. Please see the readme orhttp://www.gim.bnl.gov/cruises/index.html for additional information.

title: Ron Brown SCS Data - Leg 1 [Fairall]
summary: This dataset contains data from the two 'messages' requested for recording by the EPIC group (WHOI-ETL and RAIN). The data are at 2-s time resolution and there are 'HDR' files that describe what variables are archived. For more information please see the following web site: http://www.etl.noaa.gov/programs/2001/epic

title: Ron Brown SCS Data - Leg 2 [Fairall]
summary: This dataset contains data from the two 'messages' requested for recording by the EPIC group (WHOI-ETL and RAIN). title: Ron Brown Meteorology Microwave Radiometer (20, 31, 90 GHz) - Leg 1 [Fairall]

During Leg 1 of R/V Ron Brown's participation in Eastern Pacific Investigation of Climate (EPIC) 2001. The readme contains information on the formating of the data, please see http://www.etl.noaa.gov/programs/2001/epic for more information.

title: Ron Brown Meteorology merged Microwave Radiometer/Ceilometer - Leg 2 [Fairall]

During Leg 2 of R/V Ron Brown's participation in Eastern Pacific Investigation of Climate (EPIC) 2001. Please see http://www.etl.noaa.gov/programs/2001/epic for more information.

title: Ron Brown Cruise Tracks - Leg 1 and Leg 2 [Fairall]
summary: This dataset contains 2 JPEG images of the paths taken by the NOAA R/V Ron Brown. During both Legs 1 and 2 of R/V Ron Brown's participation in Eastern Pacific Investigation of Climate (EPIC) 2001. Please see http://www.etl.noaa.gov/programs/2001/epic for more information.

title: NOAA P-3 Meteorology Dropsonde Profiles [NOAA/AOC]
summary: The EPIC Aircraft:P-3 Meteorology Dropsonde Profiles dataset (NOAA/AOC) is one of several archived by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS) in support of the Eastern Pacific Investigation of Climate (EPIC) project. The data were collected and provided by The National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration/Aircraft Operations Center (NOAA/AOC). This dataset contains 0.5 second vertical resolution profiles derived from dropsondes released from the NOAA-P3 aircraft during EPIC. Dropsondes were released during aircraft flights on the following days: September 2001(3, 5, 9, 13, 16, 20, 21, and 28) and October 2001(3, 5, 6, and 7).

title: Ron Brown Meteorology Rawinsonde (hi-res) - Leg 2 [Yuter]
summary: This Dataset consists of rawinsonde data collected during the EPIC cruise of the NOAA Ship Ron Brown. Each datafile contains the ships location, the sonde's UTC release time, and a vertical profile of pressure, temperature, humidity,  latitude and longitude, total wind speed and direction,  and U and V wind components, every one seconds during the  sonde's ascent. Consult the README for more information. Note:A new version of this dataset was provided by The University of Washington in September 2003. This version replaces the original dataset. The most significant difference between the new and old  versions of the NOAA Ship Ron Brown Rawinsonde data is that the newer version contains corrected lat/lon positions.

title: Ron Brown Meteorology Navigation - Leg 2 [Weller]
summary: This Dataset consists of navigation data collected during the EPIC cruise of the NOAA Ship Ron Brown.

title: Ron Brown and IMET WHOI Buoy Data [Weller]
summary: This Dataset consists of Improved Meteorology (IMET) buoy data collected during the EPIC cruise of the NOAA Ship Ron Brown. The buoy is located at 20.15S 85.15W.

title: Ron Brown Oceanography CTD - Leg 2 [Weller]
summary: This Dataset consists of Conductivity, Temperature and Depth (CTD) system data collected during the EPIC cruise of the NOAA Ship Ron Brown.

title: Ron Brown Oceanography Thermosalinograph - Leg 2 [Weller]

title: Ron Brown Meteorology Satellite GOES 8 - Leg 2 [Weller]

title: Ron Brown Oceanography ADCP - Leg 2 [Weller]
summary: This dataset consists of Acoustic Doppler Current Profiler (ADCP) data collected during the EPIC cruise of the NOAA Ship Ron Brown.

title: NOAA P-3 Meteorology Doppler Radar Data [NMT]
summary: This data set contains meteorological doppler radar data from the P-3 aircraft.  It contains the data from 12 flight missions.  For more information see http://merlin.nmt.edu/projects/epic2001/aircraft/.

title: Mexico SMN-CNA Automated Weather Station Data
summary: This dataset contains data from the Mexico Servicio Meteorólogico Nacional (SMN) - Comisión Nacional Del Agua (CNA).  Plesase see the readme file or the SMN-CNA web site http://smn.cna.gob.mx for more information.  The readme is in spanish.

title: NODC Buoy Data
summary:
This dataset contains data from the NOAA Marine Environmental Buoy Database (NODC File 291). It contains wind, wave, and other marine data collected by the NOAA National Data Buoy Center (NDBC). The data are collected frrom NDBC moored buoys and from C-MAN (Coastal-Marine Automated Network) stations.

For more information see the NODC buoy page at http://www.nodc.noaa.gov/BUOY/buoy.html.

title: Interpolated Global Lagrangian Drifter Buoy Data [NOAA/AOML]
summary:
This dataset contains satellite-tracked drifting buoy data that were collected by numerous investigators and agencies in several conuntries for the World Ocean Circulation Experiment-Tropical Oceans Global Atmosphere (WOCE-TOGA) Surface Velocity Program.

For more information see the AOML/NOAA web page at http://www.aoml.noaa.gov/phod/dac/dacdata.html.

title: Mexico Navy SEMAR Automated Weather Station Data
summary:
This dataset contains automated weather station data from the Mexican Navy SEMAR stations that are located along the coast of Mexico and its islands.

More information on the network can be found at http://meteorologia.semar.gob.mx/. This web site is in Spanish.

title: Global Drifter Program (GDP) Data Assembly Center (DAC) GTS Buoy Data [NOAA/AOML]

title: NOAA P-3 Radar Data (Lower Fuselage C-band and Tail X-band) [AOC]
summary: This dataset contains the Aircraft P-3 Data for Doppler X-Band (Tail) Radar Radial Reflectivity, Doppler X-Band (Tail) Radar Radial Velocity and Lower Fuselage C-Band Radar Data. Data is grouped into one minute files and they are viewable using Solo software available through UCAR/ATD. This is the raw radar data.

title: Ocean Forest Oil Weather Station Data
summary: This data set consists of a single file of hourly resolution surface meteorological and  oceanographic data from the Forest Oil (http://www.forestoil.com) fixed structure weather station.  The station is mainted by ESSI Corporation (http:www.essicorp.com) and is located off the Texas coast from Galveston.  These data were retrieved from the National Data Buoy Center (NDBC).  This data  set covers the period from 1 January to 29 August 2005.  The data are in space delimited ASCII format.  NCAR/EOL has conducted no additional quality control of these data.

title: 3-hourly Visible Imagery over Continental South America (archive)

If you cannot access HPSS and want to order this data, please send an email to codiac AT ucar.edu

title: WSI, dropsondes, MGLASS animated composite imagery
summary: These composite images of sonde times and storm tracks superimposed on WSI radar contain sets of images for each BAMEX IOP. Animations are available from MMM http://locust.mmm.ucar.edu/bamex/

title: ACE-1: Aircraft C-130 SABL Flight Summaries (GIF Images at RSF/ATD/NCAR) (Morely)
summary: SABL data are now online through RSF/ATD/NCAR as GIF images.

title: CASES-97: Argonne ABLE Data and Imagery (wind profiler,RASS,sodar,NDVI) (Link to ANL)
summary: Information on ABLE instrumentation and performance as well as browse imagery is available via a link to the Argonne National Laboratory (ANL) ABLE Data Archive site. Wind profiler, RASS, sodar data, and NDVI data and NDVI readme file are located there. Imagery is available there for the Whitewater, Beaumont, Oxford, and Smileyberg profilers, as well as for several ARM profilers, and the OSU rainguages.

title: CASES-97: Surface PAM/ASTER Information and Browse Imagery (Link to NCAR/SSSF)
summary: Information on PAM/ASTER instrumentation and performance as well as browse imagery for the CASES-97 project is available via a link to the NCAR/SSSF site. This data was last updated on June 5, 2000. NOTE: This link to NCAR/SSSF has changed as of February 26, 2001. The new page shows available information on PAM/ASTER instruments and data.

title: OKMESO Meteorological Data (original OCS format)
summary: This dataset contains Oklahoma Mesonet 5-Minute and 15-minute Surface Data. OCS quality control flags are included in the data. The format is described in the readme file. This dataset is password protected. For password information, please see the contact for this dataset.

title: ACE-ASIA Aircraft: C-130 Aerosol Mass of organic and elemental carbon < 1um (Huebert)
summary: The ACE-ASIA Aircraft: C-130 Aerosol Mass of organic and elemental carbon <1um (Huebert) data are available online.  Data is in txt format. This dataset has been updated 12 May 2004.  For details, see the README file.

title: ACE-ASIA Surface: Gosan Aerosol Optical Measurements (Ogren/Jefferson)
summary: The ACE-Asia Surface Kosan Aerosol Neph/humido/radiometers/filters (Ogren/Jefferson) data are now available online. This data contains aerosol light scattering and absorption coefficients taken at the Kosan measurement site on Cheju Island, South Korea from April 5, 2001 to June 26, 2001. This dataset was updated May 16, 2003.

title: ACE-ASIA Surface: Asia Lidar Observation at TUMM/Tokyo (Data) (Murayama)
summary: This dataset contains ground-based lidar observations of aerosols by Aerosol lidar for April 2001 in Tokyo at the Tokyo University of Mercantile Marine (TUMM), located in the Tokyo Bay area. All data is in .txt format. Updated April 3, 2002 Updated June 3, 2002 (added March and May data)

title: ACE-ASIA Surface: Asia Lidar Observation/Ceilometer Data at Amami by TUMM/NIES (Murayama/Sugimoto)
summary: This data set contains Ceilometer (Vaisala CT25K) backscatter data collected by TUMM/NIES/CCSR at Amami, Japan during APEX-E2 in April, 2001 in text matrix format.  The data were collected continuously from April 13, 2001 08:34 to April 26, 2001 03:42 UTC. Updated April 3, 2002

title: ACE-ASIA Aircraft: C-130 Auxiliary Sampler Bulk Aerosol Mass of Anions and Cations (Huebert)
summary: This data was collected from the NCAR/NSF C-130 during the ACE-Asia program.  It consists of samples collected using a 90mm auxiliary Teflon filter sampler (AUX) and analyzed using ion chromatography on site. This dataset has been updated 12 May 2004.  For details, see the README file.

title: Station List
summary: The International H20 Project (IHOP) 2002 data sets contain data collected from over six thousand stations in the IHOP 2002 domain and time period. The station information provided defines each station in the IHOP 2002 datasets with station location, name, frequency of observation, etc. Note that the IHOP 2002 Ancillary Station List was updated in January 2005. Hourly stations 16587401 MANSFIELD and 16624401 MINDEN had previously been omitted but are now included.

title: Mexico SMN-CNA Automated Weather Station Data [Creighton]
summary: This dataset contains automated weather station data from the Mexico Servicio Meteorólogico Nacional (SMN) - Comisión Nacional Del Agua (CNA). Please see the readme file or the SMN-CNA web site http://smn.cna.gob.mx for more information. The readme is in spanish. These data are in Excel format and replace the previously available ASCII dataset.

title: CEPEX Nadi High Resolution Soundings
summary: This dataset contains the 10-sec vertical resolution sounding data taken at Nadi, Fiji (WMO 91680) during CEPEX. Sounding schedule was 00, 06, and 12 (wind only) UTC daily. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: CEPEX Funafuti High Resolution Soundings
summary: This dataset contains the contact vertical resolution sounding data taken at Funafuti, Tuvalu (WMO 91643) during CEPEX. Sounding schedule was 00 and 12 (wind only) daily. Data was digitized from strip chart output.  This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: CEPEX Kwajalein High Resolution Soundings
summary: This dataset contains the 50-m vertical resolution sounding data taken at Kwajalein (WMO 91366) during CEPEX. Sounding schedule was 00 and 12 UTC daily. System used was a military Meteorological Sounding System (MSS). This dataset consists of pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: CEPEX GTS Operational Soundings
summary: This dataset contains the mandatory/significant level sounding data taken at CEPEX sounding stations during CEPEX. Sounding schedule was 00 and 12 daily. Data was extracted from the NCAR/SCD GTS database. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: CEPEX Lear Jet Dropsondes (NCAR)
summary: This dataset contains the 10-sec high resolution Dropsonde data taken from the Aeromet Lear Jet during CEPEX. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.

title: GCIP/EOP Sub-Surface: ARM SWATS Data (2002/07 version)
summary: The Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment (GEWEX)  Continental-scale International Project (GCIP) Enhanced  Observing Period (EOP) Department of Energy (DOE)  Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great  Plains (SGP) Soil Water and Temperature System (SWATS) data set is provided as is" and was not quality controlled by  UCAR/JOSS.    The Soil Water and Temperature System is designed to  provide information about the temperature of the soil and  the status of water in the soil profile. Sensors installed  at various depths below the soil surface provide hourly  measurements of soil temperature and estimates of soil-waterpotential and volumetric water content. SWATS systems are  installed at 21 of the ARM/SGP/CART Extended Facilities  (EFs).   Please see the README file for more complete information

title: Narrow Field of View (NFOV), AIMR, TMI, AVHRR Compilation Dataset [Valero]
summary: This data set is a compilation of 4 independent data sets acquired during the INDOEX Intensive Field Phase. Each data set has been averaged to a common time database corresponding to the duration of the NCAR C-130 aircraft. In the case of satellite measurements (TMI data from the TRMM satellite and AVHRR data aboard the NOAA-14 satellite), the data has also been co-located to the latitude/longitude location of the NCAR C-130 at the specified time.

title: SGP97 Upper Air: DOE ARM SGP AERI Vertical Profile Data
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation  Measurement (ARM) program operates an Atmospheric Emitted Radiance Interferometer (AERI) at the Central Facility of its Southern Great Plains site.  AERI provides vertical profiles every 8 min of temperature, dew point and water vapor mixing ratio.  For further information on this data set see the README file.

title: SGP97 Surface: DOE ARM SGP BSRN Radiation Data
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation  Measurement (ARM) program operates a Baseline Surface Radiation Network (BSRN) station at the Central Facility of its Southern Great Plains site.  BSRN provides 1-min observations of direct-beam normal solar irradiance, downwelling hemispheric diffuse solar irradiance,  downwelling hemispheric solar irradiance and downwelling hemispheric infrared irradiance.  For further information on this data set see the README file.

title: SGP97 Surface: DOE ARM SGP EBBR Data
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation  Measurement (ARM) program operates a network of 12 Energy Balance Bowen Ration (EBBR) stations at its Southern Great Plains site.  EBBR provides 30-min observations of latent and sensible heat flux along with net radiation, atmospheric pressure, bowen ratio, wind speed and direction,and the following parameters at five locations surrounding the sites:  soil moisture, soil temperature, soil heat flow,soil heat capacity and soil heat flow at the surface. For further information on this data set see the README file.

title: SGP97 Upper Air: DOE ARM SGP 915 MHz Profiler RASS
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) program operates 915 MHz profilers at the Central Facility and three Intermediate Facilities of its Southern Great Plains site. The 915 MHz profiler Radio Acoustic Sounding System (RASS) provides hourly vertical profiles of the virtual temperature. The measurements start at 0.097 km and continue up to 2.408 km with a vertical spacing of about 0.1 km. See the README and header portion of the netcdf file for futher information.

title: SGP97 Upper Air: DOE ARM SGP 915 MHz Profiler Winds
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation  Measurement (ARM) program operates a 915 MHz profiler site at the Central Facility and three intermediate facilities of its Southern Great Plains site. The 915 MHz profiler Radio Acoustic Sounding System (RASS) provides hourly vertical profiles of the components of the wind.  Both the high and low modes are included.  The low mode starts at 0.087 km and continues to 2.342 km with a vertical spacing of about 0.06 km.  The high modes starts at 0.318 km and continues to 6.187 km with a vertical  spacing of about 0.2 km.  See the README and header portion of the netcdf file for futher information.

title: SGP97 Upper Air: DOE ARM SGP 50 MHz Profiler RASS
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) program operates a 50 MHz profiler site at the Central Facility of its Southern Great Plains site. The 50 MHz profiler Radio Acoustic Sounding System (RASS) provides hourly vertical profiles of the virtual temperature. The measurements start at 2.19 km and continue up to 5.94 km with a vertical spacing of about 0.15 km. See the README and header portion of the netcdf file for futher information.

title: SGP97 Upper Air: DOE ARM SGP 50 MHz Profiler Winds
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation  Measurement (ARM) program operates a 50 MHz profiler site at the Central Facility of its Southern Great Plains site. The 50 MHz profiler provides hourly vertical profiles of the components of the wind.  Both high and low modes are included.  The low mode covers from 1.455 km to 8.442 km with a vertical spacing of about 0.3 km.  The high mode  covers from 2.576 km to 16.548 km with a vertical spacing of about 0.6 km.  See the README and header portion of the netcdf file for futher information.

title: CIRES Tethered Lifting System (netCDF) [Balsley]
summary: This dataset contains the CIRES Tethered Lifting System (TLS) data collected during CASES-99. The data are in netCDF format.

title: FMCW (UMASS) Radar Data [Fraiser]
summary: This dataset contains FMCW Data (in netCDF format) for all CASES-99 IOPs. A companion dataset (45.302) contains gif plots of these data at selected times during each IOP.

title: HRDL Lidar Data [Banta and Newsom]
summary: This dataset contains HRDL Data in netCDF collected during the CASES-99 Experiment near Leon, Kansas. For more information, please see the README file.

title: Eddy Correlation Data (RAW) [Hartogensis]
summary: This dataset contains NetCDF data collected by two eddy correlation systems, one at 10m height and the other at 3m. This data was collected at a sampling rate of 20Hz. Processed eddy correlation data is also available in a companion dataset(45.601)

title: COMET CASE 024 ACARS data
summary: This dataset contains ACARS data.                            Data is archived as netCDF files.

summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation  Measurement (ARM) program operates an Atmospheric Emitted Radiance Interferometer (AERI) at the Central Facility of its Southern Great Plains site.  AERI provides vertical profiles every 8 min of temperature, dew point and water vapor mixing ratio.  For further information on this data set see the README file.

title: SGP99 Upper Air: DOE ARM SGP MWR Vertical Profile Data
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation  Measurement (ARM) program operates an Microwave Radiometer (MWR) at the Central Facility of its Southern Great Plains site.  MWR provides hourly vertical profiles of cloud liquid water, water vapor density and absolute temperature.  For further information on this data set see the README file.

BSRN provides 1-min observations of direct-beam normal solar irradiance, downwelling hemispheric diffuse solar irradiance,  downwelling hemispheric solar irradiance and downwelling hemispheric infrared irradiance.  For further information on this data set see the README file.

title: SGP99 Surface: DOE ARM SGP SMOS Surface Meteorology Data
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation  Measurement (ARM) program operates Surface Meteorological Observation Stations (SMOS) at many of its Boundary Facilities at its Southern Great Plains site.  SMOS provides 1-min observations of surface meteorological parameters.  For further information on this data set see the README file.

title: COMET CASE 025 ACARS data
summary: This dataset contains ACARS data.                            Data is archived as netCDF files.

title: CEPEX ER-2 Navigation/State Parameters
summary: This dataset contains navigation and state parameter data from the ER-2 for 16 missions during CEPEX. The navigation data was taken from the ER-2 Inertial Navigation System (INS) with a satellite NBS time code receiver. Navigation parameters include: time, altitude, latitude, longitude, air speed, pitch, roll, ground speed, and angle of attack. The state parameters include: u,v,w wind components, total air temperature and pressure, static air temperature and pressure, computed wind, differential pressure, and  vertical velocity.

title: CEPEX ER-2 Lyman Alpha (Water Vapor)
summary: This dataset contains water vapor measurements from the  Harvard University Lyman Alpha instrument aboard the ER-2 for 9 missions during CEPEX. The instrument used the techniques of photofragment fluorescence combined with dual path absorption to measure water vapor concentrations ranging from 1013 to 1016 molecules/cubic centimeters at pressures from 50 to 500 mb. The detection scheme utilized the Lyman-Alpha photons (121.6 nanometers) to photo- dissociate water vapor and produce excited OH molecules which emit photons that are detected by a photomultiplier near 314 nanometers. Units are in ppmv. Principal Investigators were Weinstock, Dessler, Hintsa, and Anderson (Harvard University).

title: CEPEX ER-2 Ozone
summary: This dataset contains ozone measurements from the Harvard University Water Ozone Experiment (WOX) aboard the ER-2 for 9 missions during CEPEX. The ozone instrument  determined ozone by measuring the absorption of 253.7 nanometer radiation. Ambient air was alternately drawn through a scrubber that chemically removed ozone to determine a reference signal. The ozone signal was determined with ambient air flowing through the detection cell. Ozone concentration was then determined using Beer's law. Units are ppbv. Principal Investigators were  Weinstock, Dessler, Hintsa, and Anderson (Harvard Univ).

title: CEPEX ER-2 Cloud Lidar System (CLS)
summary: The Cloud Lidar System (CLS) was flown aboard the ER-2 to conduct cloud radiation measurements during CEPEX. The  instrument was designed to operate at high altitudes  in order to obtain measurements above the highest clouds  providing the true height of cloud boundaries and the  density structure of less dense clouds. The height  structure of cirrus, cloud top density and multiple cloud layers are also provided. The laser type was ND:YAG I,II. Principal Investigator was Dr. James Spinhirne.

title: Aircraft C-130 Ozone Concentration (Kok)
summary: This dataset contains ozone measurements taken aboard the C-130 aircraft during ACE-1 by Greg Kok (NCAR/RAF). The data consist of time (UTC), location, "fast" ozone (chemiluminescense), and "standard" ozone (UV absorption). These data were processed and quality controlled by NCAR/RAF following the field phase of ACE-1.

title: Aircraft C-130 Flight Line Parameters (Updated 9/18/96)
summary: This dataset contains the NCAR/Research Aviation Facility (RAF) C-130 flight line parameters from the 32 missions flown during ACE-1. These flight line parameters are a subset of the entire parameter list and do not include any experimental or researcher data. Please review the accompanying read.me file for further details. These 1 Hz frequency data have been processed and quality controlled by NCAR/RAF.

title: Aircraft C-130 Carbon Monoxide Concentration (Kok)
summary: This dataset contains carbon monoxide measurements taken aboard the NCAR C-130 aircraft during ACE-1 by Greg Kok (NCAR/RAF). The data consists of time (UTC), location, carbon monoxide (infrared absorption) in ppbv. These data were processed and quality controlled by NCAR/RAF following the field phase of ACE-1.

title: Aircraft C-130 Carbon Dioxide Concentration (Kok)
summary: This dataset contains carbon dioxide measurements taken aboard the NCAR C-130 aircraft during ACE-1 by Greg Kok (NCAR/RAF). The data consists of time (UTC), location, carbon dioxide (infrared absorption). These data were processed and quality controlled by NCAR/RAF following the field phase of ACE-1.

title: Aircraft C-130 Hydrogen Peroxide Concentration (Kok)
summary: This dataset contains hydrogen peroxides measurements taken aboard the NCAR C-130 aircraft during ACE-1 by Greg Kok (NCAR/RAF). The data consists of time (UTC), location, total soluble peroxide concentration measured as hydrogen, concentration of gas-phase hydrogen peroxide (ppbv), concentration of soluble organic hydroperoxides measured as hydrogen, and equivalent concentration of methylhydroperoxide. These data were processed and quality controlled by NCAR/RAF following the field phase of ACE-1.

title: ACARS
summary: ACARS

title: C-130 Chemistry Ozone and Fast Ozone (Faloona/Campos)
summary: The DYCOMS-II Aircraft: C-130 Chemistry Ozone and Fast Ozone dataset is one of several aircraft data sets collected on the C-130 aircraft as part of the Dynamics and Chemistry of Marine Stratocumulus Phase II: Entrainment Studies (DYCOMS-II) project. The data files described herein are separate for the two instruments (slow and fast ozone) named according to the convention: TECO - 131RF??TO3.nc, Fast - 131RF??FO3.nc. Keeping with RAF protocol they are in 1 and 25 Hz NetCDF format, respectively, and all units are parts per billion by volume (ppbv).

title: ACE-ASIA Surface: Kosan Radiation Radiometers (Valero)
summary: The ACE-Asia Surface Kosan Radiation Radiometer (Valero) data are now available online. This data contains radiation measurements made during ACE-ASIA at the surface site on Kosan, Cheju Island, Republic of Korea from March 26, 2001 to May 4, 2001. All data is in NetCDF format.

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Chemistry Atmospheric DMS (Bates)(netCDF)
summary: This dataset contains DMS measurements taken on board the Ron Brown Ship during the ACE-Asia project, March-April 2001.  This data is in netCDF format.  However, the same dataset can also be ordered in an ASCII text format.

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Chemistry Aqueous DMS (Bates)(netCDF)
summary: This dataset contains aqueous DMS measurements taken on board the Ron Brown Ship during the ACE-Asia project, March-April 2001.  This data is in netCDF format.  However, the same dataset can also be ordered in an ASCII text format.

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Aerosol Number Concentration (Covert/Bates) (netCDF)
summary: This dataset contains S02, Radon, and ozone measurements taken on board the Ron Brown Ship during the ACE-Asia project, March-April 2001.  This data is in netCDF format.  However, the same dataset can also be ordered in an ASCII text format.

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Chemistry CO (Johnson)(netCDF)
summary: This dataset contains Carbon Monoxide measurements taken on board the Ron Brown Ship during the ACE-Asia project, March-April 2001.  This data is in netCDF format.  However, the same dataset can also be ordered in an ASCII text format.

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Meteorology Navigation and Surface State Parameters (Johnson)(netCDF)
summary: This dataset contains ship speed, headings, temperature, relative humidity, pressure, insolation, wind and rainfall rate measurements taken on board the Ron Brown Ship during the ACE-Asia project, March-April 2001.  This data is in netCDF format.  However, the same dataset can also be ordered in an ASCII text format.

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Oceanography SST, Salinity (Johnson)(netCDF)
summary: This dataset contains sea surface temperature and salinity measurements taken on board the Ron Brown Ship during the ACE-Asia project, March-April 2001.  This data is in netCDF format.  However, the same dataset can also be ordered in an ASCII text format.

title: ACE-ASIA Aircraft: C-130 Radiation Broadband (TSBR and FSBR) Measurements (Valero)
summary: This dataset contains radiation measurements made during ACE-ASIA on the C-130 aircraft. Archived data consists of four broadband radiometers (two uplooking and two downlooking). In each location one of the broadbands (TSBR or Total Solar Broadband Radiometer) measured the total" solar bandpass and the other (FSBR or Fractional Solar Broadband Radiometer) measured the "fractional" solar bandpass. This data is in .cdf format."

title: ACE-ASIA Aircraft: C-130 Radiation Spectral (TDDR) Measurements (Valero)
summary: This dataset contains radiation measurements made during ACE-ASIA on the C-130 aircraft. Archived data consists of two spectral narrowband radiometers (one uplooking and one downlooking). Each TDDR (Total-Direct-Diffuse Radiometer) had a hemispherical field-of-view, and a scanning shadowband was used (only on the uplooking instrument) to regularly block the sun thus allowing determination of the total, direct, and diffuse components of the radiation field. All data is in .cdf format.

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Aerosol Sub- and super-micron major ions-7 stage (netCDF)(Quinn)
summary: This dataset contains aerosol sub- and super- micron nss sulfate, MSA, ammonium and other major ion measurements, using 7-stage multi-jet cascade impactors, taken aboard the Ron Brown ship during the ACE-Asia field project. This dataset contains the netCDF data files.  Data can also be downloaded in a comma delimited (.csv) format. A readme in PDF format accompanies the dataset when ordered.

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Aerosol light absorption at 550nm (netCDF)(Quinn)
summary: This dataset contains aerosol light absorption measurements at 550nm using a Particle Soot Absorption Photometer (PSAP) taken aboard the Ron Brown ship during the ACE-Asia field project. This dataset contains the netCDF data files.  Data can also be downloaded in a tab delimited (.acf) format.

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Aerosol total and sub-micron light scattering (CDF)(Quinn)
summary: This dataset contains aerosol total and sub-micron light scattering and backscattering measurements using a nephelometer taken aboard the Ron Brown ship during the ACE-Asia field project. This dataset contains the netCDF data files.  Data can also be downloaded in a tab delimited (.acf) format.

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Aerosol Sub- and super-micron major ions-2 stage [Cations](netCDF)(Quinn)
summary: This dataset contains aerosol sub- and super- micron nss sulfate, MSA, ammonium and other major ion measurements, using 2-stage multi-jet cascade impactors, taken aboard the Ron Brown ship during the ACE-Asia field project. This dataset contains the netCDF data files.  Data can also be downloaded in a tab delimited (.acf) format.

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Aerosol Sub- and super-micron major ions-2 stage [Anions](netCDF)(Quinn)
summary: This dataset contains aerosol sub- and super- micron nss sulfate, MSA, ammonium and other major ion measurements, using 2-stage multi-jet cascade impactors, taken aboard the Ron Brown ship during the ACE-Asia field project. This dataset contains the netCDF data files.  Data can also be downloaded in a tab delimited (.acf) format.

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Aerosol Gravimetric analysis of mass as a function of size (netCDF)(Quinn)

title: ACE-ASIA Ship Ron Brown: Aerosol Sub- and super-micron mineral dust (netCDF)(Quinn)
summary: This dataset contains aerosol sub- and super-micron mineral dust concentrations using a spectrometer, taken aboard the Ron Brown ship during the ACE-Asia field project. This dataset contains the netCDF data files.  Data can also be downloaded in a tab delimited (.acf) format.

title: ACE-ASIA Aircraft: C-130 Chemistry O3 and Fast O3 (Campos/Faloona)

title: CEPEX NMC Analyzed Model Fields
summary: This dataset contains selected 12-hourly National Meteorological Center (NMC) Analyzed Model Fields collected during CEPEX. Selected parameter fields include: mean sea level pressure, relative humidity, temperature, and u,v wind components. Grid resolution is 2.5 x 5.0 degrees. There are 5 vertical levels for relative humidity; 10 vertical levels for other parameters. The model output contains 1 analyzed field followed by 9-10 forecast fields for each 12-hour run.

title: New Horizon Oceanography ADCP [Rudnick]
summary: This dataset contains preliminary ADCP data from the EPIC field project's New Horizon Ship. Data provided in netCDF.

title: New Horizon Oceanography CTD [Rudnick]
summary: This dataset contains preliminary CTD data from the EPIC field project's New Horizon Ship. Data provided in netCDF.

title: Precipitable Water and Surface Observation Array [Univ of Arizona]
summary:
This dataset contains precipitable water and surface data collected by the University of Arizona as part of a university-based GPS Network for Atmospheric and Geodetic Research and Education Sponsored by the National Science Foundation. Not all stations in this dataset cover the entire time period. Some start later than the begin date while others end before the end date.

For more information, see the U of Arizona Precipitable Water site at http://www.atmo.arizona.edu/faculty/research/gps/gps_pwv.html.

title: P-3 Meteorological State and Navigation Parameters - slow data (netCDF) [NOAA/AOC]
summary:
This dataset contains the NOAA P-3 (N43RF) State and Navigation parameters from the missions flown during SALLJEX. These netCDF files contain the raw (type 4 record) slow data from the NOAA/AOC standard tape in netCDF format.

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055)

title: SuomiNet Precipitable Water (hourly) Data
summary: SuomiNet is a network of GPS receivers that provide realtime atmospheric precipitable water vapor measurements.  This dataset contains hourly data files of precipitable water vapor measurements collected during the BAMEX time period.

title: NCAR/NSF C-130 Chemistry SO2 and DMS Data [Bandy]
summary:
This data set contains the SO2 and DMS chemistry data from the C-130 aircraft during the RICO project. The data are all 1 second integration of 25 samples per second., with each flight's data in both NetCDF and ASCII file formats. The filenames are in the form: RICO_yyyymmdd_DMS/SO2-LRT-RFff.txt/nc where yyyymmdd is the flight date, the data is either DMS or SO2, RFff is the flight number (01to 19 inclusive), and the file is either netCDF or ASCII format. The values are parts-per-trillion by volume, with -32767 as the missing value.

Also included is a netcdf file for the circle statistics that Bjorn Stevens requested at the data workshop in January 2006.

title: STORM Composite Station List

title: GCIP/GIDS-1 Composite Station List
summary: List of stations whose data are included in the GCIP/GIDS-1 data sets. List includes Station name, latitude, longitude,elevation, station type, observing network ID, WMO Number, and FAA call sign.

title: VORTEX Partial Station List (OBSOLETE)
summary: Partial list of stations whose data are included in the  VORTEX data sets.  List includes Station name, latitude,  longitude,elevation, station type, observing network ID, and station id.

summary: This is currently a link to an ftp site containing hydrographic plots from the United States Coast Guard Cutter (USCGC) Healy (HLY) HLY-02-01, HLY-02-03, and the Polar Star AWS-02-1 cruises of 2002. These plots are subject to revision and will be loaded into the EOL data archive database once they are finalized.

summary: NCEP ETA model 500mb initial analysis map images for the GAPP period.

title: NCEP ETA Model 1000mb Initial Analysis Maps (GIF)
summary: NCEP ETA model 1000mb initial analysis map images for the GAPP period.

title: STORM-FEST 5-minute Surface Land Composite
summary: 5 min composite from data collected at sites with 5 min or less resolution (about 120 sites).  Sites include ASOS, AWOS NWS/FAA, FSL, ICN, HPCN, PAM and USGS).  Data includes  temperature, dewpoint, station pressure, wind speed/ direction and precipitation.  All data converted to a commonformat and quality controlled.

title: Meteorology CPTEC (Brazil) Forecast Products: Eta 20 km
summary:
This dataset contains the CPTEC 20 km model GIF images generated during the SALLJEX field campaign. (These images are the same as found in the SALLJEX Field Catalog.)

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: SALLJEX Enhanced Raingage Network Data
summary:
SALLJEX precipitation database version 3

This database includes a highly dense spatial coverage of daily precipitation data for the period 15/Nov/02-15/Feb/03 over Argentina, Paraguay and Uruguay and only GTS data over the rest of the countries in the SALLJEX region. 

Each record has the following information separated by the character ;": day; month; hour; latitude; longitude; observation; observation code; Station name; Province ;Country; Institution name.  See the readme file for more specific information.

title: ASOS China Lake, CA 1-minute Data [NAVAIRWD China Lake]
summary: This data set contains 1-minute resolution surface meteorological data from the Automated Surface Observing System (ASOS) stations located at the Naval Air Weapons Station (NAWS) China Lake during the Terrain-induced Rotor Experiment (T-REX).  These data were provided by NAWS China Lake for the T-REX period (March and April 2006).  Each gzipped file contains one day of data.  The data are in comma-delimited ASCII.

title: China Lake HANDAR Hourly Data [NAVAIRWD China Lake]
summary: This data set contains hourly resolution surface meteorological data during the Terrain-induced Rotor Experiment (T-REX) from the Naval Air Weapons Station (NAWS) China Lake network of 12 HANDAR weather stations. These data were provided by NAWS China Lake for the T-REX period (March and April 2006). The data are in Excel format and each file contains two months of data for a station.

title: China Lake HANDAR 5-minute Data [NAVAIRWD China Lake]
summary: This data set contains 5-minute resolution surface meteorological data during the Terrain-induced Rotor Experiment (T-REX) from the Naval Air Weapons Station (NAWS) China Lake network of 8 HANDAR weather stations. These data were provided by NAWS China Lake for the T-REX period (March and April 2006). Each gzipped file contains one month of data for a station. The data include wind, temperature, humidity and pressure. The data are in columnar ASCII format.

title: CPTEC Enhanced Analysis (initial data for experiment 3)
summary:
This data set is provided by the CPTEC/INPE-Brazil and contains the initial and boundary conditions in binary files to be used as input to the models for experiment #3. A GRADS control file is included.

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055).

title: ACE-ASIA Aircraft: C-130 Aerosol Number Size Distribution, 8-120 nm (L.Russell)
summary: This dataset contains C-130 aircraft data readings of Aerosol Number size distribution between 8 and 120 nm.  Taken by Lynn Russell during the ACE-ASIA field project.

title: NWS Radar Data KAMX Miami Aug 25-6 (Katrina) [McNoldy, CSU]

This dataset contains gif movies of land based radar data collected during Katrina at NWS Miami station KAMX. This dataset covers the time period Aug 25 12:00-Aug 26 05:55 and shows Katrina crossing Florida. These data were downloaded from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA)
Office of Oceanic and Atmospheric Research Atlantic Oceanographic and Meteorological Laboratory (AOML) Hurricane Research Division (HRD) Mission Catalog Katrina 2005 Radar Data page.

title: NWS Radar Data KLIX Slidel Aug 28-9 (Katrina) [McNoldy, CSU]
summary:

These data were downloaded from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA)
Office of Oceanic and Atmospheric Research Atlantic Oceanographic and Meteorological Laboratory (AOML) Hurricane Research Division (HRD) Mission Catalog Katrina 2005 Radar Data page.

title: AFWA MM5 45 km Imagery

title: NWS Radar Data KBYX Key West Sep 20 (Rita) [McNoldy, CSU]

These data were downloaded from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) Office of Oceanic and Atmospheric Research Atlantic Oceanographic and Meteorological Laboratory (AOML) Hurricane Research Division (HRD) Mission Catalog Rita 2005 Radar Data page.

Data is grouped into one minute files and they are viewable using Solo software available through NCAR/EOL. This is the raw radar data.

title: NEXRAD Radar composite - Atlantic Coast

title: NEXRAD Radar composite - Gulf Coast
summary: This dataset contains NEXRAD radar data around the United States coast of the Gulf of Mexico.

title: NEXRAD Radar composite - Puerto Rico Vicinity
summary: This dataset contains NEXRAD radar data around Puerto Rico.

title: AFWA MM5 45km Imagery
summary: These data are AFWA MM5 Forecast product model images for the last half of the field phase of the T-REX experiment. Data are available for 31 March 2006 - 30 April 2006,. They are at 45km resolution.

title: RICO Graduate Seminar Series

This data set covers the period from 1 June to 31 July 2002.  The data are in GEMPAK format. NOTE: The precipitation for the AWOS stations within this data set have a known problem.  See the readme file for complete information.  Correct 1-minute resolution AWOS precipitation data are available as a companion dataset.

The ABLE EBBR was located at the Whitewater, KS site during the BAMEX period. Data cover the period from 20 May to 7 July 2003. The data are in columnar ASCII format.

title: ABLE ECOR Data [DOE]

summary: This data set contains the cloud radar flight track imagery from the flights of the Wyoming King Air aircraft.
